window.OP_SEARCH_INDEX = [
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-antidote%20%5B1132034939655831633%5D.html', label: 'op-antidote', searchLabel: 'op antidote', text: 'operation antidote operation antidote black-kit paratrooper raid after sundown to seize sealed polonium-210 vials, interrogate the buyer, eliminate zahar and sentinel principals, and locate the clandestine lab before the cargo disappears under alert. departure erewhon after sundown insertion haho to nearby abandoned site uniform black kits follow-on intel hogweed station, fen bog situation an undercover source in whalers bay reports sentinel is selling sealed polonium-210 vials to a mysterious buyer arriving tonight. sigint ties the transaction to special sentinel unit zahar. the source has gone silent and may be held at one of the target sites. he may still have in-person intelligence, so proceed carefully and search for him. execution haho into the ao, move site-to-site without triggering radio alarms, and immediately recover the vials if compromised because sentinel can relocate them within minutes. alpha wind farm w02: kill russ lawson and the two aides managing cargo movement. bravo / charlie interrogate the buyer at whalers bay airfield, then secure fanny bay port and obtain depot access from the zahar commander. delta clear toxic storage depot, verify polonium-210 in the secure room, call cbrn, and debrief on-site. alert risk if a radio operator detects the team, assume only minutes remain before the vials are relocated. buyer lead interrogation should reveal russian-contractor ties and a telephone number before the buyer is eliminated and hidden. optional site if time permits, investigate anchor point station north of the route for extra intelligence. objective alpha wind farm w02 eliminate russ lawson and his two aides responsible for transporting the high-risk cargo. objective bravo whalers bay airfield interrogate the buyer without raising the alarm, identify his backers, then disappear the body. objective charlie fanny bay port secure the port, neutralize zahar personnel, and force secure-room access from the commander or recover a finger. objective delta toxic storage depot destroy remaining zahar, secure the depot, confirm the sealed polonium-210 vials, and search for lab intel.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-backhand%20%5B1131651353249337494%5D.html', label: 'op-backhand', searchLabel: 'op backhand', text: 'operation backhand operation backhand immediate helicopter assault into south wild coast to demolish the electric engine factory drone shipment and then wipe out the wolves blue tiger qrf before they can weaponize executions against civilians. origin asf hq / tier 1 insertion overseer helicopter, green kit specialist demolition expert required exfil hq or nearby safe site situation four hours after operation oculus, gottlieb used the planted beacon to track the stolen shipment to electric engine factory in south wild coast. chatter confirms the crate holds a new lethal drone type from golem island. the wolves intend to use the drone against non-cooperative civilians and broadcast the executions, so the factory and shipment must be sabotaged immediately. execution deploy from hq by overseer, use overwatch because both sites show heavy enemy presence, and conduct eyes-only reconnaissance because cyclops is down and rc-gps jammers are active. alpha clear and demolish electric engine factory and inspect nearby toos or missing outcast reports. bravo destroy blue tiger at the northwest lake bulkington outpost and seize actionable intel. debrief exfil to hq or a safe site for post-action reporting. isr gap no drone isr is available. sentinel jammers and cyclops maintenance mean binoculars and optics only. friendly concern reports indicate missing outcast operators in the ao, so inspect the factory perimeter for allies in trouble. overwatch ort-7 ground reporting points to heavy enemy presence at both locations, making overwatch strongly recommended. objective alpha electric engine factory clear the facility, destroy the drone shipment, and sabotage the production site. objective bravo blue tiger outpost eliminate the wolves qrf northwest of lake bulkington and collect all relevant intel.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-black-fin%20%5B1147893075696431176%5D.html', label: 'op-black-fin', searchLabel: 'op black fin', text: 'operation black fin operation black fin night halo maritime insertion for a six-site combat-diver sweep across northeast coastal black sites, restoring friendly control, hunting pows, and breaking enemy sea-air denial between moa island and sinking country. departure asf hq by helicopter at 1900 insertion high-altitude halo to maritime ip team combat divers / scuba capable isr cyclops grounded, mini-drones only situation enemy forces occupy six key maritime locations across the disputed northeast coastline, blocking movement between moa island and sinking country and using the sites as black-site interrogation locations for captured allies. command intent is to recapture the full set of nodes, re-establish friendly presence in the ao, and search every objective for pows and exploitable material. execution fly from asf hq at altitude, halo onto the maritime ip, and clear the objective chain with stealth and precision while using organic mini-drones for local reconnaissance. freedom of action command has authorized flexible handling of each objective as long as recapture and pow search are achieved. search standard check all locations for prisoners and sensitive intelligence. return complete foxtrot at ancient village and rtb from there. no air isr cyclops is unavailable, so every site entry depends on mini-drone reconnaissance and team-level stealth. hvt note at camp tiger, the target is any wolf encountered in the underground bunker. kit use the scuba combat-diver loadout or the operation amber sky "nokk" skin equivalent. objective alpha bunker edgehod north infiltrate the bunker and secure enemy documents while checking for pows. objective bravo camp tiger capture the high-value target inside the underground bunker and exploit the site. objective charlie bunker edgehod south sabotage enemy munitions stockpiles and deny future use of the bunker. objective delta control station tiger 02 recapture the local communications net and establish a listening post. objective echo drone station w051 neutralize enemy surveillance capability protecting the coastal corridor. objective foxtrot ancient village secure the village for homesteaders under sustained attack and rtb from foxtrot.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-black-knight%20%5B1132394344469512273%5D.html', label: 'op-black-knight', searchLabel: 'op black knight', text: 'operation black knight operation black knight conquest-mode coastal infiltration from owl forest bivouac into the mn.copper ao to destroy sam coverage, retake channels r&d center, secure project: claw data, and capture onyx for interrogation. ao channels / good hope mountain border recommended time 1700 step-off, nightfall by r&d center insertion watercraft from owl forest bivouac extract call lightning 1-2 with onyx situation bodark forces seized channels r&d center to steal project: claw research and other skell technology data. they have reinforced the ao\'s air defenses enough to deny a direct aerial approach. sigint indicates bodark cyber specialist onyx may be on site supervising the breach. capturing him is a cia priority because of prior government-network intrusions. execution insert by boat, clear murmur drone coverage, demolish the electric grid control sams and comms relay, remove the hilltop sam, then assault the r&d center and strip the servers. start depart owl forest bivouac and acquire watercraft for the coastal approach. suppress neutralize murmur uavs and destroy all marked sam systems with c4. exploit download claw data, wipe servers, detain onyx, and extract to hq. air denial multiple sam sites and the main comms relay must be demolished before extraction is safe. target onyx can be represented by any enemy near the servers inside channels r&d center. data handling secure project: claw research first, then wipe the servers to prevent follow-on bodark exploitation. objective alpha murmur drone screen clear the hostile uav layer protecting the coastal ingress route and outcast scout lanes. objective bravo electric grid control secure the site and demo all local sams plus the primary communications relay antenna. objective charlie hilltop sam move southwest and destroy the elevated sam emplacement with c4. objective delta channels r&d center retake the center, capture onyx, secure project: claw, and call lightning 1-2 for extract.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-black-talon%20%5B1132026638339690576%5D.html', label: 'op-black-talon', searchLabel: 'op black talon', text: 'operation black talon operation black talon push qrf from army pass, recover both captured night owl elements from auroa survival shelter and red weasel outpost, and exploit any sentinel intelligence before returning unless new targets of opportunity appear. first ip army pass, southeast of auroa survival shelter friendly force outcast team night owl challenge new moon response watchful eye situation our reconnaissance coverage depends on outcast ground teams because manpower is stretched thin and aerial isr alone cannot cover the rugged terrain. night owl was captured while investigating auroa survival shelter. cyclops tracked sentinel movement and confirmed one element remains at the shelter while the second was transferred to red weasel outpost for interrogation. both are alive as of the latest isr. execution move from army pass to the first detention site, recover the alpha element, search for actionable intelligence, then assault red weasel outpost and recover bravo. id procedure use challenge "new moon" and expect "watchful eye" before opening cells. primary task rescue both outcast elements and conduct site exploitation. follow-on if routes and tempo allow, extend into nearby toos and rtb. warning hostages are split between two separate sentinel-held compounds. expect pressure at the first site and a harder interrogation posture at red weasel outpost. too options drone station w111, natural hazards control, bunker edgehod south, camp weasel, auroa weather station, and nearby checkpoints remain candidate follow-on targets. isr source armaros imagery from cyclops confirms site layouts and detention points for alpha and bravo rescue phases. objective alpha auroa survival shelter recover the first night owl element and search the shelter for actionable sentinel intelligence. objective bravo red weasel outpost recover the second night owl element, exploit the interrogation site, and prepare rtb.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-blue-remedy%20%5B1132362938343243787%5D.html', label: 'op-blue-remedy', searchLabel: 'op blue remedy', text: 'operation blue remedy operation blue remedy halo from south cape station into channels, knock out the eagle sam site, secure step up startup, and lock down the extended perimeter so the amber ruin antidote work can continue under friendly protection. briefing south cape station insertion max-altitude halo to designated lz priority prevent any lab compromise authority all perimeter toos greenlit situation at step up startup in south channels, skell scientists and outcasts are racing to produce an antidote to the amber ruin nerve agent. this is the only facility on auroa with the equipment needed to finish the work. intel indicates a sentinel unit has learned about the project and is moving to destroy research material and execute or capture allied personnel. site communications are already lost. execution deploy from south cape station, stay at maximum altitude to avoid radar, jump into the lz, and clear outward through the objective chain until the whole security belt is stable. ingress halo into channels airspace and assemble at the lz. secure neutralize the sam threat, retake step up startup, and call overlord. expand capture the power plant, checkpoint, and barracks, then rtb. threat sentinel is expected to push directly on the lab and erase antidote research. speed and violent perimeter control are required. friendly fireteams overlord, dagger, specter, and panther are standing by to hold captured nodes once each site is secured. isr security footage confirms active antidote work in the main lab and recovering civilians in the treatment unit who will be moved to erewhon. objective alpha eagle sam site disable the sam position before the team is exposed to sustained air-defense coverage. objective bravo step up startup secure the lab, protect scientists and outcasts, and radio fireteam overlord to take the site. objective charlie auroa power plant capture the power node, exploit sentinel intel, and call in dagger to hold it. objective delta checkpoint shark charlie clear the checkpoint and hand control to specter for route security. objective echo abandoned barracks capture the barracks, call panther, and complete the perimeter before rtb.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-codebreaker%20%5B1134469686172602388%5D.html', label: 'op-codebreaker', searchLabel: 'op codebreaker', text: 'operation codebreaker operation codebreaker haho from erewhon to the lz north of the a.i. experimental center, covertly plant comint devices on six antennas across alpha and bravo, then retake darkwood island port and exploit what sentinel was moving through the site. insertion haho to lz north of a.i. experimental center primary payload 4 comint devices at alpha, 2 at bravo stealth constraint no radio alerts at alpha or bravo end state devices transmitting, darkwood port retaken, rtb situation after the previous operation, the team recovered sentinel\'s asymmetric encryption keys. the mission now is to decode and intercept sentinel traffic in real time to break their opsec, generate intelligence, and support counterattacks. the operation has three tasks: bug the antennas at the a.i. experimental center, bug campus relay station atop sugarloaf mount, then recapture darkwood island port and investigate the smuggling chain. execution keep alpha and bravo covert so sentinel doesn\'t realize their comms are compromised. hostiles in the way are greenlit, but no outgoing radio alarms. alpha plant intercept devices on the four antennas at the a.i. experimental center. bravo move to campus relay station on sugarloaf mount and plant devices on both antennas. charlie retake darkwood island port, clear 20+ hostiles, exploit the site, confirm all devices transmit, and rtb. low footprint alpha and bravo must stay covert so sentinel continues broadcasting over compromised channels and a future counterattack can be planned. darkwood resistance isr estimates 20+ hostiles at darkwood island port. capture or eliminate resistance, then recover actionable shipping intel. audio note a local voice message is preserved below in the support section for briefing reference. objective alpha a.i. experimental center install four comint intercept devices across the tactical antennas and avoid radio compromise. objective bravo campus relay station reach sugarloaf mount, plant devices on both relay antennas, and keep the station silent. objective charlie darkwood island port recapture the port, clear or capture resistance, and exploit all records tied to sentinel cargo movement.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-cold-resolve%20%5B1132368729414574151%5D.html', label: 'op-cold-resolve', searchLabel: 'op cold resolve', text: 'operation cold resolve operation cold resolve deploy from erewhon at sundown in white winter kit, land near mathilda\'s palace, eliminate the eclipse unit meeting and mass-grave operation, then capture camp black widow, auroa data farm, and pumping station to secure south-central silent mountain. insertion abandoned homesteader site lz near mathilda\'s palace kit warm white snow-camouflage loadout primary threat sentinel eclipse unit at mathilda\'s palace end state three critical structures captured, rtb situation after weeks of fighting, the goal is to seize south-central silent mountain\'s key structures and convert them into friendly operating bases. cyclops isr identified an eclipse unit secret meeting at mathilda\'s palace and spotted them burying bodies in a mass-grave tunnel at the nearby cemetery. execution strike mathilda\'s palace first from the nearby lz, call in perimeter security once each objective is captured, and continue through the infrastructure chain. mathilda\'s palace eliminate eclipse unit and radio crow to hold perimeter. black widow / data farm capture camp black widow for a future fob and auroa data farm for secure-channel access, then call avalanche and dagger. pumping station secure the data farm\'s water-cooling link and radio lynx to hold perimeter. mass grave tunnel the cemetery tunnel at mathilda\'s palace is a confirmed body-burial site. future fob camp black widow is intended to become the team\'s main forward operating base in this sector after capture. signals value auroa data farm should reveal how much of skell technology\'s secure traffic sentinel controls. objective alpha mathilda\'s palace stop the eclipse unit meeting, and hand perimeter control to crow. objective bravo camp black widow capture the camp as a future main fob and radio avalanche to secure the perimeter. objective charlie auroa data farm seize the data infrastructure, prepare for sigint exploitation, and call dagger to hold the site. objective delta pumping station capture the water-cooling node linked to data farm and radio lynx to secure it.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-coral%20%5B1132027448746332180%5D.html', label: 'op-coral', searchLabel: 'op coral', text: 'operation coral operation coral twin operation to op staghorn. infiltrate from seal passage at sundown in low-profile civilian clothing, secure five south liberty civilian areas, gather trafficking intel fast, then eliminate eclipse unit at liberty airport and rtb to south cape station. insertion seal passage bivouac / western infil cover low-profile civilian clothes, concealed armor and compact weapons threat sentinel eclipse unit / civilian abductions exfil south cape station after liberty airport is secure situation sentinel\'s eclipse unit has invaded civilian areas in south liberty city and is abducting civilians, including teenagers, while abusing women during transport to unknown destinations. the mission is time-sensitive: secure the targeted residential areas, locate intel on where civilians are being taken, and destroy the liberty airport trafficking node. execution move fast through each civilian objective, assist residents, secure each area, and collect only high-value intel rather than deep-clearing every room. residential sweep clear john dewey residences, maunga nui eco park, autumn lake district, ayn rand residences, and frederic bastiat residences. intel push search for evidence of transfer routes and destination sites while keeping pace. liberty airport eliminate eclipse unit, secure the airport, then rtb to south cape station. no aerial recon liberty airport radar coverage and urgency prevent aerial isr. work from poc-provided ground intel and visual checks. low-profile kit wear plate carriers under clothing when possible. minimal chest rigs are acceptable, but keep visible military gear to a minimum. concealed smg a sleeveless jacket can work as a low-profile weapon sling for a compact smg during movement through civilian areas. objective alpha john dewey residences secure civilians, stabilize the site, and collect any actionable trafficking intel. objective bravo maunga nui eco park assist civilians, clear eclipse personnel, and search quickly for route or detention clues. objective charlie autumn lake district secure the housing block and recover any evidence of where prisoners are being moved. objective delta ayn rand residences clear the site, protect remaining civilians, and keep the team moving toward the airport target. objective echo frederic bastiat residences finish the final residential sweep and consolidate any intelligence pointing to liberty airport. objective foxtrot liberty airport eliminate eclipse unit, stop the trafficking pipeline, secure the airport, and rtb.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-corrosion%20%5B1144981396364988567%5D.html', label: 'op-corrosion', searchLabel: 'op corrosion', text: 'operation corrosion operation corrosion deploy in greens from hq to hlz salamander, search the hvt\'s last known trail, rescue doctor mason grady at the emergency center, identify the flood by the large bandage on his left arm, and extract him alive to erewhon. insertion hlz salamander, then foot patrol to airship air station primary target the flood / smuggler of narcotics and class 6 hazmat key asset doctor mason grady, emergency center constraint no radio alarm to enemy toc situation local recon finally has a lead on the enemy officer codenamed the flood, briefly spotted in a convoy near the fen bog border. he is tied to narcotics and class 6 hazardous-material smuggling across auroa. doctor mason grady, working under duress at the emergency center, confirms the hvt was treated there and discharged this afternoon. grady will provide the target\'s current location if he is rescued. execution search the hvt\'s trail, interrogate associates, rescue grady, then move on the target location and capture the flood alive if a current fix is obtained. alpha / bravo search airship air station and the checkpoint for actionable intel and movement logs. charlie clear the emergency center, move doctor grady to the rally point, and obtain the hvt\'s current location. delta if grady confirms outpost red tiger, pid the arm bandage, mark the hvt, and extract him alive. radio silence if a radio alarm reaches enemy toc, the flood may disappear again. prevent calls from leaving each site. grady handling any civilian in a white lab coat inside the emergency center can roleplay doctor grady. rescue means clear the site and direct him to the outcast rally point. hvt pid grady identifies the target by a large bandage on his left arm and places him at outpost red tiger, 2.2 km northwest of the emergency center. objective alpha airship air station search the site by any means necessary for actionable intelligence on the flood and his network. objective bravo checkpoint search recover logs and movement records that indicate where the hvt and his associates are operating. objective charlie emergency center rescue doctor grady, secure the area, and obtain the flood\'s current location. objective delta outpost red tiger find the bandaged hvt, confirm pid with optics or drone, capture him alive, and exfil to erewhon.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-crescendo%20%5B1132028002922930357%5D.html', label: 'op-crescendo', searchLabel: 'op crescendo', text: 'operation crescendo operation crescendo infiltrate from twin islands bivouac, copy all four distributed murmur a.i. functions without damaging the infrastructure, and beat the 35-minute server-lock timer that starts after the first breach. command asf hq / tier 1 insertion twin islands bivouac primary payload full murmur a.i. module across four sites constraint 35-minute lockout after first server security breach situation after clemens auer\'s rescue in op solaris, his infrastructure knowledge gives a path to regain control of murmur drones around auroa by recovering and restoring the a.i. module. the module is split across four infrastructures transmitting live data through long-range antennas. preserve those systems intact so they can be used after the sites are secured. execution move from twin islands bivouac through all tos, secure each location, copy that site\'s a.i. function, and keep the pace tight once alpha\'s server breach starts the lockout timer. alpha / bravo recover flight-path and target-acquisition modules from the underwater cable station and sentinel corp. server rooms. charlie / delta copy armament, power-management, and testing algorithms from the a.i. experimental center and driftwood islets atc tower. preserve infrastructure do not damage antennas, server rooms, or station hardware needed for post-mission control. 35-minute lockout once the first server\'s security is breached, all servers lock after 35 minutes. missing that window means the full module cannot be recovered. recommended team build have drones active with an est specialist on the team to support movement and site control. alpha entrance the underwater cable station is underground. its cave entrance sits near the insertion point along the south coastline. objective alpha underwater cable station deep inside the station, locate the server room hosting the initial drone flight-path module and copy it. objective bravo sentinel corp. location secure the server room responsible for target acquisition and make a clean copy of that function. objective charlie a.i. experimental center enter the data-storage building and recover the armament function without damaging the facility. objective delta driftwood islets testing zone secure the atc tower and copy the final power-management function and testing algorithms.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-fragma%20%5B1148247568258711575%5D.html', label: 'op-fragma', searchLabel: 'op fragma', text: 'operation fragma operation fragma foot-move from pleasant island bivouac near sunset across the liberty and restricted area 01 border, disrupt the dam-breach plot, investigate drone transport and prisoner abuse, and exfil to fob bandit for debrief with the outcast poc. mode conquest mode on insertion pleasant island bivouac / sunset foot patrol ao liberty / restricted area 01 border region exfil fob bandit, east liberty ancient fort situation a rogue sentinel unit working with bodarks plans to breach jace skell dam, risking downstream devastation to the auroa solar power plant and potentially threatening auroa parliament. intel also indicates bodarks are moving lethal drones through outpost red fox and may be holding prisoners there as live test subjects at the training center, while the dam unit prepares to target outcast leadership. execution move on foot from pleasant island bivouac, perform all reconnaissance from the ground because hostile air defense blocks aerial isr, and watch for outcast patrols in the ao. dam plot investigate and disrupt the rogue unit\'s plan around jace skell dam before a breach can be triggered. red fox / training center interdict lethal-drone transport, locate prisoners, and confirm whether live-target testing is underway. bandit debrief collect any documents tied to attacks on outcast leadership and deliver the findings to the poc at fob bandit. no aerial recon hostile air-defense coverage means aerial reconnaissance is not feasible. expect to build the picture from ground movement and close site exploitation. friendly friction outcast patrols may be active in the ao. maintain pid and avoid blue-on-blue contact while moving between objectives. prisoner urgency if detainees are found at red fox or the training center, protecting them takes priority over secondary target exploitation. objective alpha jace skell dam stop the planned breach, clear the rogue detachment, and recover any intel on the floodwave operation. objective bravo outpost red fox cut the bodark drone-transport route, search for prisoners, and gather evidence on the logistics chain. objective charlie training center confirm or disrupt lethal-drone live-target testing and secure any captives or operational plans. objective delta fob bandit exfil to east liberty ancient fort and debrief the outcast point of contact with all recovered intel.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-horseman%20%5B1132364165735010315%5D.html', label: 'op-horseman', searchLabel: 'op horseman', text: 'operation horseman operation horseman deploy from erewhon after 2020, land at the lz, investigate alpha centauri residences for jonathan mayne, trace his movement through skell security and control station viper 04, then rescue him at outpost green viper. deployment urgent qrf from erewhon after 2020 hours initial site alpha centauri residences / northwest infinity vip jonathan mayne, skell tech ml engineer, st-1 clearance end state mayne rescued, recovery team called, rtb situation at 2016 hours erewhon received a distress call reporting jonathan mayne\'s abduction from alpha centauri residences. sentinel personnel searched the residences at gunpoint and used aggressive interrogations. humint says mayne may be coerced into working for a wolves unit. his st-1 access and lethal-drone ml expertise make him a vip who must be located immediately. execution secure the residences, exploit mayne\'s home lab, follow the work trail to skell security, then push north to viper 04 and outpost green viper. residences clear alpha centauri residences and search for clues on mayne\'s location. skell security / viper 04 search the skell transport offices, then interrogate enemies at control station viper 04. green viper secure outpost green viper, free the prisoners, call recovery, and rtb. vip risk the wolves cannot be allowed to exploit mayne\'s drone-targeting knowledge. speed matters more than broad site exploitation. lab lead at the residences, mayne\'s home lab should reveal that he works in the skell transport building at skell security. transfer lead at skell transport, a calendar note points to a meeting at control station viper 04, where interrogation reveals a transfer to outpost green viper. objective alpha alpha centauri residences secure the residential area and exploit mayne\'s home lab for evidence of where sentinel took him. objective bravo skell security / skell transport search the offices, confirm mayne is absent, and recover the meeting note pointing north. objective charlie control station viper 04 interrogate any enemy for mayne\'s whereabouts and identify the prisoner transfer route. objective delta outpost green viper clear the outpost, gather final intel, free mayne and the other scientist, then radio recovery and rtb.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-marrow%20%5B1132031176324960257%5D.html', label: 'op-marrow', searchLabel: 'op marrow', text: 'operation marrow operation marrow bigfoot departs erewhon at 2203 in a technical, exploits the lima 3 barrel dump east of white giant, ambushes drone station w041, tracks stewmaker\'s operation to the chem-extraction complex, and clears silent valley mine before returning with samples and intel. callsign qrf bigfoot step-off 2203 from erewhon / technical patrol primary target arthur murillo, alias stewmaker collection barrel samples, comms intel, and kill confirmation photo situation decrypted sigint captured a sentinel commander discussing body-disposal methods and confirmed arthur murillo, flown in from bolivia, as the stewmaker responsible for dissolving prisoner bodies in chemical solutions. thirty minutes ago reaper observed a convoy crash east of white giant. the spilled barrels match stewmaker\'s m.o., and the enemy is regrouping at drone station w041 to recover the cargo. execution exploit the crash cargo first, then hit w041, follow the comms trail to the chemical site, and finish by rescuing civilians at silent valley mine. lima 3 secure the barrel dump site and collect samples from multiple barrels. dsw041 ambush the recovery detachment, exploit the comms building, and deliver the supply truck to the nearest abandoned outcast site northeast. chem-extraction / silent valley eliminate stewmaker, upload a confirmation photo, then clear silent valley mine after reaper reports civilians held there. tribute tasking this opord is a ghost recon wildlands tribute and intentionally centers on the stewmaker storyline and barrel-site exploitation. enemy strength drone station w041 isr estimates roughly 14 hostiles. all targets of opportunity tied to civilian disappearances are greenlit. extraction return to erewhon by requested extract or by vehicle once samples, comms intel, and stewmaker confirmation are secured. objective alpha site lima 3 secure the crashed cargo site east of white giant and gather chemical evidence from the dumped barrels. objective bravo drone station w041 ambush the regrouping detachment, clear the station, and pull comms intel pointing to stewmaker\'s operating location. objective charlie chem-extraction complex secure the chemical facility, eliminate stewmaker, and send a confirmation photo to toc. objective delta silent valley mine move immediately to the mine, free the civilians, and prevent further casualties from the linked detachment.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-miscible%20%5B1131642235516104806%5D.html', label: 'op-miscible', searchLabel: 'op miscible', text: 'operation miscible operation miscible deploy from erewhon by overseer, clear three new argyll production sites, identify and sample the unknown chemical, capture any hvt alive, convoy the poisoned goods north to the disposal point, destroy the load with c4, and exfil from hlz harrier. command asf hq / tier 1 insertion erewhon hq to lz by overseer, then foot patrol priority intel chemical sample and evidence of poisoned shipment chain exfil hlz harrier on sween mountain, with hvt if captured situation homesteaders and outcasts have been hospitalized or killed after consuming products traced to three skell-built sites in new argyll. sentinel seized those facilities about a week ago. evidence indicates sentinel is poisoning selected goods with an unidentified chemical and shipping them to a targeted area to quietly suppress local resistance. execution secure each facility in sequence, gather intel, load poisoned goods into a vehicle, and convoy north for c4 disposal. capture commanders or radio operators alive when possible. alpha clear new argyll winery, exploit the top-floor makeshift lab, and collect a chemical sample. bravo / charlie search for hvts, secure each site, collect intel, and keep loading poisoned goods into the convoy vehicle. disposal / exfil destroy the load at the northern disposal point, then move to hlz harrier on sween mountain. pid discipline multiple civilians are present on site. hostiles are greenlit, but pid a visible weapon before engaging to prevent friendly-fire or collateral incidents. hvt handling if a commander, radio operator, or other senior hostile is found, capture alive and extract to hq for interrogation. chemical source at alpha, the unknown substance originates from a top-floor makeshift lab. prioritize samples and documentation from that space. objective alpha new argyll winery secure the site, collect lab intel and a chemical sample from the top floor, then load poisoned goods for convoy. objective bravo juice processing center look for an hvt, clear the facility, collect intel, and add all poisoned goods to the vehicle. objective charlie brewery repeat bravo tasking: secure, exploit, search for hvt, and load remaining contaminated products. objective delta disposal point / hlz harrier drive north, destroy the vehicle and poisoned shipment with c4, then extract from sween mountain.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-moon-lake%20%5B1132397396798734456%5D.html', label: 'op-moon-lake', searchLabel: 'op moon lake', text: 'operation moon lake operation moon lake start at night from the no man highland crash site with only a pistol and minimal clothing, survive, scavenge civilian shelter gear, procure weapons on-site, interrogate outpost red ferret, protect auroa weather station, and finish at camp weasel. start point no man highland bivouac / crash site at night starting loadout t-shirt, pants, pistol only / iron sights, no suppressor primary target wolves lieutenant at camp weasel condition lost radio contact with fireteam mamba, beacons still active situation outcast scout team 5 observed dead civilians being dumped into moon lake from a truck near misty ridge. tracking points to a wolves lieutenant operating from camp weasel. fireteam mamba was sent to eliminate him but was shot down by a sam. your team begins at the crash site with minimal gear and must recover combat capability on the move. execution stabilize from the crash, move to shelter, scavenge civilian cold-weather clothing only, then use on-site procurement at outpost red ferret to arm up and push the mission forward. abandoned site move west for shelter and pick up warmer civilian clothing and a beanie, but no military weapons or armor yet. outpost red ferret interrogate enemies, gather intel, and procure weapons, vests, headgear, radio, and mobile equipment as you clear. follow-on strike use red ferret intel to defend auroa weather station, then infiltrate camp weasel and eliminate the lieutenant. follow up intel interrogation at red ferret should reveal an imminent attack on auroa weather station and lethal-drone testing tied to camp weasel. weather station priority once red ferret is cleared, secure auroa weather station, protect civilians, and collect any actionable intelligence before moving on camp weasel. pid requirement after camp weasel is secured, photograph the hvt\'s body for positive identification, then return to base promptly. objective alpha crash site / no man highland survive the crash and move out from the bivouac with only your pistol and bare-minimum clothing. objective bravo abandoned site shelter recover from exposure and gather civilian supplies only, especially warmer clothing and a beanie. objective charlie outpost red ferret clear the post, interrogate enemy personnel, and procure the weapons and field gear needed to continue. objective delta auroa weather station interdict the pending assault, safeguard all civilians, and exploit the site for additional intel. objective echo camp weasel infiltrate the camp, eliminate all hostiles, designate and kill the lieutenant hvt, and capture pid photography.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-oculus%20%5B1131649996693983353%5D.html', label: 'op-oculus', searchLabel: 'op oculus', text: 'operation oculus operation oculus depart erewhon near sundown in greens, helocast behind the stubb bay island, take a boat to the wild coast, reclaim ancient harbour, then covertly tag the shipment crate at storage depot and extract at hlz grizzly. departure erewhon hq near sundown / green uniforms insertion helocast behind stubb bay island, then boat infiltration primary task track the golem island shipment and tag its crate exfil hlz grizzly / long valley bivouac situation tristan gottlieb at outcast toc intercepted chatter about a mystery shipment arriving from golem island by armed patrol boat and being received at ancient harbour in northwest wild coast. the shipment is now held at storage depot in long valley. nearby drone factories suggest the crate likely contains critical classified components tied to a larger program. execution insert quietly by water, move from the coast to alpha, hand ancient harbour to outcasts once secure, then patrol to bravo and tag the target crate without alerting the enemy. helocast drop behind the island to avoid detection and link up with the boat. alpha secure ancient harbour, search for shipment clues, and call in outcasts to take over. bravo covertly place a tracking beacon on the main-warehouse crate, then move to hlz grizzly. do not alert bravo the storage depot task is covert beacon placement. avoid triggering alarms or firefights that could cause the crate to be moved early. ancient harbour clues search the port thoroughly before pushing inland. the shipment\'s handling trail at alpha may reveal which factory or program bravo is feeding. follow-on this operation sets up a later deployment tied to the crate\'s destination, referenced in the archive as op backhand. objective alpha ancient harbour secure the harbour, inspect the area for traces of the incoming shipment, and radio outcasts to assume control once clear. objective bravo storage depot without alerting the enemy, tag the shipping crate in the main warehouse with a tracking beacon to monitor its next movement. objective charlie hlz grizzly break contact cleanly after beacon placement and move to long valley bivouac for extraction. intel reference warehouse cctv gottlieb\'s captured cctv frame confirms the crate\'s location inside the bravo warehouse and should guide terminal approach.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-orca%20%5B1132751109174345839%5D.html', label: 'op-orca', searchLabel: 'op orca', text: 'operation orca operation orca falcon deploys from leviathan bivouac by armed helicopter, inserts alpha at the maritime ip, clears four north channels objectives for outcast fireteam harrier, and extracts once ancient village, oceanic power plant, ancient harbor, and blue cove station are secured. mode conquest / fireteam falcon insertion leviathan bivouac to maritime ip by armed helicopter friendly support outcast fireteam harrier standing by at toc extraction bravo air pickup to any secured safe site in the ao situation north channels is deteriorating fast. allied rebels report bodarks and sentinel jointly seizing power infrastructure and ancient coastal stations while executing anyone resisting them. harrier intends to use those sites as resupply hubs and safe havens for stranded outcasts, but they cannot survive the current enemy presence without falcon clearing the objectives first. execution alpha is a 3-man ground element. bravo is the pilot and airborne fire support. keep harrier updated, clear all tos, then call bravo for extraction. insert depart leviathan bivouac, fly to the maritime ip, and drop alpha for the ground push. clear bravo remains overhead while alpha secures each coastal objective in sequence. turnover once each site is safe, inform harrier so they can move in and establish presence. no isr / no minis cyclops is off-station and enemy rc/gps jammers are active at all locations, so do not plan around miniature recon drones or live isr. helicopter employment recommended loadout is door gunners on both sides, anti-vehicle capability for the pilot, and lmg ground support for alpha. targets of opportunity all tos in the ao are greenlit if they improve outcast control. maintain pid and watch for friendly rebels needing assistance. objective alpha ancient village secure the village and prepare it for harrier occupation and sustainment use. objective bravo oceanic power plant clear hostile forces from the plant and deny enemy use of critical power infrastructure. objective charlie ancient harbor secure the harbor and remove enemy control over the coastal station network. objective delta blue cove station clear the final station, confirm all tos are secured, and coordinate bravo pickup.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-oxide%20%5B1150112464147599360%5D.html', label: 'op-oxide', searchLabel: 'op oxide', text: 'operation oxide operation oxide launch from fob bandit at 1900, land on the designated lz, hit the communications sites holding civilians, capture hvt limo if present, and hand network control back to golden eagle through on-site control-room access. briefing location fob bandit / south cape station step-off 1900 hours / designated lz insertion primary target hvt limo, enemy commander observed at bravo network task access control rooms and link with golden eagle situation enemy forces are coercing civilians across multiple comms locations and using the network infrastructure to sustain control. earlier recon placed commander limo at bravo, but the target may have displaced to another node. this is a large-scale civilian rescue mission. target id discipline is mandatory before every engagement. execution clear each site, protect civilians, seize control-room access, and report link status to golden eagle once the network is secured. immediate action rapidly neutralize hostile forces actively controlling or threatening civilians. secondary action capture hvt limo if found and restore friendly network control from the local control rooms. comms link authenticate with golden eagle and confirm the data stream is operational before moving on. civilian density each objective reports 6-14+ civilians on site. expect crowded interiors and crossfire risk around control buildings and walkways. threat pattern automated turrets, mortars, rooftop or catwalk snipers, and heavy gunners are confirmed at several locations. generators are present at alpha, bravo, and echo. radio drill use the scripted oxide to golden eagle authentication exchange once a control-room terminal is secured and the link is ready. objective alpha alpha control site 18+ hostiles, two elevated snipers, mortar, turret, heavy gunners, lower generator, and 12+ civilians on site. objective bravo bravo control site 6 hostiles, hvt limo observed center-left, one internal heavy gunner, center-right generator, pad turret, and 6+ civilians. objective charlie charlie control site 12+ hostiles, one sniper on the top catwalk, no automated defenses, no generator, and 13+ civilians. objective delta delta comms compound 18+ hostiles, three snipers, one rocket gunner, rooftop mortar, turret near comms building, no generator, and 14+ civilians. objective echo echo control site 20+ hostiles, three catwalk snipers, mortar, heavy gunner, center generator, and 12+ civilians. golden eagle link control-room authentication challenge code: sierra-charlie-niner-3-alpha. report network status and confirm the data stream after link establishment.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-panko%20%5B1146442427226402918%5D.html', label: 'op-panko', searchLabel: 'op panko', text: 'operation panko operation panko silent mountain raid to recover three captured tango-7 outcasts, interrogate qrf elements at submarine cable control and mathilda\'s palace, then hit auroa intranet control and neutralize kodiak before the target vanishes again. ao silent mountain primary target kodiak / auroa intranet control priority task find the tango-7 captives and prevent enemy qrf radio alerts exfil rtb after charlie is secure and exploited situation network lima-zero, the qrf distress channel for allied locals, was flooded by an enemy cyber operative. four civilians died before they could reach the team, and three tango-7 outcasts were captured inside sinking country. opsec traced the attack to target kodiak, last assessed as a bald caucasian male with a russian-linked alias profile and active presence around auroa intranet control. execution work alpha and bravo first to interrogate enemy qrf personnel and recover leads on tango-7, then strike charlie once kodiak is fixed on site. alpha / bravo secure both qrf sites fast enough to stop a radio warning from reaching kodiak. site exploitation exploit every captured node and interrogate all useful personnel for the captives\' location. charlie gain pid on kodiak, neutralize the target, clear aic, and rtb. cyber trigger expect enemy operators to spook if alpha or bravo gets a radio alert out. keep the hit synchronized and deny comms early. hvt profile kodiak\'s electronic signature is confirmed. visual reference is limited to one civilian-uploaded photograph taken under duress. recovery priority any interrogations or recovered files that indicate where tango-7 is held take priority over routine exploitation. objective alpha submarine cable control interrogate enemy personnel on tango-7\'s whereabouts, clear the site, and exploit all systems and documents. objective bravo mathilda\'s palace secure the qrf position, question survivors, and collect any intelligence pointing to the outcast prisoners. objective charlie auroa intranet control confirm kodiak\'s identity, neutralize the target, clear the facility, and complete full site exploitation. target reference civilian photo upload single image from a captured civilian suggests a near-bald caucasian male. use only as supporting id, not sole pid.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-paramount%20%5B1132742972803399831%5D.html', label: 'op-paramount', searchLabel: 'op paramount', text: 'operation paramount operation paramount deploy from erewhon at sundown, push from the ip near howard port through howard port, camp tiger, and bunker edgehod north, confirm the sedna slbm package, seize submarine control, call medusa for recovery, and rtb. launch site erewhon hq at sundown to the ip near howard port. primary threat three unmanned sedna submarines, likely modified typhoon-class boats. ew constraint wideband tactical jammers block rc/gps and drones until disabled. recovery team medusa combat divers recover the submarines after site control is established. situation sentinel is staging slbms for the sedna submarine program. the boats were previously observed in the bering sea and are now east of coal islands. intelligence points to bunker edgehod north as the likely warhead site, but jammers across the island chain are denying isr confirmation. execution follow the evidence chain and dismantle the launch package. exploit howard port for transit proof, eavesdrop on the camp tiger bunker meeting before clearing the island, then secure bunker edgehod north, verify slbms, and use the control module to turn the submarines over to medusa. alpha lead shipping manifests or interrogation. howard port should provide proof that the sensitive shipment was pushed to bunker edgehod north. bravo lead emergency bunker meeting. camp tiger personnel are expected to discuss targeting fort bragg, the white house, and the pentagon, and confirm missile storage at edgehod north. ao hazards sam sites and murmur patrols active. all targets of opportunity are greenlit only if they do not compromise the primary trail or submarine handoff. objective alpha howard port locate transit intelligence confirming the slbm shipment moved through the port. objective bravo camp tiger eavesdrop on the underground meeting undetected, confirm intent, then retake the island. objective charlie bunker edgehod north confirm the slbm package, secure the site, assume submarine control, radio medusa, and exfil.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-pheonix-dawn%20%5B1164985375966642286%5D.html', label: 'op-pheonix-dawn', searchLabel: 'op pheonix dawn', text: 'operation phoenix dawn operation phoenix dawn haho into the abandoned site southwest of alpha under darkness, move on foot through the rail corridor, collect origin and comms intelligence, clear the freight yard, and demolish the javelin/nv container before it departs maunga nui port at 0500. insertion night haho to the abandoned site southwest of alpha. deadline container is assessed to ship out at 0500. do not miss the window. callsigns team phantom. toc castle. roe engage hostile targets, avoid civilian harm, and positively id shots. situation sentinel is pushing a javelin and nv shipment to al-hayat. isr confirmed twenty-three javelin missiles and night-vision optics in a train cargo container destined for darb khandaq. the container is staged at maunga nui port, and sentinel appears to be enabling the illicit transfer through covert ties to al-hayat. execution confirm origin, tap enemy comms, and hit the port package. the ground approach is flexible because the situation is fluid and enemy movement is heavy across central smuggler coves. the requirement is to confirm the shipment trail, exploit enemy networks, and destroy the container under controlled demolition. container trail recover manifests at alpha. digital manifests at auroa materials deposit should confirm the container\'s origin and expose additional enemy shipping activity. network access patch into the enemy net at bravo. the comint device planted at checkpoint tiger bravo should open radio traffic for live exploitation. hvt option capture the port commander alive if present. sweep the maunga nui port comms building for intelligence and detain the site commander for interrogation if available. objective alpha auroa materials deposit infiltrate the depot and recover the digital manifests tied to the container shipment. objective bravo checkpoint tiger bravo plant the comint device on the enemy net and start harvesting transmissions. objective charlie smugglers cove freight yard halt yard operations and search for intelligence on additional illicit shipments. objective delta maunga nui port secure the port, exploit the comms building, demolish the target container, and exfil to hq.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-red-queen%20%5B1147101840673079318%5D.html', label: 'op-red-queen', searchLabel: 'op red queen', text: 'operation red queen operation red queen halo from the blackhawk at sundown, move in light black kits, restore viper 04 comms, clear checkpoint viper golf, raid skell foundation head office, recover the aircraft at auroa airport, then deliver it to outcast allies at plz watcher. insertion blackhawk launch from hq, halo to the lz at sundown. loadout light black kits for minimal footprint in the ao. recon no aerial isr link. mini drones are dcs-prepped and safe to use. end state fly plane and helicopter in formation to plz watcher, then exfil to hideout neptune. situation critical infrastructure is under seizure across northeast infinity. enemy forces are taking over the comms network, blocking a key supply route, arresting skell technology civilians, and occupying auroa airport after receiving a plane with valuable equipment. execution patrol, recon alpha and bravo, then flow through the full objective chain. land undetected, conduct ground reconnaissance on the first two targets, clear each site in sequence, recover the plane at delta, and transfer it to outcast personnel at plz watcher with a two-and-two formation split across aircraft and helicopter. top priority restore comms and civilian security. viper 04 must be reconnected to local teams, and civilians at skell foundation head office must be protected during the raid. route interdiction checkpoint viper golf must reopen. clear the roadblock and intercept any enemy vehicles encountered on the msr. targets of opportunity authorized if mission tempo holds. additional objectives can be hit as long as they do not compromise the four primary tasks or the aircraft delivery. objective alpha control station viper 04 secure the site and reestablish the local communications link. objective bravo checkpoint viper golf clear the checkpoint, reopen the supply corridor, and intercept enemy traffic. objective charlie skell foundation head office exploit the office for intelligence and neutralize hostile forces threatening civilians. objective delta auroa airport secure the airfield, recover the plane, and depart toward plz watcher.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-renewed-hope%20%5B1132738687139057804%5D.html', label: 'op-renewed-hope', searchLabel: 'op renewed hope', text: 'operation renewed hope operation renewed hope deploy from erewhon, land northwest of anti-aircraft ruins, rescue julius reilley, then roll through sentinel corp land base, the ammunition depot, and the equipment depot while standby teams move in to hold each cleared site. launch site erewhon hq to lz northwest of anti-aircraft ruins. primary rescue julius reilley, ost-6 marksman, held at anti-aircraft ruins. depot priority capture land base, ammunition depot, and equipment depot intact. air threat active sam coverage across sinking country. use caution on movement and lz timing. situation prisoner rescue and logistics recovery. reilley was captured after heavy border fighting and is being held at the ruins. at the same time, ongoing battles have depleted friendly ammunition and kit stocks, and cyclops has identified multiple sentinel depots that can stabilize the line if seized quickly. execution clear each objective and call in the holding force. insert at the northwest lz, rescue reilley, then move through each target site in sequence. once a location is cleared, radio the standby teams forward so they can secure the perimeter while the assault element continues to the next objective. target of opportunity additional captures are greenlit. any reachable sentinel target can be hit if it does not compromise the core rescue/depot sequence. possible detainees check every site. isr indicates detention cells may exist at all objectives, so sweep for imprisoned allies during each clearance. comms rhythm report site handoff cleanly. clearance calls should confirm all hostiles neutralized and authorize the standby element to advance and hold. objective alpha 1 anti-aircraft ruins rescue julius reilley and secure the site as a secondary ammunition depot. objective bravo 2 sentinel corp land base capture the base and convert it into the outcast hq for this sector. objective charlie 3 ammunition depot clear the storage site and secure the stockpile for friendly resupply. objective delta 4 equipment depot capture the final depot, finish the sweep for detainees, then rtb.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-riptide%20%5B1148950384178647130%5D.html', label: 'op-riptide', searchLabel: 'op riptide', text: 'operation riptide operation riptide helocast west of the main pumping station as a combat diver team, secure the pumping station and auroa power plant before a scorched-earth sabotage, raid step up startup, protect civilians receiving care, recover research, and return to fob bandit. launch site fob bandit / south cape station or nearby friendly site insertion night helocast west of main pumping station team type combat diver team recon constraint mini drones blocked by short-range rcgps jammers situation hostile forces seized the main pumping station and auroa power plant in southwest channels and may sabotage the power grid as part of a scorched-earth withdrawal. step up startup is also compromised, sensitive research is exposed, and civilians receiving medical care are on site. all three sites must be secured before irreversible damage occurs. execution insert by helocast, use ground reconnaissance and cyclops isr in place of jammed mini drones, disable any local jammers if found, then clear alpha, bravo, and charlie in sequence and rtb. alpha secure main pumping station, neutralize enemy forces, and preserve the water-supply infrastructure. bravo clear auroa power plant and prevent grid sabotage. charlie raid step up startup, recover research, protect civilians, and return to base. jammer effect expect short-range rcgps tactical jammers to disable team mini drones. fall back to visual recce unless the jammers can be found and shut down. enemy count source isr estimates roughly 14 hostiles at alpha, 18 at bravo, and 12 at charlie. civilian constraint step up startup has civilians receiving medical care on site. clear cleanly enough to prevent friendly or civilian losses. objective alpha main pumping station secure the station and keep the water infrastructure intact. objective bravo auroa power plant eliminate hostiles and safeguard the power grid from sabotage. objective charlie step up startup recover sensitive research and neutralize threats to civilians receiving care.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-rustle%20%5B1132400228893470781%5D.html', label: 'op-rustle', searchLabel: 'op rustle', text: 'operation rustle operation rustle haho from erewhon onto skell technology head office roof, clear down through the building, capture the murmur transport specialist alive in the parking lot, destroy the shipment, move him to dt-09 for troy pickup, then exploit the auroa hospital and detention center follow-on. launch site erewhon / after sundown insertion helicopter haho to skell technology head office roof recovery team troy for hvt pickup at dt-09 / dt-13 recon constraint no recon drones available, use eyes and binoculars situation cyclops tracked a special-unit transport specialist moving murmur drone shipments from island factories to wolves camps and finally to a secret meeting at skell technology head office. cyclops had to relocate after only two isr captures due to increased radar activity, but the window is good enough to capture the transport specialist alive and exploit his unit\'s logistics network. execution attack from the roof, clear down fast, interrogate the transport specialist in the lot, destroy the staged murmur shipment, then use his phone lead to raid auroa hospital, capture the lieutenant, and free prisoners at detention center. head office capture the transport specialist alive and destroy the skell technology crate staging murmur drones. hospital haho to the roof, keep the helicopter, secure civilians, and capture the visiting lieutenant alive. detention center roof infil again, clear the site, free the prisoners, and rtb after troy handles the detainees. hvt behavior the transport specialist may refuse to talk, but his phone should reveal the lieutenant is visiting wounded personnel at auroa hospital. lieutenant intel interrogate the hospital hvt for the civilian transfer pipeline to detention center and onward to scandium mine on golem island. story link the golem island continuation is operation whisper after this rescue chain is complete. objective alpha skell technology head office clear from roof to lot, capture the transport specialist alive, and interrogate him. objective bravo murmur shipment / dt-09 destroy the staged crate, move the hvt to dt-09, and call troy for pickup. objective charlie auroa hospital secure civilians, capture the lieutenant alive, and transfer him to a nearby dt site for troy. objective delta detention center roof infil, neutralize the unit, free the prisoners, and end the operation.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-silent-horizon%20%5B1133006954701262968%5D.html', label: 'op-silent-horizon', searchLabel: 'op silent horizon', text: 'operation silent horizon operation silent horizon qrf from south cape station to southern seal islands, insert covertly northeast of sentinel corp naval base via the lake ip, rescue the allied poc before execution, capture the auroa airfield helicopter pilot alive, and return both team and hvt to south cape station. launch site south cape station fob insertion covert helicopter drop northeast of sentinel corp naval base / lake ip rescue target allied poc held at sentinel corp naval base capture target enemy helicopter pilot at naval base auroa airfield situation humint confirms an allied point of contact is being held at sentinel corp naval base and faces imminent execution. at the same time, sigint confirms an enemy helicopter pilot with high-value personnel intelligence just arrived at naval base auroa airfield. the mission is to free the captive poc, capture the pilot alive, and extract him to south cape station for interrogation. execution insert northeast of the naval base, penetrate quietly to the prisoner location, secure a foothold, rescue the poc, then move to auroa airfield and assault the pilot\'s position with surprise and control. alpha clear the prisoner\'s vicinity, liberate the allied poc, and exploit the site for actionable intel. bravo infiltrate auroa airfield, locate the pilot, neutralize protection, and capture him alive. charlie extract the team and hvt to south cape station for handoff. speed requirement the poc is under imminent execution threat. prioritize a clean rapid breach at alpha before broader site exploitation. pilot pid the hvt can be treated as a bagman or another special enemy type at auroa airfield, but he must be captured alive. intel value the pilot is believed to hold critical information on high-ranking sentinel personnel and should be protected through exfil. objective alpha sentinel corp naval base insert covertly, eliminate immediate threats, free the allied poc, and exploit the holding site. objective bravo naval base auroa airfield pinpoint the pilot, suppress guards as needed, secure him alive, and recover any nearby intel. objective charlie south cape station return the team and captured pilot to fob for interrogation handoff.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-silent-shore%20%5B1150792346749915146%5D.html', label: 'op-silent-shore', searchLabel: 'op silent shore', text: 'operation silent shore operation silent shore launch from round top bivouac under night cover, exploit sutherland vineyard, secure a watercraft, sweep all six egg island drone hotspots, dismantle project hunter, then clear neptune to hold the perimeter while the team exits and rtbs. briefing site round top bivouac / southeast new stirling parameters classic world / drones active kit nvgs, thermal optics, heavy firepower hold force fireteam neptune situation files decrypted after capturing outpost red fox expose project hunter, a sentinel/wolves program testing modified skell lethal drones on egg island under a central european ai specialist. sutherland vineyard is being used as the logistics hub, cyclops reports a platoon-sized enemy presence offshore, and six drone patrol hotspots are mapped on the island. helicopter insertion is blocked by drone anti-air capability, so watercraft is required. execution search sutherland vineyard for project hunter intel, patrol the coastline to acquire a boat, cross to egg island, clear all six hotspots, recover drone chips/documents, then call neptune once the island is under control. alpha / bravo exploit sutherland vineyard, then patrol both marked docks to source watercraft for the island crossing. charlie systematically clear all six egg island hotspots and recover actionable drone intelligence. delta contact neptune for perimeter handoff, call extract, and rtb. threat density expect a dispersed platoon-sized force and active lethal drones across egg island. maintain thermal/nvg discipline and carry enough firepower for sustained contact. intel priorities collect drone chips, documents, and any references to the ai specialist or project hunter deployment to liberty. insertion constraint do not approach egg island by helicopter. acquire surface transport at the coastline docks marked on the sutherland map. objective alpha sutherland vineyard search the logistics hub and recover any project hunter intelligence. objective bravo coastline watercraft patrol the shoreline and secure a boat from one of the marked docks. objective charlie egg island hotspots clear all six drone test zones, destroy hostile squads, and recover chips and documents. objective delta neptune handoff radio neptune to hold the island perimeter, then call extract and return to base.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-silver-dawn%20%5B1146934558797865124%5D.html', label: 'op-silver-dawn', searchLabel: 'op silver dawn', text: 'operation silver dawn operation silver dawn fireteam shredder will halo east of shark bank station, kill victor reynolds and his squad, demolish control station tiger 01, neutralize the cliffside behemoth and relay, then seize the wild coast freight yard shipment and hand exploitation to bandit. launch site erewhon hq / 2200 / green kit fireteam shredder tools demolition charges and emp devices insertion halo to lz east of shark bank station situation victor reynolds, a former auroa navy officer tied to maritime weapons smuggling, has been located at shark bank station during a command-network meeting. his elimination and squad wipe are priority one. control station tiger 01 supports enemy uav operations, a behemoth on the western cliff is blocking friendly maritime movement, and a critical shipment is staged at wild coast freight yard with civilians on site. execution halo to the east-side lz, move on foot or use ao transport, hit alpha through delta in sequence, provide victor reynolds photo id to toc, and return to base after bandit takes over freight yard exploitation. alpha / bravo kill reynolds at shark bank station, then secure and demolish control station tiger 01. charlie disable the behemoth with emp and explosives, and destroy its network relay. delta secure the wild coast shipment, protect civilians, call bandit, and rtb. hvt proof after eliminating reynolds, send photo id to toc over comms net for confirmation. behemoth kill the western-cliff behemoth should be neutralized with emp devices and explosives before the relay is destroyed. bandit handoff once the freight yard is recaptured, contact bandit so they can exploit the site and search additional containers for supplies. objective alpha shark bank station eliminate victor reynolds and his squad, then transmit photo id to toc. objective bravo control station tiger 01 secure the station and execute controlled demolition to degrade enemy uav isr. objective charlie western cliff behemoth destroy the behemoth and the network relay obstructing friendly maritime traffic. objective delta wild coast freight yard secure the shipment, protect civilians, and hand the site to bandit for exploitation.' },
  { href: 'op-silver-scythe.html', label: 'op-silver-scythe', searchLabel: 'op silver scythe', text: 'operation silver scythe operation silver scythe sitrep during operation silver scythe, our unit is tasked with a critical two-part mission: 1. conduct a rescue of bandit 3, a friendly indigenous recon element captured near the anti-aircraft ruins after their position was overrun. 2. assault and neutralize an enemy black site and its reinforcement logistics hub. at 1834 hours, during ingress, our mh-6 little bird came under fire from an enemy sam battery. a catastrophic failure in the onboard countermeasures prevented flare deployment. as a last resort, the team was forced to bail out over hostile terrain, equipped only with their parachute, kit, and sidearm. we are now deep behind enemy lines, cut off from command and outnumbered. the mission has not changed: rescue friendly forces and destroy enemy assets. failure to act will cost allied forces countless lives and further strengthen enemy positions along the contested fb/sc border region. mission phases twin islands bivouac start at twin islands bivouac (roleplayed as the crash site where we just regrouped, everyone is alive but had their bell rung. no major injuries. set the time to something around 1900 hours.) resupply and scavenge sweep the southern island for supplies, weaponry, and usable items. locate a boat and cross mainland to assault anti-aircraft ruins. rescue bandit 3 assault the anti-aircraft ruins and liberate captured friendly personnel. conduct site exploitation. infiltrate airship air station investigate and infiltrate the airship air station (enemy black site). gather intelligence, demolish munitions crates in the building (roleplay finding 2 blocks of c4). seize shipping center seize the shipping center to cut off enemy reinforcements to the eastern border. sanitize site. return to base return to erewhon hq for debrief and r&r once all mission objectives are complete. mission survival rules 1. starting conditions begin with only a suppressed pistol. act as you would in a real combat survival scenario. no backpack and no item-wheel items - reason: the team bailed out during an aircraft emergency and lost most gear. 2. enemy weapon use any weapon taken from enemy forces must have all attachments removed. iron sights only, and no suppressors on rifles. reason: the enemy is a low-tech local militia with only basic gear (no optics, no grenades, no suppressors, etc.). 3. vehicles no helicopters. ground vehicles and watercraft are allowed. reason: airspace is heavily defended — anything airborne gets shot down immediately. example run 1. start at the bivouac with pistols only. 2. move to the south island, ambush a two-man patrol, and recover two basic rifles (stripped bare). take their boat and travel to the aa ruins. 3. at the ruins, fight using only basic rifles and free the pows. on the base you recover binoculars and a map. from this point, you may use the tac map and binoculars, but still no item-wheel gear due to the low-tech militia scenario. operational intent survive. adapt. complete the mission. use stealth, precision, and violence of action when required. improvise with whatever resources you can salvage. every encounter is a chance to rebuild capability, use it.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-skyfall%20%5B1143848105909952545%5D.html', label: 'op-skyfall', searchLabel: 'op skyfall', text: 'operation skyfall operation skyfall deploy from south cape station, fly high over sam coverage, halo southeast of arrow testing zone, neutralize azrael drones at alpha, bravo, and delta, stop the grandview mansion abduction cell, and hold their leader alive for oxide pickup. launch site south cape station parameters story mode / drone, azrael, helicopter: classic insertion halo to lz southeast of arrow testing zone custody handoff rt-7 oxide retrieves the captured leader at charlie situation azrael strikes across auroa escalated beyond control last night around 0200 when sentinel hit outcasts and non-combatants. or-4 estimates at least fifteen casualties while ground reconnaissance is still building the full picture. the mission is to neutralize all azraels and hostiles at three primary sites while also stopping the sentinel squad abducting civilians at grandview mansion. execution fly north from south cape station at elevated altitude to avoid confirmed sam coverage, halo to the lz, move through alpha and bravo, capture the charlie leader alive, then finish delta and exfil from the maintenance area. alpha / bravo clear arrow testing zone and assembly hall omega two and destroy all azrael drones. charlie eliminate the abduction squad at grandview mansion, interrogate their leader, then leave him secured for oxide. delta clear the maintenance area, neutralize remaining azraels, and exfil. air threat most drones are grounded, but potential azrael fly-bys remain possible overhead. stay ready to prosecute air threats fast. civilian rescue grandview mansion is tied to an active civilian-abduction cell. control the site quickly and preserve the leader for questioning. exfil delta is the final objective and extraction point once all objectives are complete and the charlie detainee is secured for rt-7. objective alpha arrow testing zone clear the testing zone and neutralize all azraels on site. objective bravo assembly hall omega two clear the hall and destroy all azraels in and around the facility. objective charlie grandview mansion eliminate the abduction team, keep the leader alive, interrogate him, and hold him for oxide. objective delta maintenance area clear remaining azraels and exfil from delta once the ao is stable.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-solaris%20%5B1132028178832031797%5D.html', label: 'op-solaris', searchLabel: 'op solaris', text: 'operation solaris operation solaris launch qrf from south cape station to auroa solar power plant, rescue clemens auer or interrogate sentinel for his transfer route, exploit the detention center prisoner logs, then recover him at abandoned barracks and confirm his safety to skell. launch site south cape station / qrf primary target clemens auer, skell level-one a.i. engineer initial ao auroa solar power plant / north liberty follow-on detention center and abandoned barracks if clemens is off-site situation clemens auer, previously missing since operation citadel, has contacted erewhon through a secure channel from auroa solar power plant while sentinel forces interrogate workers at gunpoint. skell cannot afford to lose him because he has complete knowledge of the drone infrastructure. reach the plant immediately, protect civilians, and recover clemens or track his movement. execution helo direct to the plant, choose a practical lz, clear sentinel, and interrogate one hostile if clemens is missing. if transferred, search detention center logs for d.i.d. 357 / cell 4b and follow his note to abandoned barracks. solar power plant liberate the site before civilian casualties and interrogate one sentinel for clemens\' location. detention center check the lobby computer and prisoner logs, then search cell 4b for the hidden note and coordinates. abandoned barracks retake the site, free clemens, radio skell for a security team, and exfil to south cape station. interrogation cue if clemens is not at the plant, the captured sentinel should reveal he was ordered to detention center processing for forced stolas mark 4 drone work. prisoner log search for clemens auer / cause of detention: obstructing sentinel operations / d.i.d. 357 / cell 4b. story continuation once clemens is safe and skell security is inbound, this thread can continue into operation crescendo. objective alpha auroa solar power plant helo in, secure the plant, prevent civilian casualties, and identify whether clemens is still on site. objective bravo detention center exploit prisoner logs and cell 4b to recover the seal islands coordinate lead. objective charlie abandoned barracks free clemens from the detention cells, confirm his safety to skell, and hold until support arrives. objective delta south cape station exfil after clemens is secure and the site handoff is complete.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-steel-dust%20%5B1148229681045327923%5D.html', label: 'op-steel-dust', searchLabel: 'op steel dust', text: 'operation steel dust operation steel dust step off from devil forest bivouac under darkness, sweep southeast ra01 from devil forest gold mine through omega r&d, azrael crash recovery, russel gold mine, burnet ridge, w161, and assembly hall omega 1, then exfil to south cape station. insertion point devil forest bivouac / night movement primary target mine commander and lethal ground-drone production chain movement foot-mobile with route adjustments from on-site intel exfil request pickup or use seized transport to south cape station situation command has located the enemy unit reactivating auroa\'s gold mines to support lethal ground-drone production. their commander and cell remain mobile, but their presence in southeast restricted area 01 is confirmed. the mission is to eliminate or capture the commander, destroy the drone production line, and exploit additional high-value targets across the ao. execution move from devil forest bivouac to the first objective on foot, exploit each site in sequence, adapt the route as fresh intel appears, and finish by exiting to south cape station. gold mines hit devil forest gold mine and russel gold mine to find the elusive commander and suppress the mining network. drone infrastructure secure omega r&d, capture w161, and destroy the assembly hall omega 1 assembly line. intel recovery exploit the azrael crash site and the burnet ridge weapons deal before exfil. commander pattern the mine commander does not stay in one location for long. treat devil forest and russel as priority capture/kill sites and update the route based on what each stop reveals. research seizure omega r&d should be taken intact enough to secure copies of all research material before any demolition or site denial actions. azrael exploit retrieve the black box and data storage at the crash site north of blackburn ridge to improve understanding of azrael drone operations. objective alpha devil forest gold mine locate and neutralize or capture the enemy commander running the mine network. objective bravo omega r&d center seize control and secure copies of all research materials tied to lethal drone production. objective charlie azrael crash site recover the black box and onboard storage north of blackburn ridge. objective delta russel gold mine reacquire the commander if he moved, then neutralize or capture him. objective echo burnet ridge weapon deal disrupt the deal and collect intel on the smuggling network. objective foxtrot drone station w161 capture the station and shut down regional lethal drone patrol control. objective golf assembly hall omega 1 capture the hall and destroy the lethal drone assembly line. objective hotel south cape station exfil by requested extraction or recovered vehicle movement to south cape station.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-stormbringer%20%5B1135195819524489236%5D.html', label: 'op-stormbringer', searchLabel: 'op stormbringer', text: 'operation stormbringer operation stormbringer razor will haho northwest of greenfield plain under darkness, silently neutralize the behemoth blocking maritime traffic, seize the camp kodiak gunship after killing the hvt, use cas to drive north through drone patrols, and recapture the driftwood islets testing zone. launch site erewhon / overseer insertion haho to lz northwest of greenfield plain fireteam razor required roles heavy gunner and demolition expert situation this is the final assault to secure driftwood islets, a key approach node near golem island. success will mark the liberation of darkwood island from sentinel occupation. the island chain is defended by behemoth coverage, the camp kodiak hvt and gunship, land and air drone patrols, and a heavily occupied testing zone with 20+ hostiles and lethal drones. execution insert silently to avoid the behemoth\'s acoustic ground sensors, destroy the drone at greenfield plain, raid camp kodiak for the hvt and gunship, then split between a fast ground element and cas element to clear north into the testing zone. alpha neutralize the behemoth at greenfield plain. bravo eliminate the camp kodiak hvt and secure the gunship. charlie / delta use cas and ground maneuver to clear north, recapture the driftwood islets testing zone, call in the security team, and rtb. approach discipline maintain a silent approach into alpha so the behemoth\'s acoustic sensors do not cue the site before the demolition strike lands. drone threat expect multiple air and ground drones throughout charlie and delta. cas from the captured gunship should pace the ground element\'s advance. hold phase once delta is secure, radio the security team to assume the perimeter and preserve the site while razor returns to base. objective alpha greenfield plain destroy the behemoth drone that is blocking maritime traffic and shielding the southern approach. objective bravo camp kodiak kill the hvt, seize the gunship, and prep it for cas tasking over the northbound push. objective charlie northbound clearance split into a quick ground element and cas element, then clear patrols and drone positions across the islets. objective delta testing zone recapture driftwood islets testing zone, establish control, and hold until the security team arrives.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-subterra%20%5B1132358171697086615%5D.html', label: 'op-subterra', searchLabel: 'op subterra', text: 'operation subterra operation subterra strike silent valley mine, confirm uranium with a portable near-infrared spectrometer, push into chem-extraction to verify and secure yellowcake, interrogate for the maunga nui port container number, then seize the shipment before exfil and gear decon at erewhon. launch site erewhon / sunset transport overseer helicopter detection tool portable near-infrared spectrometer final site maunga nui port shipment intercept situation scott davis, the turned sentinel commander captured at skell security r&d center, reports uranium deposits at silent valley mine and yellowcake production at the chem-extraction complex for black-market resale. a shipment is staged to leave through maunga nui port. even if the material is not weapons-grade, it is a step toward dirty-bomb supply chains and the entire pipeline must be shut down. execution clear silent valley mine, confirm uranium, call in a security team, then move to chem-extraction, mask up before entering, inspect barrels, and interrogate the high-ranking commander for shipping-container pid before the port intercept. mine sanitize silent valley mine and verify uranium presence with the spectrometer. complex / control center confirm yellowcake authenticity, then interrogate the commander on-site or at mining control center. port identify the container, seize the shipment at maunga nui port, and task the construction-site team to move it to safety. gas mask warning equip gas masks before entering chem-extraction. yellowcake is not the main radiological threat at this stage, but inhalation is hazardous. container pid recover a shipping manifest or container number through interrogation. if the commander is not at chem-extraction, push to mining control center. post-op move back to erewhon, debrief, and clean all gear after handling uranium-linked materials and site dust. objective alpha silent valley mine infiltrate, clear the site, and use the spectrometer to confirm uranium deposits before handing the area to support. objective bravo chem-extraction complex locate the barrels, verify yellowcake authenticity, and secure the production line. objective charlie commander interrogation extract the maunga nui port container identifier from the high-ranking commander at the complex or mining control center. objective delta maunga nui port capture the port, intercept the yellowcake container, secure the area, and initiate safe relocation.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-sustained-force%20%5B1132740123021287434%5D.html', label: 'op-sustained-force', searchLabel: 'op sustained force', text: 'operation sustained force operation sustained force haho southwest of dark wood, liberate dunback farm, forsyth farm, and burnside orchard, seize the food trucks sentinel has been diverting, convoy all supplies to nc-19, and coordinate the coral boat pickup before exfil to hq. launch site erewhon / sundown / green kit insertion helicopter to altitude, haho to lz southwest of dark wood convoy destination site nc-19 food-truck handoff poc callsign coral situation sentinel units have seized civilian farms north of new stirling and are diverting loaded food trucks to undisclosed locations. that theft is draining the regional resistance cache and weakening outcast sustainment. the mission is to retake all three farms, neutralize targets of opportunity, and move the recovered food trucks to nc-19 for outcast pickup. execution jump haho to the lz, move farm-to-farm in sequence, neutralize resistance, collect intel, secure each truck, then convoy the three vehicles to nc-19 and contact coral for the boat handoff. farm clears retake dunback farm, forsyth farm, and burnside orchard and secure each truck in turn. nc-19 delivery convoy all recovered supplies to november charlie one niner and prep the load for transport. coral linkup radio coral for pickup eta, hold security until outcasts arrive, then exfil or fast-travel rtb. too clearance handle targets of opportunity during each farm clear, but keep the priority on preserving the food trucks and preventing supply loss. radio script "coral, this is dagger one, sierra safely delivered to nc-19 at grid 256840. contents are being prepped for transport, advise eta, over." extraction once coral confirms the pickup and outcasts arrive, mission is complete. rtb to erewhon or call extract based on command preference. objective alpha dunback farm liberate the farm, neutralize sentinel resistance, collect intel, and secure the food truck. objective bravo forsyth farm repeat the clear-and-secure pattern and add the second truck to the convoy package. objective charlie burnside orchard clear the orchard, capture any useful intel, and recover the final truck before moving to nc-19. objective delta site nc-19 deliver all three food trucks, establish coral comms, and hold the drop-off site until boat pickup is complete.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-thunderbolt%20%5B1144985921603772567%5D.html', label: 'op-thunderbolt', searchLabel: 'op thunderbolt', text: 'operation thunderbolt operation thunderbolt haho from erewhon to pleasant island, capture the attack hvt alive, rescue chloe reynolds and all civilians, secure project omega research, then hit the outpost red fox follow-on target while keeping the hvt controlled for transport to hq. launch site erewhon hq / 2130 / black kit insertion helicopter to dz, haho to lz 500m southeast of target primary task extract hvt alive and keep civilians unharmed end state island secured, security team on site, hvt delivered to hq situation chloe reynolds sent a distress message from pleasant island in central restricted area 01. the site manages project omega, a lethal-drone research and production effort, and is currently under enemy assault. prevent project omega material from falling into hostile hands, preserve all civilians on site, and move fast. based on reynolds\' message, enemy strength is estimated at 12+ heavily armed hostiles and there is no live cyclops isr support. execution deploy by helicopter from erewhon, jump haho to the lz, push to pleasant island with haste, pid the hvt, secure the island, and radio the security team to hold the facility and assist civilians. island assault reach pleasant island, identify the hvt, and capture him alive for interrogation. site control clear the island, protect all civilians, and lock down project omega research material. red fox follow-on if intel is found, raid outpost red fox, eliminate the wolf lieutenant, and rtb with the captive hvt. team lead note pick any enemy on pleasant island as the hvt, define his appearance and location clearly to the team, and ensure he is taken alive. possible extension one enemy may carry intel that a high-ranking wolf lieutenant is holding a meeting at outpost red fox roughly 1 km southeast of the island. civilian priority reynolds\' photo confirms civilians are being searched by sentinel. move quickly and control fires to avoid civilian harm. objective alpha haho insertion helo to the dz, then haho into the lz southeast of pleasant island. objective bravo capture hvt alive reach the island, pid the on-site commander, and secure him for interrogation. objective charlie secure pleasant island clear all hostiles, protect the civilians, and call the security team to hold the area and assist survivors. objective delta hq delivery depart with the hvt and return him to hq for questioning after any red fox follow-on is complete.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-triad%20%5B1144981357517361192%5D.html', label: 'op-triad', searchLabel: 'op triad', text: 'operation triad operation triad deploy from whiteman shelf bivouac to muddy pond lz, patrol the driftwood islets beacon sites, recover three sealed skell briefcases before sentinel or wolves reach them, document the crash containers, and hand the cases back to skell at erewhon hq. launch site whiteman shelf bivouac / 2100 insertion muddy pond lz, then foot patrol across all beacon pings recovery teams griffin, hunter, scalar on standby for container lift return deliver all sealed briefcases to skell at erewhon hq situation radar station north now gives visibility over north-eastern auroa air traffic. at 20:15 a skell transport cargo aircraft was shot down by drone swarms over driftwood islets, after which three beacons began transmitting secure skell-net coordinates from the crash zone. jace skell confirms the signals are from three sealed briefcases carrying critical data. they are still transmitting their location, but sentinel and wolves may converge on the crash sites first if recovery lags. execution move from muddy pond lz to each beacon, secure the briefcase, document the scattered container contents, upload findings to hq, and call griffin, hunter, or scalar to recover supplies once each site is cleared. muddy pond land and begin the islet patrol toward all three beacon locations. crash sites recover the sealed briefcases, document the containers, and transmit all intel to hq. erewhon hq rtb with the cases and hand them directly to skell for exploitation. ao activity drones, azrael coverage, and helicopter patrols should remain active. cyclops has already reported patrol movement and multiple drone deployments across the islets. targets of opportunity neutralize too encountered along the patrol route as long as it does not compromise the briefcase recovery or delay the handoff chain. package pid the desired item is a sealed black secure briefcase matching the reference image. do not break seals in the field unless survival or transport security requires it. objective alpha muddy pond lz insert at muddy pond and organize the patrol toward all three transmitting case locations. objective bravo beacon recovery sites recover each sealed briefcase, confirm the crash containers, and call standby recovery teams after every site is secure. objective charlie driftwood islets security clear hostile patrols and drone-supported positions as needed to protect the route and prevent interference with package extraction. objective delta erewhon hq delivery return all recovered briefcases to erewhon and deliver them to skell intact.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-umbral%20%5B1134111975522177054%5D.html', label: 'op-umbral', searchLabel: 'op umbral', text: 'operation umbral operation umbral insert west of the underwater cable station by gyps helocast from erewhon, swim in under stealth, breach both alpha server rooms at the same time, hunt the bravo hvt, lock down the campus data farm, and reclaim skell foundation campus technology. launch site erewhon insertion gyps helocast west of underwater cable station primary method underwater stealth approach, speed, suppressed weapons end state campus secured, ai research recovered, rtb situation enemy activity in cape north has escalated around the underwater cable station, construction site, campus data farm, and skell foundation campus. the mission is to extract movement data, eliminate the hvt, deny enemy access to ai research, and recover campus technology. some civilians in the ao may have flipped and may be carrying concealed weapons. treat unknowns carefully, keep the approach covert, and be ready for armed interference inside ostensibly civilian spaces. execution deploy from erewhon by gyps, helocast west of alpha, swim in, and use synchronized breaches to pull data from both cable-station server rooms. roll bravo for the hvt, continue to charlie to secure the data farm, then clear delta and recover skell foundation ai material. alpha breach both underwater cable station server rooms simultaneously to authenticate and download movement data. bravo find and eliminate the hvt at the construction site, or catch him in transit toward charlie if the initial lead is stale. charlie / delta secure the campus data farm, then reclaim skell foundation campus and recover all research material before rtb. server breach the alpha server rooms must be breached at the same time or the authentication path fails. split the stack and coordinate timing before going loud inside the station. civilian risk reports indicate some local civilians may be compromised and armed. watch hands, screen for concealed weapons, and avoid assuming noncombatant behavior. loadout combat diver fit should stay in multicam black or full black for the underwater movement and suppressed close-in work through alpha. objective alpha underwater cable station enter through the cave access and pull data from both server rooms with synchronized breach timing. objective bravo construction site hvt locate and eliminate the target on site, or track him along the route toward charlie if he is already moving. objective charlie campus data farm secure the data farm and deny further enemy access. the server building is the demolition priority if hard reset is required. objective delta skell foundation campus clear the recently arrived enemy force, secure ai research material, and hold the campus long enough to complete recovery.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20op-wavelength%20%5B1131652257025372412%5D.html', label: 'op-wavelength', searchLabel: 'op wavelength', text: 'operation wavelength operation wavelength fireteam breaker will helocast off hunt beach, scuba to shore, switch into dry black ppe, seize three suspected radioactive components across red shark outpost, navy fuelling station, and cold war ruins, then move fast to hlz sparrow for watcher extraction. launch site south cape station / post-sundown insertion high-altitude flight to maritime ip, helocast, then scuba ashore protection lead plates, potassium iodide, handheld geiger counters extraction hlz sparrow situation intercepted traffic between sentinel and an unknown russian contact confirms three package deliveries to sentinel outposts in channels province. the working assessment is that the packages contain radioactive components for an underground weapons program. the mission is to recover all three components before sentinel can assemble radioactive payloads, keeping the operation covert and minimizing exposure time once packages are in hand. execution fly at max altitude to avoid sam and murmur-drone coverage, helocast near hunt beach, scuba to the coast, switch into dry black ppe, and move to alpha, bravo, and charlie on foot. use geiger counters to confirm package pid at each site, then push to hlz sparrow for extract. alpha clear to the red shark outpost comms building and seize the first component. bravo recover the second component from the navy fuelling station warehouse near the second dock. charlie grab the final package from the cold war ruins depot before the handoff occurs, then move to hlz sparrow. covert status this is a seizure mission. avoid compromises, keep eyes on the sky for murmur drones, and do not get pinned near sam coverage during insertion or exfil. isr quality cyclops was forced to rtb due to weather, so aerial imagery is weak. local camera taps provide likely package sites, but final confirmation must come from geiger checks. callsigns fireteam callsign is breaker. hq callsign is watcher. hostiles and other targets of opportunity are greenlit if the core package recovery remains uncompromised. objective alpha red shark outpost search the comms building and seize the first radioactive component package identified by partial camera intel. objective bravo navy fuelling station recover the second component from the warehouse near the second dock after geiger-confirmed pid. objective charlie cold war ruins secure the final package from the small depot before its scheduled change of hands. objective delta hlz sparrow move quickly to extract after all components are secured to limit radiation exposure while carrying the packages.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20%E2%9D%97-cbrn-op-extremis%20%5B1132740832064192603%5D.html', label: 'Ground Branch Task Force - OPORDS BREAKPOINT ALPHA - ❗-cbrn-op-extremis [1132740832064192603]', searchLabel: 'ground branch task force   opords breakpoint alpha   ❗ cbrn op extremis [1132740832064192603]', text: 'operation extremis operation extremis emergency cbrn push into whalers bay\'s gas-zone corridor to destroy every dr-code wb-38 amber ruin crate, dismantle aconite station, and capture the airfield commander before the buyer\'s cargo plane can export the agent. world state amber sky on for gas areas insertion erewhon to auctions glade bivouac, near 2000 defector anders christensen crate id dr-code wb-38 situation sentinel stabilized amber ruin ahead of schedule, used it on homesteaders, and is preparing to ship production off auroa. christensen defected after seeing the test reports and provided the operation details. intercepted comms indicate a cargo plane is authorized to land at whalers bay airfield in two days for a transaction that likely moves the agent to an external buyer. execution deploy a cbrn team from erewhon, verify suit integrity at the lz, move into the gas zone, investigate checkpoints for extra intelligence, and destroy all identified crates and lab capacity. checkpoint sweep secure weasel delta and weasel foxtrot while collecting any additional intelligence. crate destruction destroy wb-38 crates at storage depot and land chassis factory. endgame clear aconite station, capture the whalers bay airfield commander alive, and extract with gyps support if needed. no export amber ruin cannot leave the island under any circumstances. full destruction of the disguised skell-equipment crates is mandatory. recon status cyclops verified most of christensen\'s intelligence, but ground teams may still uncover more at checkpoints and stations. biological threat this cbrn package is focused on a biological amber ruin hazard, so suit checks at auctions glade are required before entering the zone. objective alpha checkpoint weasel delta secure the checkpoint and search for intelligence on the shipment network. objective bravo storage depot destroy all amber ruin crates camouflaged as civilian skell equipment. objective charlie land chassis factory secure the factory and eliminate every wb-38 marked crate on site. objective delta checkpoint weasel foxtrot secure the area and gather any additional intelligence before pushing deeper. objective echo drone station w061 capture the station, resupply, and destroy excess enemy weapons, ammo, and radio gear. objective foxtrot aconite station / whalers bay airfield destroy the authentication lab, collect intel, then capture the airfield commander alive for interrogation at hq.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20%E2%9D%97-cbrn-op-otrovna%20%5B1132748196385398866%5D.html', label: 'Ground Branch Task Force - OPORDS BREAKPOINT ALPHA - ❗-cbrn-op-otrovna [1132748196385398866]', searchLabel: 'ground branch task force   opords breakpoint alpha   ❗ cbrn op otrovna [1132748196385398866]', text: 'operation otrovna operation otrovna night haho cbrn infiltration into the amber ruin gas zone to interrogate perimeter leadership, wiretap enemy comms, breach the production facility, and destroy every azrael uav and poison stockpile at maintenance area. world state amber sky, drones, azrael, heli on team fireteam oracle / full cbrn kit insertion haho to ardmore ridge bivouac extract cbrn x-ray outside gas zone situation red dragon 2 reports an enemy platoon on the restricted area 01 border and workers at maintenance area fitting azrael drones with modified amber ruin payloads. if the uavs launch, resistance forces in new sterling and across auroa face a major chemical threat. a qrf is required immediately. execution insert at night in full cbrn gear, stay covert through ardmore farm and checkpoint fox charlie, and avoid any alert until maintenance area is reached. alpha quietly secure ardmore farm and interrogate the perimeter commander if possible. bravo / charlie secure fox charlie, plant the relay wiretap, then breach the barricaded amber ruin production facility. delta destroy all azrael uavs, amber ruin reserves, and local toos at maintenance area. stealth constraint an alert before reaching maintenance area could compromise the entire mission and allow payload relocation or launch prep. signals task install a wiretap on the checkpoint fox charlie relay for future interception of enemy communications. priority intel interrogate the enemy leader to learn how sentinel plans to weaponize amber ruin on uavs. objective alpha ardmore farm secure quietly, gather intelligence, and question the local commander if possible. objective bravo checkpoint fox charlie secure the checkpoint, collect intelligence, and plant a comms-relay wiretap. objective charlie amber ruin production facility breach and clear the barricaded production building inside the gas-zone perimeter. objective delta maintenance area set demo on all azrael drones, amber ruin reserves, and any nearby targets of opportunity.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20%F0%9F%8C%8B-golem-op-basalt%20%5B1132025512320045056%5D.html', label: 'Ground Branch Task Force - OPORDS BREAKPOINT ALPHA - 🌋-golem-op-basalt [1132025512320045056]', searchLabel: 'ground branch task force   opords breakpoint alpha   🌋 golem op basalt [1132025512320045056]', text: 'operation basalt operation basalt a sunset rhib run from wreck ship bivouac will hit ancient harbor from the south, recover the radio operator\'s skell tech rfid access module using less-than-lethal control where possible, then patch into the golem island satellite dish mainframe and pull project titan intelligence. start point wreck ship bivouac south of golem island insertion rhib movement 1.3 km northwest to ancient harbor access item rto-carried skell tech credentials module follow-on destroy heliport shipment if mainframe intel confirms it situation the team has reached golem island, the home of project titan, after slipping past legion drone swarms under dsi-camo and establishing a bivouac at a shipwreck south of the island at 2015 hours. command wants the force to determine what sentinel has been doing with titan infrastructure since the invasion. the immediate objective is to acquire network credentials from ancient harbor and use them to access the golem island satellite dish mainframe, which controls island communications and should contain actionable project titan intelligence. execution launch at sunset by rhib, approach ancient harbor from the south, and work north through the site to locate the radio operator. avoid hard gunfire until the access module is in hand because a stray round could destroy the credential device. alpha find the radio operator at ancient harbor and recover his network access module. bravo patch into the satellite dish mainframe and download all actionable intelligence. branch if the server confirms a fresh heliport shipment, move northeast, destroy it, then rest at the nearest bivouac. credential handling use less-than-lethal control until the rto module is secured. the rfid device is not bulletproof and can be ruined by stray fire. recon limits a strict no-fly zone and legion drone patrols prevent meaningful isr. use project titan tacmap archives, binoculars, and miniature drones as terrain and signal conditions allow. server lead mainframe intel should reveal a weapons and mre shipment delivered to golem island heliport one hour ago. destroy that shipment before it transfers east. objective alpha ancient harbor infiltrate from the south, locate the radio operator, and obtain the skell tech access module needed for the dish breach. objective bravo golem island satellite dish access the top-side mainframe, download project titan intelligence, and identify any immediate follow-on targets.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20%F0%9F%8C%8B-golem-op-obsidian%20%5B1151564847318847599%5D.html', label: 'Ground Branch Task Force - OPORDS BREAKPOINT ALPHA - 🌋-golem-op-obsidian [1151564847318847599]', searchLabel: 'ground branch task force   opords breakpoint alpha   🌋 golem op obsidian [1151564847318847599]', text: 'operation obsidian operation obsidian an off-books black-kit strike from sector 3 bivouac will demolish all eight project titan network nodes across red phoenix outpost and no man\'s land, exploit any local intelligence, and then pull a coastal watercraft for rtb under volcanic smog and jammer-constrained isr. step-off sector 3 bivouac / dusk, approx. 2000 profile off-record operation in black kits hazard active golem volcano smog and sulfur dioxide exposure exfil locate coastal watercraft and rtb situation project titan archive intelligence identifies eight critical network nodes spread across two remote locations on eastern golem island. destroying those nodes should knock down part of titan\'s infrastructure and materially slow the program. the amphibious infiltration of sector 3 is already complete, a preparation bivouac is in place, and the mission is to locate and demolish all nodes while collecting any actionable project titan intelligence found on site. execution at dusk, move from sector 3 bivouac in black kit with gas masks and nv/thermal optics, then place c4 on the alpha and bravo node clusters. golem volcano sulfur dioxide and reduced visibility are active mission factors, and miniature drones are unusable due to local rcgps jamming. alpha infiltrate red phoenix outpost and demolish the first four project titan network nodes. bravo advance to no man\'s land and neutralize the remaining four nodes with c4. exfil secure any extra intel or targets of opportunity, then move to the coast and rtb by watercraft. respiratory hazard golem volcano is active and sulfur dioxide levels in the smog are a genuine risk. gas masks are mandatory throughout the route. optics use nv and thermal optics to preserve visibility in volcanic haze and low light while moving through the node sites. isr constraint airspace is restricted and local rcgps jammers disable miniature drones, so rely on archived tacmap data and binoculars-only ground recon. objective alpha red phoenix outpost identify the first four project titan network nodes inside the outpost and destroy each one with c4. objective bravo no man\'s land pinpoint the remaining four nodes in the second cluster and demolish them to complete the infrastructure strike. ao map archived project titan tacmap reference for the red phoenix outpost and no man\'s land node clusters along eastern golem island.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20%F0%9F%8C%8B-golem-op-onyx%20%5B1132361892636131338%5D.html', label: 'Ground Branch Task Force - OPORDS BREAKPOINT ALPHA - 🌋-golem-op-onyx [1132361892636131338]', searchLabel: 'ground branch task force   opords breakpoint alpha   🌋 golem op onyx [1132361892636131338]', text: 'operation onyx operation onyx a black-kit ground patrol from sector 2 eastern bivouac will investigate project nebiros on golem island, unlock and copy data from the missile site ruins server, recover the manpads prototype from forgotten sanctuary, sweep the testing zone, and demolish ancient harbor\'s weapons depot. launch point sector 2 eastern bivouac near missile site ruins step-off sundown / black kits mobility foot movement with osp transport only core tasking project nebiros intelligence and manpads prototype recovery situation documents recovered from outpost green viper partially decrypted into a project nebiros lead: a wolves unit on golem island appears to be testing next-generation weapons there. the intel picture is incomplete, but it is sufficient to justify an urgent ground investigation. the mission is to collect more nebiros data, recover a unique manpads prototype from forgotten sanctuary, and cripple any active weapons infrastructure found during the sweep. execution depart from sector 2 eastern bivouac near missile site ruins at sundown, stay in black kit, and move on foot unless transport can be procured on site. tactical jammers deny drone support, so all recon must be done by eyes and binoculars unless a jammer source is located and disabled. alpha reboot four security nodes at missile site ruins, breach the underground server, copy all data, then demo the server. bravo / charlie recover the manpads prototype at forgotten sanctuary and investigate the golem island testing zone for targets of opportunity. delta seed demolition across ancient harbor\'s ammunition and weapons caches, exfil, detonate, and rtb by watercraft. jammer constraint tactical jammers and drone-swarm patrols block isr and outbound signals, so expect binoculars-only reconnaissance and no friendly drone tasking. server security do not get spotted before all four missile site ruins nodes are rebooted. if alerted early, the enemy may wipe the underground server before the download completes. prototype handling the manpads should be stored in a secure weapon container at forgotten sanctuary and may require captured credentials before it can be opened and dismantled for transport. objective 1 missile site ruins reboot the four lockout nodes, breach the underground server, copy all nebiros data, and destroy the server after extraction. objective 2 forgotten sanctuary locate the manpads prototype container, obtain access if needed, dismantle the launcher, and transport it for specialist analysis. objective 3 golem island testing zone investigate the weapons test area and neutralize any valuable targets of opportunity found on site. objective 4 ancient harbor infiltrate the depot, plant demolition on all ammunition and weapon caches, exfil, and detonate the site.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20%F0%9F%8C%8B-golem-op-pyroclasm%20%5B1150761867103436890%5D.html', label: 'Ground Branch Task Force - OPORDS BREAKPOINT ALPHA - 🌋-golem-op-pyroclasm [1150761867103436890]', searchLabel: 'ground branch task force   opords breakpoint alpha   🌋 golem op pyroclasm [1150761867103436890]', text: 'operation pyroclasm operation pyroclasm a black-kit sabotage run from the sector 1 ip will cut the chemical feedstock behind golem island\'s lethal-drone program, disable the refinery and pipeline chain, and then hit the prototype workshop that shipped thermal-imaging drones into north auroa. launch point sector 1 ip / sundown loadout black kits primary threat thermal-imaging lethal drones tied to prototype workshop exit rtb to hq for debrief after charlie situation unprecedented thermal-imaging lethal drones have appeared in north auroa and have already caused multiple homesteader casualties around cape north. tracking a shipment out of camp kodiak led to a prototype workshop on golem island that appears to be the source of those systems. the workshop is supplied by a nearby chemical refinery through a pipeline network. the mission is to sabotage all three nodes, exploit any secondary opportunities on site, and keep allied positions safe. execution step off from the sector 1 insertion point at sundown in black kit and focus on deliberate sabotage of alpha, bravo, and charlie. isr is degraded by heavy drone swarms and sam coverage, so identify and exploit any additional hvts, servers, drones, or shipping manifests encountered during the route. alpha disable the chemical refinery and clear any secondary targets on site. bravo cut the chemical pipeline connecting the refinery to the workshop. charlie neutralize the prototype workshop producing the drones, then rtb. isr limits heavy drone swarms and sam sites are constraining overhead reconnaissance, so expect incomplete picture and validate the route from the ground. exploit targets during all three hits, check for servers, shipping manifests, drones, and hvts that can help confirm how the workshop is sourcing and moving its product. supply logic alpha is the chemical source, bravo is the transfer link, and charlie is the production node. destroying all three should shut down the current golem island drone line. objective alpha chemical refinery disable the refinery supplying chemical compounds to the workshop and address any secondary targets found on site. objective bravo chemical pipeline sabotage the pipeline that links the refinery to the prototype workshop and interrupts compound delivery. objective charlie prototype workshop destroy or disable the workshop producing the thermal-imaging lethal drones operating in north auroa. ao map golem island route reference covering the chemical refinery, chemical pipeline, and prototype workshop sabotage sequence.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20ALPHA%20-%20%F0%9F%8C%8B-golem-op-whisper%20%5B1132404239709257818%5D.html', label: 'Ground Branch Task Force - OPORDS BREAKPOINT ALPHA - 🌋-golem-op-whisper [1132404239709257818]', searchLabel: 'ground branch task force   opords breakpoint alpha   🌋 golem op whisper [1132404239709257818]', text: 'operation whisper operation whisper part two of operation rustle pushes onto golem island from sector 2 western bivouac, cuts all external comms at the island satellite dish, investigates the heliport and both transit camps tied to civilian transfers, and closes on scandium mine to liberate the work camp. launch point sector 2 western bivouac / 1900 priority action sabotage golem island satellite dish to isolate the island movement ground-only patrols across golem island source trail follow-up to op rustle detention-center intel situation during operation rustle, the team learned a special sentinel unit was rounding up civilians in liberty and sending them to the scandium mine work camp on golem island. the detention-center rescue prevented one transport cycle, but the island pipeline still needs to be dismantled. the mission is to reach golem island, sever outside communications, trace the three main transport nodes, and then move on scandium mine to liberate the camp. execution step off from sector 2 western bivouac near 1900, move first to the golem island satellite dish, and place demolition on the top-side main module to cut the island\'s external link. after that, clear the heliport, camp phoenix, camp salamander, and finally scandium mine. dish sabotage the satellite module and isolate golem island. transit chain clear the heliport, camp phoenix, and camp salamander while gathering proof of prisoner transfer routes. mine clean scandium mine and attempt to liberate the work-camp civilians, then rtb. drone saturation heavy drone swarms prevented a cyclops recon flight and rule out aircraft use on the island. treat ground-team tacmap imagery as the primary navigation reference. camp salamander access the checkpoint comms-building computer is biometrically locked. use an enemy to unlock it, pull the logs, then demo the main gate to sever the msr into sector 03. team lead end-state if no surviving workers are found at scandium mine, call the site and rtb. prior ground intel indicates the camp population may already have been killed. objective 1 golem island satellite dish set demolition on the top-side main module to cut all outside comms and isolate the island. objective 2 golem island heliport eliminate the receiving squads and disable warehouses, comms, automated defenses, and other key heliport systems. objective 3 camp phoenix kill the elite processing team, destroy strategic infrastructure, and recover any local intel on prisoner staging. objective 4 camp salamander unlock and extract transit logs from the comms computer, then demo the main gate to cut the sector 03 msr. objective 5 scandium mine clear the work-camp area and attempt to liberate the civilians held there before returning to base. ao map golem island route reference covering the satellite dish isolation point, heliport, camp phoenix, camp salamander, and scandium mine.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-boomslang%20%5B1241501070493225084%5D.html', label: 'op-boomslang', searchLabel: 'op boomslang', text: 'operation boomslang operation boomslang a 2015 halo package will recover both halves of viper-3 from outpost blue tiger and electric engine factory, destroy the lethal-drone shipment at the factory, then covertly capture hvt sultan at mechanical r&d center and move him to safehouse valkyrie-6 for extract to hq interrogation. step-off erewhon hq / 2015 hours insertion halo to lz, then foot movement through alpha and bravo vehicle move use on-site transport from bravo to charlie under low profile detainee handoff deliver sultan to safehouse valkyrie-6, then hq situation viper-3, an allied special reconnaissance team, has been split between outpost blue tiger and the electric engine factory after a wolves convoy carrying the prisoners was spotted by reaper drone over wild coast. recovering both groups is the first priority, and clearing those locations will also reduce enemy pressure on friendly border forces. the electric engine factory contains a lethal-drone shipment delivered by train this morning and staged for sale to offshore sentinel clients. at mechanical r&d center, sentinel\'s chief bagman sultan is meeting a rogue auroan diplomat and must be captured alive before that window closes. execution deploy from hq at 2015, halo to the lz, and move on foot through alpha and bravo. after securing the factory and collecting buyer/destination intel, take a low-profile site vehicle to charlie, capture sultan as covertly as conditions allow, and drive him to valkyrie-6 for extraction. alpha eliminate the enemy qrf at outpost blue tiger and free the first half of viper-3. bravo secure electric engine factory, free the remaining prisoners, demolish the drone truck, and search for sales-route intel. charlie capture sultan at mechanical r&d center, secure civilians only if needed, and move him to valkyrie-6. hostage priority viper-3 recovery comes before the shipment strike or bagman grab. both detention sites must be stabilized and cleared before the force pushes to charlie. drone shipment at bravo, destroy the supply truck carrying lethal drones and exploit any documents or portable electronics that identify the offshore buyer or next destination. capture rule if civilians are at risk during the sultan takedown, secure the site first. if not, prioritize a quiet live capture and immediate transfer to valkyrie-6. objective alpha outpost blue tiger eliminate the hostile qrf and release the first half of viper-3 from the holding cell. objective bravo electric engine factory free the remaining viper-3 prisoners, demolish the drone shipment truck, and exploit the factory for buyer intelligence. objective charlie mechanical r&d center capture sultan alive during the meeting, then move the detainee to safehouse valkyrie-6 and call extract. ao map wild coast route reference covering the halo insertion, outpost blue tiger, electric engine factory, mechanical r&d center, and safehouse valkyrie-6.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-canopy%20%5B1176193943591993374%5D.html', label: 'op-canopy', searchLabel: 'op canopy', text: 'operation canopy operation canopy a qrf package inserts at lz mustang, clears the fen bog testing zone, silently exploits the photovoltaic park w01 maintenance station with cipherlink tam, then secures fen bog port, confirms the radioactive package with uhf sonar, and calls cbrn decon to recover the suspected tactical warhead. launch site asf hq / tier 1 tasking insertion touchdown at lz mustang around 2300 specialist kit cipherlink tam and uhf sonar carried by est terminal action tag north-dock container and bring in cbrn decon situation enemy forces were observed using lethal drones against allied pows inside fen bog testing zone only hours ago. alpha must halt those atrocities, clear the site, and download comms-building test data as proof of the unit\'s crimes. a second time-sensitive threat is moving through fen bog port: a radioactive shipment that may be a tactical nuclear warhead bound for an underground weapons program. the team must identify the package location, secure the dock area, and hand the container to cbrn decontamination personnel. execution touch down at lz mustang southwest of alpha around 2300 and move on foot through all objectives. the est specialist should use cipherlink tam inside 50 meters of the bravo leader\'s phone without being seen, then use uhf sonar at charlie to confirm the radioactive package before decon is requested. alpha clear fen bog testing zone and pull all test data from the comms building. bravo infiltrate the pv park w01 maintenance station without firing and wirelessly exploit the qrf leader\'s phone. charlie secure fen bog port, scan the container with uhf sonar, call cbrn decon, and rtb. no-shot constraint bravo must stay fully covert. one shot or visible compromise at pv park w01 can spook fen bog port and put the radioactive shipment out of reach. est exploit at bravo, get within 50 meters of any enemy leader at the maintenance station and pull phone data with cipherlink tam to help identify the port container. decon call at charlie, the target container is on the north dock. confirm positive id, mark grid yankee echo 156 niner 0, and relay full hazmat requirements before returning to base. objective alpha fen bog testing zone eliminate hostile forces and recover all drone test data from the comms building as evidence of pow executions. objective bravo photovoltaic park w01 covertly reach the maintenance station, exploit the leader\'s phone with tam, and keep fen bog port unaware. objective charlie fen bog port secure the dock, identify the radioactive package with uhf sonar, and bring in the cbrn retrieval team. ao map fen bog route reference covering lz mustang, fen bog testing zone, photovoltaic park w01, and fen bog port before rtb.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-citrinitas%20%5B1242130620562538516%5D.html', label: 'op-citrinitas', searchLabel: 'op citrinitas', text: 'operation citrinitas operation citrinitas fireteam oxide will halo near fanny bay port, interrogate and eliminate sandman before destroying his explosive shipment, then demolish the whalers bay ammunition depot, retake the land chassis factory, exploit shipment logs at checkpoint weasel foxtrot, and roll into the nor\' wester cliff hideout for cybint analysis. step-off erewhon hq / 2015 hours assault force fireteam oxide in green kit insertion helicopter lift and halo near alpha hideout nor\' wester cliff field hide for resupply and cybint review situation recent humint opened a window to strike enemy positions in whalers bay by destroying their main ammunition warehouse and retaking the land chassis factory tied to lethal drone production. a local manifest indicates those drone parts are being produced for a client in fujian, china, making site exploitation a priority at charlie and delta. sandman, the enemy demolition expert linked to multiple civilian infrastructure bombings in the ao, has just arrived at fanny bay port with a fresh explosive shipment. he is a high-priority target of opportunity and should be interrogated first, then eliminated with his security detail before the crates are destroyed. execution oxide deploys from erewhon hq at 2015, inserts by helicopter and halo near alpha, and then patrols on foot or uses low-profile local transport between objectives. after delta, move northwest to the nor\' wester cliff hideout to resupply, recuperate, and analyze collected cybint before the next strike. alpha interrogate sandman at fanny bay port, kill him and his security detail, then demolish the explosive crates staged in the east warehouse. bravo secure checkpoint weasel delta and the storage depot, then conduct a controlled demolition of the warehouse ammunition stockpile. charlie retake land chassis factory and exploit the site to identify where drone parts are being shipped. delta hit checkpoint weasel foxtrot, search shipment logs, and move to the covert field hideout for cybint exploitation. sandman pid sandman can be treated as any enemy near the helo at fanny bay port. interrogate first for operational details, then terminate and burn the explosives load. civilian handling checkpoint weasel delta and the storage depot may include civilians, but they can be disregarded for roleplay during the bravo demolition phase. cybint follow-on at nor\' wester cliff, analyze portable-device cybint to identify channels port as the next drone-shipment transfer point, then stage through hunt beach bivouac and destroy that shipment covertly. objective alpha fanny bay port interrogate sandman, kill him with his detail, and destroy the explosive crates staged inside the east warehouse. objective bravo checkpoint weasel delta / storage depot secure the checkpoint and depot, then execute a controlled demolition of the ammunition stockpile in the warehouse. objective charlie land chassis factory retake the facility and conduct sse to confirm where the fujian-bound drone components are being routed. objective delta checkpoint weasel foxtrot exploit convoy and shipment logs, then shift northwest to the nor\' wester cliff hideout for the post-assault intelligence readout. ao map whalers bay route reference covering fanny bay port, checkpoint weasel delta, land chassis factory, checkpoint weasel foxtrot, and the move to nor\' wester cliff.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-condor%20%5B1174870926349836298%5D.html', label: 'op-condor', searchLabel: 'op condor', text: 'operation condor operation condor a night halo strike in black kit will investigate ort-5\'s last known position, silently clear ancient harbor, then seize howard airfield, neutralize hvt falcon near the helipad, and break the behemoth-backed weapon stash identified after operation gator. insertion blackhawk halo into northwest sinking country kit black night loadout with heavy firepower primary hvt falcon / john anderson\'s personal pilot end state debrief on site and call allied forces to establish an fob situation post-gator intelligence has verified the enemy unit\'s primary weapon stash at howard airfield, making the site the main objective for this strike. before pushing the runway complex, the team must first clear ancient harbor to the west and investigate ort-5\'s last known position after comms were lost with the recon element. falcon, john anderson\'s personal pilot, is expected at the airfield and must be eliminated to disrupt the wolves command structure. a behemoth drone and reinforced ground security are defending the area, so the charlie assault should be treated as a violent close fight. execution the team inserts by blackhawk and halo to bypass heavy radar and air defenses, then moves to the ao under night cover in black kit. ancient harbor must be cleared without triggering an early alarm at howard airfield, since that would compromise the follow-on strike against falcon and the weapons stockpile. alpha move from the halo ip to ort-5\'s last known position and determine the recon team\'s status. bravo clear ancient harbor silently and prevent the covert meeting there from warning the airfield. charlie secure howard airfield, kill falcon near the helipad, and neutralize the behemoth-backed defenses. airfield threat a heavily armed behemoth and a reinforced land drone presence are guarding howard airfield. bring enough firepower to end the charlie fight decisively. stealth constraint bravo must be kept quiet. any alarm raised at ancient harbor can harden howard airfield before the assault team arrives. friendly unknown ort-5 went dark in the ao. alpha is a welfare and recovery check before the team commits to the maritime outpost and airfield objectives. objective alpha ort-5 last known position investigate the recon team\'s last known location near the halo ip and confirm whether ort-5 can be recovered or linked back into the assault. objective bravo ancient harbor clear the covert maritime outpost and the meeting activity on site without broadcasting a warning to howard airfield. objective charlie howard airfield seize the weapons stash, eliminate falcon around the helipad, and collapse the airfield\'s behemoth-supported defenses. ao map northwest sinking country route reference covering the halo ip, ort-5\'s last known position, ancient harbor, and howard airfield.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-conundrum%20%5B1240610538631860274%5D.html', label: 'op-conundrum', searchLabel: 'op conundrum', text: 'operation conundrum operation conundrum qrf jaguar will halo east of rigel residences, recover cia asset sandpiper from a locked-down sentinel cordon, eliminate hvt sphinx and the enigma command element at jace skell conference hall, exploit checkpoint viper foxtrot if the route stays quiet, and then clear blue viper outpost to break enigma\'s remaining force structure. step-off erewhon hq / 1900 hours insertion halo to the lz east of alpha, then move on foot off-road primary hvt sphinx / enigma commanding officer recovery priority safeguard sandpiper before the jace skell hit situation cia asset sandpiper, embedded undercover at jace skell conference hall, has produced an actionable target package on enigma after prior sigint linked that unit to covert action on auroa and repeated civilian and allied rebel casualties. intelligence indicates sphinx was trained by a rogue veteran of 1st nzsas, so the opposing force should be treated as a highly capable sof element. sandpiper triggered his sarsat beacon at 1350. toc camera access from a previous comint tap confirms rigel residences is now locked down by sentinel security, with guards blocking exits and conducting violent interrogations in the area. execution qrf jaguar departs erewhon hq at 1900, halos to the lz east of alpha, and moves to each objective on foot while avoiding road exposure. the sequence must stay quiet enough to avoid spooking sphinx or triggering a radio warning to blue viper outpost before the command hall strike lands. alpha stabilize rigel residences and secure sandpiper before the lockdown escalates into civilian casualties. bravo hit jace skell conference hall and eliminate sphinx with his sentinel security detail. charlie if conditions allow, clear checkpoint viper foxtrot and bag logs and portable electronics tied to convoy movement through the ao. delta assault blue viper outpost, free the captive allied rebel, then call pelican to help establish the site as a rebel fob. compromise risk any premature alert from alpha or bravo could push sphinx out of reach or warn the enigma fob, so the movement plan should stay off-road and control radio/weapon signature as long as possible. friendly asset sandpiper is the first-person source for the jace skell target package and must be protected at alpha before the force pivots to the conference hall strike. enemy capability expect disciplined enigma personnel and a trained sof commander. sphinx may present as any special enemy profile at bravo and should be treated as the key terminal objective there. objective alpha rigel residences break the lockdown, prevent civilian casualties, and secure sandpiper so the source survives the enigma takedown. objective bravo jace skell conference hall neutralize sphinx and the meeting security detail before a warning reaches blue viper outpost. objective charlie checkpoint viper foxtrot target-of-opportunity sweep for logs and portable electronics that explain what enigma convoys have been moving across this border sector. objective delta blue viper outpost eliminate the remaining enigma unit, free the rebel prisoner confirmed by humint photo, and hand the site to pelican for rebel fob setup and on-site debrief. ao map infinity and new stirling border-region route reference covering the east-of-alpha halo insertion, rigel residences, jace skell conference hall, checkpoint viper foxtrot, and blue viper outpost.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-crescent%20%5B1165985681219268628%5D.html', label: 'op-crescent', searchLabel: 'op crescent', text: 'operation crescent operation crescent a night halo package from fob bandit will strike the raven abduction unit operating around southwest restricted area 01, hit the leadership meeting at stony creek village, place a comint tap at gate 05, clear the devil\'s forest gold mine cell through its tunnels, and then restore control of omega r&d center while safeguarding any civilians left on site. departure point fob bandit / south cape station insertion little bird night halo into southwest ra01 at 1500 meters or higher priority threat raven unit tied to liberty province civilian abductions final support call guardian to relocate civilians and exfil back to fob bandit situation sentinel\'s raven unit has been traced to a forced-labor abduction network pulling civilians out of liberty province and moving them into camps around restricted area 01. reconnaissance indicates a critical meeting tonight split between stony creek village and devil\'s forest gold mine, creating a rare opportunity to break the unit\'s local leadership structure in one pass. a separate detachment has also seized the omega r&d center, where lethal drone research is under way. the mission\'s top priority is to neutralize raven first, then retake the r&d site, verify research materials have not been compromised, and ensure any civilians there remain unharmed. execution the team launches from fob bandit by little bird, halos into the ao under night cover, and stays above 1500 meters during insertion because behemoth and ra01 air defenses are active. after landing, establish the ambush at alpha first, then plant the comint device, tunnel into devil\'s forest gold mine, and finish by pulling power at omega r&d before calling guardian for civilian relocation and exfil support. phase 1 ambush the raven leader arriving by road at stony creek village and clear the enemy presence there. phase 2 install the comint device on the gate 05 relay for traffic monitoring. phase 3 use one of the three tunnel entrances for a quiet infil at devil\'s forest gold mine and eliminate the remaining raven members. phase 4 deactivate the omega r&d generator immediately, retake the center, secure all civilians, and coordinate guardian-assisted exfil. air threat behemoth and other ra01 air-defense systems are active, so the little bird halo profile should stay at 1500 meters or above to preserve the undetected insertion. tunnel access devil\'s forest gold mine has three tunnel entrances. a tunnel-first entry is the preferred way to surprise the target cell and keep the charlie hit quiet. civilian handling omega r&d center must be retaken without harming civilians. once the site is safe, radio guardian to assist with relocation and close out the return to fob bandit. alpha stony creek village establish a road ambush, eliminate the raven leader as he arrives, and clear the enemy personnel holding the village meeting site. bravo gate 05 network relay install a comint device on the relay to monitor traffic and generate follow-on intelligence on the network\'s communications pattern. charlie devil\'s forest gold mine infiltrate through the tunnel system, use the underground approach to preserve surprise, and eliminate the remaining raven unit personnel. delta omega r&d center deactivate the power generator immediately, restore control over the facility, secure any civilians still present, and confirm no research material has been compromised. tacmap southwest ra01 area reference for the halo insertion, stony creek village ambush, gate 05 comint placement, devil\'s forest gold mine tunnel assault, and omega r&d center recapture before exfil to fob bandit.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-crusader%20%5B1242425388441796628%5D.html', label: 'op-crusader', searchLabel: 'op crusader', text: 'operation crusader operation crusader team crusader will execute a halo insertion into west ra1 to finish the uav-base takedown uncovered during operation neptune spear. the force must silently remove the outpost red ferret qrf before any alert can launch the drones, sabotage assembly hall omega 02, shut down the arrow testing zone, and exfil by flying the two captured gunships back to south cape station for allied use. briefing site south cape station at 1900 hours deployment 2020 step-off, halo jump to the lz south of alpha area of operations west ra1 uav launch and maintenance complex lineage follow-up to operation neptune spear, part 2 of the same strike sequence situation aerial isr launched after operation neptune spear confirmed two primary uav launch and maintenance bases in west ra1. the mission priority is to sabotage those uavs and render the supporting infrastructure unusable before sentinel can launch them and break the strike window. outpost red ferret is the first problem because it houses a sizable qrf tasked to respond to emergencies at the western bases. if alpha is compromised, the enemy may launch the uavs immediately, which would prevent a full single-sortie destruction of the fleet. execution crusader inserts by halo at the lz south of alpha, then moves on foot along the tacmap route using the isr-recommended entry points. alpha must remain covert for as long as possible. the arrow testing zone should be approached from top to bottom as indicated on the tacmap, which is the safest route assessed during planning. phase 1 neutralize the red ferret qrf quietly and exploit any targets of opportunity before the uav sites are alerted. phase 2 secure assembly hall omega 02 and sabotage all uavs and facility systems on site. phase 3 infiltrate the arrow testing zone from the top-down approach, sabotage the facility, and use the two helicopters on site to return to south cape station. covert constraint alpha cannot go loud early. if red ferret gets a warning out, the western uav bases can launch their aircraft and destroy the chance to neutralize all platforms in one sortie. route guidance isr strongly recommends the marked infiltration points and a top-to-bottom entry through arrow testing zone. that approach should be treated as the default unless contact forces a reroute. objective handling assembly hall omega 02 should be treated as a full sabotage target for uavs and infrastructure. civilian presence can be disregarded for roleplay at bravo per the original mission note. alpha outpost red ferret eliminate the enemy qrf, preserve covert status as long as possible, and act on any targets of opportunity that could warn the western uav sites. bravo assembly hall omega 02 secure the hall and sabotage every uav plus the supporting facility infrastructure so the site can no longer launch or maintain aircraft. charlie arrow testing zone infiltrate from the safer top-down route, sabotage the test facility, then fly the two helicopters on site back to south cape station and turn the gunships over to allied forces at the fob. tacmap west ra1 movement plan showing the lz south of alpha, outpost red ferret, assembly hall omega 02, and the recommended top-down approach into arrow testing zone before flying the captured helicopters back to south cape station.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-crypt%20%5B1166778178098962472%5D.html', label: 'op-crypt', searchLabel: 'op crypt', text: 'operation crypt operation crypt a late-afternoon helicopter package from south cape station will hit four northeast liberty sites tied to sentinel\'s organ-trafficking pipeline while the british nca raids the london market operating under the alias golden goose. the team must establish pid, eliminate the commanders, radio operators, and bagmen running the local network, and collect actionable intelligence before any alert lets the suspects scatter. briefing site south cape station / asf hq tier 1 area of operations northeast liberty organ-processing corridor insertion helicopter lz south of alpha, then foot movement through the targets extraction use the helicopter at auroa hospital if possible, otherwise call for pickup to south cape station situation intelligence links a london-based organ market to sentinel harvesting operations on auroa. operating under the alias golden goose, the network sells organs taken post-mortem from outcasts captured during sentinel raids, then ships them overseas through a concealed medical-processing chain. intercepted traffic confirms the people running that network are motivated by major financial returns and are actively coordinating with overseas buyers. the nca will strike the london market at the same time this team hits cryohope, the cryogenization center, eternity, and auroa hospital in northeast liberty. the intent is a synchronized dismantling of both ends of the pipeline, paired with enough site exploitation to drive follow-on targeting. execution the team deploys by helicopter in late afternoon, lands south of cryohope, and then clears each marked site on foot. at every objective, pid comes first, followed by the elimination of high-ranking operators and the collection of records, devices, or documents. civilians at the marked locations are suspected collaborators, so hidden weapons remain a concern even when personnel present as noncombatants. alpha clear cryohope, identify leadership personnel, and seize all intelligence tied to local processing and shipment management. bravo push to the cryogenization center and repeat the pid, leadership kill/capture, and site-exploitation process. charlie hit eternity, account for the large guard presence and possible underground space, and pull all exploitable material before anyone flees. delta secure auroa hospital, eliminate the command cell, document the execution evidence, and extract using the on-site helicopter if viable. enemy presence current estimates indicate 10 tangos at cryohope, 9 at the cryogenization center, 15+ at eternity with a possible underground section on the right side, and a platoon-sized element of 25+ at auroa hospital. cleaner threat sentinel cleaners may appear in civilian clothing at the target sites. maintain weapon and hand awareness during pid because concealed weapons remain a realistic threat. external link nca footage from london positively identifies a missing outcast inside the overseas organ market, while local footage shows another execution at auroa hospital 17 hours before the briefing. those two references reinforce the direct liberty-to-london pipeline. alpha cryohope land south of the first target, move into cryohope, confirm pid on the local command or bagman element, eliminate the leadership cell, and collect all usable intelligence from the site. bravo cryogenization center clear the center, maintain close scrutiny on suspected civilian collaborators, and recover documents or devices that connect the cryogenization chain to the wider golden goose network. charlie eternity assault the eternity site, control the large enemy presence, investigate the suspected underground section suggested by elevation readings, and prevent any leadership personnel from escaping with records. delta auroa hospital secure the hospital processing node, eliminate high-ranking sentinel personnel, recover execution and shipment evidence, and extract back to south cape station using the on-site helicopter if possible. tacmap route reference for the landing zone south of cryohope, the sequential movement through cryohope, cryogenization center, eternity, and auroa hospital, and the planned hospital-side extraction back to south cape station.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-cyclone%20%5B1264392246090797067%5D.html', label: 'op-cyclone', searchLabel: 'op cyclone', text: 'operation cyclone operation cyclone a blackhawk-borne haho package will step from erewhon hq to break up a sentinel splinter cell planning coordinated attacks against critical st infrastructure. the force will intercept the weapons pipeline at howard port, destroy the sparrowhawk sam site, infiltrate camp tiger before its servers lock down, and finish by destroying the equipment depot stockpiles while bringing hvt torus back to hq for interrogation. briefing site erewhon hq at 2014 hours insertion method blackhawk under darkness with haho jump into the ao movement plan foot infiltration with maritime transfer from alpha to bravo mission focus preemptive strike on logistics, air defense, command systems, and supply stockpiles situation cybint indicates that a sentinel splinter cell is preparing a coordinated assault on critical st infrastructure. four locations form the core of that network. howard port is being used to smuggle advanced weaponry into the region. sparrowhawk sam site threatens friendly air operations. camp tiger functions as the cell\'s tactical command center and barracks. the equipment depot stores the munitions and supplies keeping the whole effort viable. the mission is built around neutralizing the network before the assault can be launched. speed matters, but so does discipline: the team needs to stay stealthy long enough to seize intelligence and disrupt systems before the enemy can destroy data or lock down the key sites. execution the team inserts under darkness, lands, and proceeds to howard port on foot. after interrogating and killing hvt neon there, the force uses the boat to reach the island sam objective. from there the mission pushes inland to camp tiger for a stealth intelligence hit before closing out at the equipment depot with demolition and hvt capture. phase 1 intercept the advanced-weapons shipment at howard port and interrogate hvt neon before neutralizing him. phase 2 use the boat to reach the island and execute controlled demolition of the sparrowhawk sam site. phase 3 infiltrate camp tiger, pull intelligence before the servers lock down, then cripple the toc and eliminate the remaining splinter-cell presence. phase 4 destroy the dock and warehouse stockpiles at the equipment depot, then capture hvt torus alive for return to hq. priority interrogation neon is the senior logistics coordinator linked to the howard port shipment and can expose the structure of the planned hit. he should be interrogated immediately on site before termination. stealth window camp tiger is the most sensitive intelligence phase. detection there risks server lockdown and loss of exploitable data, so the team should treat charlie as a quiet penetration before shifting into destructive action. end-state capture torus is the officer in charge of distribution at the equipment depot and the required live capture at the end of the mission. the depot can be destroyed, but torus needs to survive for interrogation back at hq. alpha howard port intercept and secure the advanced-weapon shipment, interrogate hvt neon about the planned strike, then neutralize him once the intelligence is extracted. roleplay guidance: any enemy near the helipad can stand in as the hvt if needed. bravo sparrowhawk sam site reach the island objective by boat and execute controlled demolition of the sam site to restore air freedom over the area. charlie camp tiger infiltrate carefully, gather intelligence before the enemy can lock down their servers, then cripple the tactical operations center and eliminate the remaining splinter-cell fighters. delta equipment depot destroy the main stockpiles of munitions and supplies across the dock and warehouse, then capture hvt torus, the distribution officer, alive for interrogation at hq. tacmap sinking country route showing the haho insertion, howard port interdiction, island transfer to the sam site, camp tiger penetration, and final equipment depot strike.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-dolomite%20%5B1165626737028243527%5D.html', label: 'op-dolomite', searchLabel: 'op dolomite', text: 'operation dolomite operation dolomite a white-uniform strike element will move from erewhon hq into the mount hodgson area to break up a rare-earth extraction grab linked to sentinel\'s drone-production pipeline. the mission starts with a bridge ambush on the primary hvt, then secures checkpoint tiger echo, seizes a supply truck at drone station w041, captures the bagman alive at silent valley mine, and delivers the stolen load to site tango niner before extraction and interrogation turnover. mission area mount hodgson ao around silent valley mine insertion profile white-uniform movement from erewhon hq to the bridge ambush ip primary intent kill the primary hvt and capture the bagman alive for interrogation support outcome recover weapons and supply cargo for allied rebels via truck handoff situation command has received credible intelligence that two high-value targets are set to meet at silent valley mine. the broader purpose of that meeting appears tied to sentinel\'s attempt to seize rare-earth extraction needed for advanced drone production and to feed a clandestine arms-trade network. the operational window is narrow, with the primary hvt marked for elimination and the secondary target, described as the bagman, slated for live capture and interrogation. at the same time, a critical shipment of weapons and supplies is moving through drone station w041. capturing that cargo is important for allied rebels who are already under severe supply pressure. the mission therefore blends ambush, site exploitation, cargo seizure, and live hvt recovery in a single sweep. execution the team departs erewhon in white uniforms and establishes an ambush at the bridge, expecting the primary hvt to transit through the area. if the vehicle does not appear after a reasonable hold, the force will assume the primary target is already at the mine meeting the bagman and continue the mission, ensuring only the chosen target is neutralized while the bagman remains unharmed for capture. phase 1 recon the bridge, establish the ambush, and eliminate the primary hvt during transit if the opportunity appears. phase 2 secure checkpoint tiger echo and collect any usable intelligence on local movements or mine activity. phase 3 take drone station w041, steal the on-site truck, and move in convoy toward silent valley mine. phase 4 capture the bagman alive at the mine, load any additional supplies, deliver the truck to site tango niner, radio jaguar for pickup, then extract and return with the bagman for interrogation. ambush window the bridge kill remains the cleanest way to reduce overall kinetic exposure. if no vehicle appears from the tunnel or checkpoint corridor after the hold, the team should continue and treat the mine meeting itself as the decisive engagement point. capture rule the bagman is the interrogation target and must remain alive. if the mission shifts from bridge ambush to mine assault, the team should neutralize only the selected primary target and preserve the bagman for exploitation. rebel support the supply truck and any additional cargo collected at drone station w041 and silent valley mine are intended for allied rebels facing critical shortages, making the truck-delivery phase operationally important rather than optional. alpha bridge ambush set the ambush on the bridge and eliminate the primary hvt during his transit if he appears. if the transit window collapses, carry that kill requirement forward into the silent valley mine meeting. bravo checkpoint tiger echo secure the checkpoint and collect all available intelligence that clarifies sentinel\'s movements, mine access, and supply routing in the sector. charlie drone station w041 clear the station, steal the truck on site, and form the convoy that will carry recovered supplies onward to the mine and final handoff point. delta silent valley mine capture the secondary hvt, the bagman, alive before he leaves the area and load any additional supplies found on site onto the truck for onward movement. echo site tango niner and extract drop the supply truck at site tango niner, radio jaguar for pickup, then call for extraction and return to base with the bagman for interrogation. tacmap mount hodgson area route showing the bridge ambush site, checkpoint tiger echo, drone station w041, silent valley mine, and the final truck handoff at site tango niner before extraction.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-excalibur%20%5B1173634225572958318%5D.html', label: 'op-excalibur', searchLabel: 'op excalibur', text: 'operation excalibur operation excalibur a rapid black-ppe strike package will launch from hq aboard an overseer helicopter to clear a four-part crisis across the ao: secure the world seedvault chemical site and capture chemist hvt colombo, recover a manpads prototype at control station viper 03, prevent the assassination of an auroan diplomat at checkpoint viper bravo, and seize a high-value shipment at new stirling freight yard for convoy delivery to ancient village. launch 1900 from hq via overseer helicopter mission profile rapid multi-target strike with hazmat, hvt, eod, and convoy tasks critical equipment black hazmat ppe, gas masks, and pistols for seedvault entry end state all targets secured, shipment delivered to ancient village, then rtb situation zulu 3 reconnaissance has confirmed four linked threats inside the area of operations. hostile forces have converted the world seedvault into a staging point for an unidentified chemical weapon. control station viper 03 recently received a manpads prototype now locked inside a biometric armory. at checkpoint viper bravo, sentinel is preparing a false-flag bridge blast meant to kill an auroan diplomat and blame the outcasts. at the same time, undercover points of contact at new stirling freight yard have identified a high-value shipment awaiting transfer by rail. the mission therefore mixes speed with precision. the team must move fast enough to preserve the diplomat and shipment while still managing the hazardous chemical site and capturing or eliminating key enemy operators tied to the wider network. execution the package inserts rapidly by overseer helicopter, then works the objective chain in sequence. alpha is a hazmat-restricted capture site. bravo is a precision assault tied to biometric access and a manpads recovery. charlie is an eod intervention to stop a false-flag assassination. delta finishes with shipment capture and convoy movement to ancient village, where bravo team will recover the cargo after handoff. phase 1 secure the world seedvault, capture colombo alive, and call in the cbrn team for analysis and interrogation support. phase 2 assault control station viper 03, stop hvt monk from escaping, and recover the manpads prototype from the biometric armory. phase 3 conduct eod at checkpoint viper bravo to prevent the diplomat convoy ambush and preserve the bridge. phase 4 secure the new stirling shipment, convoy it to the makeshift dock at ancient village, hand it to follow-on allies, and return to base. hazmat control the world seedvault must be treated as a live chemical-threat site. gas masks and black hazmat ppe are mandatory there, and pistols-only handling is the safer weapons posture inside the confined contamination risk area. hvt package colombo, identified as benjamin hayes, is the main chemist overseeing the seedvault lab and must be taken alive. monk, identified as richard turner, controls biometric access to the viper 03 armory and cannot be allowed to escape. diplomatic risk sentinel intends to stage the bridge strike at viper bravo as if it were an outcast attack, then present itself as the rescue force. the eod phase is therefore strategically important beyond simply saving the convoy. alpha world seedvault infiltrate and secure the site using gas masks, hazmat ppe, and pistols-only handling where possible. capture hvt colombo alive, hold him in place, and radio the cbrn team to take over substance analysis and interrogation before moving on. bravo control station viper 03 conduct a precision assault on the station, eliminate or detain hvt monk before he escapes, and use his biometric access to recover the manpads prototype from the secured armory. charlie checkpoint viper bravo clear the bridge area and perform eod on sentinel\'s demolition setup to stop the planned assassination of the auroan diplomat traveling through in a night convoy. delta new stirling freight yard to ancient village recover the supply truck carrying the high-value shipment, secure the freight yard, and convoy the package to the makeshift dock at ancient village where bravo team will recover it after mission completion. tacmap ao overview tying together the seedvault chemical site, viper 03 assault, bridge eod stop, freight-yard truck seizure, and the final ancient village dock handoff before rtb.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-falcon-shield%20%5B1239394122486517811%5D.html', label: 'op-falcon-shield', searchLabel: 'op falcon shield', text: 'operation falcon shield operation falcon shield fireteam guardian will step from erewhon hq on a covert foot patrol to prevent sentinel forces from compromising the secret twin falls mountain fob. the mission is to break up a meeting involving hvt osprey, demolish the growing enemy observation-and-weapons position at control station tiger 04, recapture the shipping center, and move the recovered medical supply trucks to allied forces at russel homestead before extracting with pequod. briefing site erewhon hq at 1946 hours mission profile covert pre-emptive foot patrol east from erewhon team loadout fireteam guardian in green kits with quiet movement priority mission focus protect the fob by removing enemy reconnaissance, command, and supply pressure situation raven 2 reports increasing enemy encroachment around the secret twin falls mountain fob, creating an immediate risk that the site could be discovered or isolated. three priority targets have emerged: hvt osprey, an enemy drone controller meeting a lieutenant at the ancient sacred site; control station tiger 04, where sentinel is building an observation post around a recent helicopter weapons delivery; and the shipping center, which has been seized despite being the main pipeline for essential medical supplies arriving by rail. the operation is intended to stay fully deniable. enemy patrols encountered in the wilderness must be removed quietly, and any portable electronics or extra intelligence collected along the route should be bagged to determine how close the enemy is to understanding the fob\'s position and mission footprint. execution guardian departs erewhon at 2000 and moves on foot to the east to reach alpha without exposing the fob origin point. the team first disrupts the osprey meeting, then collapses the observation-and-weapons buildup at tiger 04, and finally retakes the shipping center before driving the two supply trucks to russel homestead for allied transfer and extraction. phase 1 reach the ancient sacred site and eliminate osprey before the meeting disperses. phase 2 secure control station tiger 04, exploit the site, and demolish the station, helicopter, and weapons cache. phase 3 recapture the shipping center and move the two supply trucks east to russel homestead in sinking country. phase 4 radio pequod at russel homestead, extract, and return to base once the handoff is complete. fob security the enemy must remain unaware of where guardian came from. this is a pre-emptive counter-encroachment mission, so outer-wilderness patrols should be treated as security threats to the twin falls mountain fob and neutralized accordingly. priority target osprey is the drone controller linked to the meeting at the ancient sacred site. eliminating him before the session adjourns is the fastest way to disrupt the enemy\'s local coordination cycle. sustainment the shipping center supplies critical medical stocks, so the two recovered trucks need to reach russel homestead intact for allied redistribution after the site is retaken. alpha ancient sacred site eliminate hvt osprey before the meeting breaks up. for mission-roleplay purposes, any enemy on or near the site can stand in as the hvt if needed. bravo control station tiger 04 secure the observation post, conduct full site exploitation, and execute controlled demolition on the station, the helicopter, and the weapons cache recently delivered there. charlie shipping center to russel homestead recapture the shipping center, then deliver both supply trucks to allied forces at russel homestead to the east in sinking country before calling pequod for extraction. tacmap route from erewhon through the ancient sacred site, control station tiger 04, and the shipping center, with the truck handoff and extraction staging continuing east at russel homestead in sinking country.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-furlough%20%5B1242287075139649556%5D.html', label: 'op-furlough', searchLabel: 'op furlough', text: 'operation furlough operation furlough qrf moonshine will move from south cape station into the channels ao to recover sensitive skell cargo from a downed transport, rescue two captured skell field engineers, and seize hvt warden before the enemy can consolidate the wreck-site exploitation and detention network. the package will move light and covert on foot across all objectives, then extract from hlz dusky at hunt beach bivouac. briefing site south cape station at 2036 hours area of operations channels ao southwest of long island insertion method foot movement from the lz southeast of alpha team profile qrf moonshine in light black kits for speed and concealment situation at 2009 hours, apex 2 reported that a skell transport cargo aircraft flying from restricted area 01 was shot down by a legion drone swarm over channels airspace. most of the classified cargo went into the water, but aerial assets have identified one container washed ashore on west cape. analysts assess that container may hold an advanced uav targeting module, making it the first priority before local enemy forces can recover it. the wider situation also includes two skell tech field engineers held nearby at a fuel depot and a fortified outpost. sigint suggests the enemy may be building leverage for a prisoner exchange tied to lieutenants being held at liberty. separately, enemy logistics expert warden has surfaced at channels port, and capturing him could expose the broader trafficking network operating in the region. execution qrf moonshine deploys from south cape station at 2100 and lands southeast of alpha, then advances on foot through the objective chain. the mission flows from cargo recovery into dual rescue action, then ends with the hvt grab at channels port before the force breaks for hlz dusky and calls for extraction. phase 1 recover the sensitive skell uav targeting module from the washed-ashore cargo container on west cape. phase 2 secure the navy fuelling station, free holmes, and act on any targets of opportunity. phase 3 recapture red shark outpost, free watson, and exploit the site for regional intent indicators. phase 4 capture warden at channels port, then move to hlz dusky at hunt beach bivouac for extraction. priority recovery the washed-ashore container may contain an advanced uav targeting module from restricted area 01. recovering it before the enemy secures the site is the opening priority because of the potential technical sensitivity. rescue package holmes and watson are the two captured skell field engineers. both rescues matter operationally and politically because the enemy appears to be preparing leverage for a possible exchange. hvt value warden is the enemy logistics expert at channels port. capturing him alive could unravel the trafficking architecture behind the current cargo, detention, and movement network. alpha west cape cargo recovery retrieve the sensitive skell technology module from the washed-ashore cargo container before local enemy elements can recover or destroy it. bravo navy fuelling station secure the fuel depot, liberate vip #1 holmes, and exploit any targets of opportunity encountered during the clearance. charlie red shark outpost recapture the outpost, liberate vip #2 watson, and conduct site exploitation to clarify the enemy\'s intent and local posture in the region. delta channels port and extract capture hvt warden at the construction area on the top-center side of channels port, then move to hlz dusky at hunt beach bivouac and call for extraction once the full package is secure. tacmap channels-area route showing the crash-related cargo recovery site, both engineer rescue objectives, channels port for the warden capture, and the final move to hlz dusky at hunt beach bivouac.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-gator%20%5B1174862764615934063%5D.html', label: 'op-gator', searchLabel: 'op gator', text: 'operation gator operation gator qrf nox will launch from erewhon hq to stop a sentinel cell known as the vanguard before it can release anthrax into the diamond river water system at dawn. the package must secure the river infrastructure, confirm the distribution line remains uncontaminated, seize the anthrax production lab, and capture the vanguard leader for return to hq. briefing site erewhon hq at 2044 hours area of operations fen bog and the diamond river corridor insertion method little bird insertion southeast of alpha before foot movement required kit cbrn loadout with gas masks for volatile anthrax exposure risk situation a renegade sentinel terrorist cell referred to in intercepted communications as the vanguard has seized critical infrastructure along the diamond river, east auroa\'s main drinking-water source. sigint indicates the cell intends to dump anthrax into the distribution system at dawn, creating a mass-casualty event for civilians and a severe ecological incident across the region. current isr also places the vanguard\'s leader at the anthrax-producing laboratory. the mission therefore combines immediate water-security action with a targeted hvt capture before the network can disperse or trigger contamination. execution qrf nox deploys at 2100 aboard a little bird and lands southeast of alpha, then patrols on foot through the target chain. the first two sites verify that the river infrastructure remains clean while removing sentinel support material. the third phase collapses the lab and captures the hvt, and the final phase shifts to hlz saladin for extraction. phase 1 secure bluecorp startup, destroy the weapons cache, and collect a water sample to confirm no contamination occurred. phase 2 repeat the same containment and sampling process at andersons farm. phase 3 hit hogweed station, secure the anthrax lab, capture the vanguard leader, and call titan to dismantle the facility. phase 4 move to hlz saladin, radio the little bird pilot, and extract the hvt back to erewhon hq. cbrn risk anthrax exposure is the defining mission hazard. gas masks and cbrn discipline are mandatory anywhere near the lab, storage materials, or contaminated infrastructure indicators. water security bluecorp startup and andersons farm both need physical security plus on-site water sampling so command can confirm the distribution system was not compromised before dawn. end state the operation is complete only when the infrastructure is verified clean, the anthrax lab is turned over to titan, and the vanguard leader is in custody for extraction. alpha bluecorp startup secure the site, destroy the weapons cache, and gather a water sample to confirm no contamination has already entered the diamond river system through this node. bravo andersons farm clear the farm complex, remove the weapons cache, and collect a second water sample to validate that the broader river-distribution line remains uncontaminated. charlie hogweed station secure the anthrax lab, apprehend the vanguard leader, and radio secondary cbrn team titan to dismantle the site once the objective area is under control. delta hlz saladin move to the extraction zone, call in the little bird pilot, and return with the hvt to erewhon hq once the contamination threat is neutralized. tacmap fen bog operation route showing the insertion point, bluecorp startup, andersons farm, hogweed station, and hlz saladin extraction sequence across the diamond river threat corridor.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-golden-claw%20%5B1243568774830100614%5D.html', label: 'op-golden-claw', searchLabel: 'op golden claw', text: 'operation golden claw operation golden claw fireteam hawk will launch from south cape station to cut the drone support layer behind sentinel\'s planned strike on liberty, then pivot to a detention-site rescue tied to the abduction of a c1 skell engineer. the package must collapse the relay and lethal drone-control nodes, recover anything portable or classified, and ensure the engineer is linked up with bandit 4 for extraction. step-off 1946 hours from south cape station primary area liberty ao initial access landing at safehouse lima 6 near the drone stations required kit low-profile movement with demolition charges and emp support situation sentinel has deployed two drone-control sites to watch liberty while preparing a large-scale strike on the center of auroa. bravo team is already pressuring the southern axis, leaving hawk to isolate and kill the drone-support element that enables isr coverage and lethal patrol control over the city during the lockdown. at the same time, cybint indicates a c1 skell tech engineer abducted from the dam three hours earlier was transferred to cell 4b at the detention center this afternoon. hawk is responsible for verifying the holding site, safeguarding the vip, and coordinating the extraction handoff with bandit 4. execution hawk departs south cape station at 2000 and inserts near safehouse lima 6 to work the objective chain either on foot or with on-site transport while keeping a low signature. the first two phases remove sentinel\'s relay and drone-control capability. the third phase clears the detention site, confirms the engineer\'s location, and transitions to exploitation if the cell transfer picture proves false. phase 1 move from lima 6 to drone station w191 and destroy the network relay after recovering portable electronics. phase 2 recapture control station fox 01, demolish the weapons cache, and seize any confidential documents. phase 3 secure the detention center and verify cell 4b for vip pheonix. phase 4 if the cell is empty, request a raven-3 isr flyby, exploit the site, then move to the ammunition storage northwest across the water to free pheonix and hand him to bandit 4. priority the drone network must be degraded before sentinel can use those sites to support the planned attack on liberty. demolition and emp effects should be decisive enough to prevent any quick restoration of isr or lethal drone tasking. recovery portable electronics, confidential documents, and any exploitable records tied to sentinel\'s drone architecture or detainee movement are high-value collection targets during the strike. rescue twist pheonix is not expected to remain at cell 4b by the time hawk arrives. the detention-center phase should be treated as a verification and exploitation step leading into the final rescue at the nearby ammunition storage. alpha drone station w191 secure the relay site, recover any portable electronics that clarify sentinel\'s network picture, and execute a controlled demolition to disable the drone-control relay supporting liberty-area surveillance. bravo control station fox 01 recapture the station, destroy the on-site weapons cache, and retrieve any confidential documents tied to lethal drone tasking or the wider attack package forming around liberty. charlie detention center and follow-on rescue secure the detention site and check cell 4b for vip pheonix. if he has already been moved, request a raven-3 isr flyby across a two-kilometer perimeter, gather all site-exploitation material, then shift northwest across the water to the ammunition storage, free pheonix from the cages, and link him up with bandit 4 before returning to south cape station. tacmap liberty-area operation path showing the safehouse lima 6 insertion, both drone-control targets, the detention-center check, and the wider movement geometry for the final rescue follow-on.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-hammerhead%20%5B1228874084239020174%5D.html', label: 'op-hammerhead', searchLabel: 'op hammerhead', text: 'operation hammerhead operation hammerhead a seal islands strike package will launch from south cape station to hit emelius port and shark base after intelligence confirmed recent container traffic from russia and china is moving a.r. nerve agent cylinders, torpedoes, and heavy weaponry into auroa. the mission is to infiltrate both sites, neutralize resistance, recover any shipping intelligence, and destroy every identified shipment before it can disperse further inland. area of operations seal islands briefing site south cape station insertion method qrf launch with rhib assault onto both waterfront targets mission focus counter-proliferation strike on chemical agent and maritime weapons shipments situation air force drone patrols have tracked recurring container ship runs into emelius port and shark base over the last several months. within the last twenty-four hours, intelligence confirmed the newest deliveries include a.r. nerve agent cylinders, torpedoes, and other heavy weapons. command has authorized an immediate maritime interdiction before those stocks are broken down and distributed. both targets are defended and sit inside a contested air picture, which limits real-time reconnaissance. archive imagery is available, but the package should expect incomplete isr, active defenses, and contact at both waterfronts. execution the qrf will step from south cape station and use rhib insertion for the first strike at emelius port. once charges are set and detonated from a safe offset, the team transitions directly to shark base and repeats the same demolition package on the second shipment node. phase 1 launch from south cape station and approach emelius port from the water\'s edge. phase 2 clear the port, collect manifests or confidential files, then rig shipments and weapon stacks with c4. phase 3 push to shark base via the entrance docks, secure the base, collect actionable intel, and destroy torpedoes plus nerve agent stockpiles. phase 4 confirm both detonations from safe distance and return to base once both sites are rendered unusable. hazards gas masks are mandatory once the force enters confirmed chemical storage areas. demolition timing needs to respect blast distance and contamination risk around any exposed a.r. nerve agent cylinders. air defense sam coverage in the area degrades aerial reconnaissance, so teams should plan off archive references, shoreline navigation, and local visual confirmation rather than expecting clean overhead isr. defensive systems automated turrets are active at both emelius port and shark base. expect static weapons to cover key approaches, docks, and interior access lanes. alpha emelius port insert from the water\'s edge, clear hostile personnel, and sweep the port thoroughly for shipping manifests or any other confidential files tied to the inbound cargo network. once the site is secure, place c4 on all identified shipments and heavy weapon stores, then break contact to a safe standoff point before detonation. bravo shark base infiltrate through the entrance docks, neutralize the base garrison, and bag any actionable intel that clarifies shipment routing or downstream distribution. locate torpedoes and every nerve agent shipment on site, rig them with c4, and destroy the cache before returning to base. tacmap seal islands operational route showing the south cape station launch, emelius port strike, shark base follow-on hit, and the overall shoreline geometry shaping rhib movement between both objectives.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-hangman%20%5B1274831813814124606%5D.html', label: 'op-hangman', searchLabel: 'op hangman', text: 'operation hangman operation hangman fireteam grizzly will haho into whaler’s bay to dismantle a live human-trafficking network, sweep the checkpoint and harbor routes, capture construction-site boss warlock for handoff, seize overall ringleader darkhorse at the oceanic power plant, and rescue the hostage labor force before more executions occur. brief erewhon hq, 2203 hours insertion night haho infil in black kits, followed by foot movement through alpha to charlie and watercraft approach to delta source target package derived from christian murray’s interrogation and confirmed by raven-3 isr exfil call nightstar after delta and return to base with darkhorse in custody situation command obtained an actionable package from the interrogation of christian murray , a former skell employee who defected to sentinel and enabled a human-trafficking ring. his reporting identified both site locations and two hvts: one running a captured construction site and another commanding the whole operation. the cell is using multiple maritime routes and the ancient harbor to move hostages in and out of the area. innocent workers are being held for ransom and forced labor, and at least five have already been executed after resisting or trying to escape. raven-3 isr confirms hostages are present at the target sites and the situation is degrading fast. execution phase 1 haho under darkness, move on foot through alpha, bravo, and charlie, and keep the approach violent and decisive once contact is made. phase 2 capture warlock at the construction site, hand him off at site whiskey bravo 2, then clear the harbor qrf and use the rhib to reach delta. phase 3 capture darkhorse at the oceanic power plant, secure the remaining workers, and call nightstar for extraction. primary risk this is an active hostage-labor and smuggling network with ongoing executions. delay favors the traffickers and increases the chance of additional deaths or maritime breakout. intermediate hvt warlock primary hvt darkhorse alpha checkpoint weasel echo secure and sweep the checkpoint for intelligence tied to the trafficking routes and local detention picture. bravo construction site neutralize all hostiles except the site leader, capture hvt warlock, and establish contact with guardian 1 for hostage relocation. deliver warlock to site whiskey bravo 2 just north of the site for roleplayed handoff to another interrogation team. charlie ancient harbor neutralize the enemy qrf stationed at the harbor, gather any maritime-route intelligence, and seize the rhib for movement to delta. delta oceanic power plant locate and capture hvt darkhorse, secure the rest of the plant, and coordinate with guardian 2 to relocate the workers. call nightstar for extraction and rtb with darkhorse once the site is stable. whaler\'s bay full-display tacmap reference for the haho insertion, the trafficking-site sequence through alpha to delta, and the final nightstar extraction route.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-harrier%20%5B1273805766960218186%5D.html', label: 'op-harrier', searchLabel: 'op harrier', text: 'operation harrier operation harrier team harrier will haho into restricted area 01 to recapture camp fox, rescue allied specialist mayfly, capture enemy jtac hopper alive at the prototype workshop, and strip control station fox 02 of its ugv-support role so rebels can hold the northern buffer. brief south cape station, 2103 hours insertion after-sundown haho infil to the rendezvous point, followed by foot movement to all targets priority rescue mayfly, capture hopper, free civilians, and establish the mountain buffer zone exfil patrol to hlz juno and call novar-1 for return to south cape station with the apprehended hvt situation sentinel is pushing into the mountain range through a three-pronged posture centered on camp fox , the prototype workshop , and control station fox 02 . camp fox is the immediate problem, where allied weapons specialist mayfly was captured while investigating the site. retaking it will allow rebel forces to establish a forward operating base on the ridge line. to the east, the prototype workshop holds both civilians and hvt hopper , an enemy jtac wanted for interrogation to prevent upcoming strikes. control station fox 02 functions as a ugv repair and support node, so reclaiming it is necessary to break hostile pressure on the northern region and give local rebels room to fight back. execution phase 1 haho to the rendezvous point before sundown ends, move on foot, and preserve surprise across the entire chain. phase 2 recapture camp fox first, then pivot to the prototype workshop for hvt capture and civilian liberation. phase 3 clear the ugv maintenance node, patrol to hlz juno, and hand control of the cleared sites to local assets on standby. operational need the mission is about creating a defensible northern buffer. if these three sites stay in hostile hands, rebels cannot stabilize the mountain corridor. rescue target mayfly capture target hopper alpha camp fox secure the camp, establish communication with bandit-1, and rescue mayfly. armaros isr 1441 identified 21 hostile personnel in the area. bravo prototype workshop capture hvt hopper alive, liberate the civilians on site, and establish communication with bandit-2. armaros isr 1456 identified 12 hostile personnel in the target zone. charlie control station fox 02 eliminate hostile squads, collect ugv metric data at the maintenance station, and establish communication with bandit-3. armaros isr 1509 identified 8 hostile personnel at the site. restricted area 01 full-display tacmap reference for the haho approach, the three target sites, and the final movement to hlz juno for novar-1 pickup.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-highlander%20%5B1174047489943416832%5D.html', label: 'op-highlander', searchLabel: 'op highlander', text: 'operation highlander operation highlander fireteam avalanche will haho into silent mountain to stop an anthrax contamination plot against the eastern water supply, capture bodark-linked hvt mongoose alive, rescue bandit 2-6 before handoff and execution, and hold the final site as a new fob for follow-on interrogation and control. mode conquest / bodark story context with outcast-interference risk if progress is not reset insertion sundown helicopter infil from carrick ridge bivouac followed by high-altitude haho jump cbrn note gas masks are mandatory at the pumping station due to extreme anthrax volatility finish establish a fob at outpost black tiger and begin voronin interrogation with charlie team support situation a rogue sentinel terror cell working with the bodarks has seized silent mountain’s pumping station , the primary water source for the eastern farmlands and population. their intent is to contaminate the system with anthrax , creating a mass threat to wildlife, crops, and civilians. parallel exploitation opportunities exist across the ao. the cell leadership is holding a clandestine underground meeting at the battery farm , where hvt mongoose (alexei voronin), the unit’s weapons specialist, can be captured. at the same time, bandit 2-6 is being held at outpost black tiger , with sigint indicating an imminent handoff to the bodarks for execution during a future broadcast. execution phase 1 haho to the ip in white kits, reach op delta, and determine whether any outcast scouts survived the aamon drone strike. phase 2 secure the pumping station with gas masks on, contain the anthrax package, and call the decon team once the site is safe. phase 3 capture voronin alive at the underground battery farm, then assault black tiger, free bandit 2-6, and convert the position into the new fob. primary hazard the pumping-station threat is biological, not just tactical. if containment fails, the fallout hits water, agriculture, and civilian population centers across the eastern region. capture target mongoose / alexei voronin rescue target bandit 2-6 alpha op delta reach the observation point, search for any surviving outcast scouts, and destroy the hostile land-drone threat in the area. bravo pumping station approach in gas masks, neutralize the hostile force, and secure the anthrax package without allowing contamination to spread. call the decon team once the site is fully under control. charlie underground battery farm raid the underground meeting site, capture mongoose alive, and keep him with the team for the final move. delta outpost black tiger assault the outpost, eliminate the wolves detachment, and free bandit 2-6 before the bodark transfer can happen. remain on site to establish the fob and begin voronin’s interrogation with charlie team assistance. tacmap full-display route reference for the haho insertion, op delta, the silent mountain pumping-station strike, the underground battery farm hit, and the final black tiger assault.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-jaguar%20%5B1242908777741811824%5D.html', label: 'op-jaguar', searchLabel: 'op jaguar', text: 'operation jaguar operation jaguar fireteam jaguar will strike across the seal islands to stop sentinel’s illicit missile and nv-optics transfer to al-hayat, kill the off-site anti-air commander locksmith, seize his portable authentication module, exploit the battery’s comms network, and destroy the outbound weapons package before it leaves auroa. brief south cape station, 2000 hours insertion 2011 departure, land southeast of target, then use local watercraft to reach the island ip cargo 23 javelin missiles and multiple nv optics delivered to emelius port for probable transfer to al-hayat finish destroy the target package, retain acquired opinfo, and rtb when the chain is complete situation isr confirmed that an lcu delivered 23 javelin missiles and multiple nv optics to emelius port. sources assess that the cargo is intended for al-hayat , the middle eastern terror group currently operating against us allies in darb khandaq. sentinel is now directly tied to the transfer chain. before the weapons package can be demolished, the team must exploit a time-sensitive target of opportunity. sigint fixed the location of the anti-air commander locksmith , currently holding an off-site meeting on entry island. his portable authentication module is required to decrypt data in the anti-aircraft battery comms building and expose sentinel’s offshore clients and operational picture. execution phase 1 land southeast of the target area, move by watercraft to the forested ip, and recon the hvt meeting site before the strike. phase 2 kill locksmith, seize the pam, then pivot by watercraft to the anti-aircraft battery for prisoner recovery and comms exploitation. phase 3 continue on foot to the listening-post objective and the dockside weapons package, then destroy the shipment and rtb. primary risk if the weapons package moves, sentinel succeeds in shipping anti-armor missiles and night-fighting gear to an active terror client outside auroa. the demolition window is the decisive point. hvt locksmith key device portable authentication module alpha entry island eliminate hvt codename locksmith along with his security detail. recover the portable authentication module for downstream decryption. bravo anti-aircraft battery secure the battery, rescue the allied prisoner, and unlock the comms-building workstation. download all enemy opinfo before leaving the site. charlie checkpoint shark bravo clear the checkpoint and plant a comint device to create a live listening post if the enemy reoccupies it. delta emelius port package secure the dockside area and identify the outbound target package. conduct controlled demolition on any stack of boxes at the dock linked to the transfer. seal islands ao full-display route reference for the lz, the island hvt strike, the anti-aircraft battery exploitation, and the final demolition push at emelius port.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-kappa%20%5B1239895003057229865%5D.html', label: 'op-kappa', searchLabel: 'op kappa', text: 'operation kappa operation kappa qrf triton will helocast into dolphin bay and drive a rapid canal-and-street assault across liberty city to break sentinel’s attack on diplomatic and skell personnel, secure the port and airport staging nodes, and recover intelligence on thirteen abducted personnel before they vanish deeper into the ao. brief south cape station, 2100 hours insertion 2140 little bird deployment with helocast into dolphin bay crisis seven dead, thirteen missing, and sentinel using liberty port and liberty airport as active staging grounds finish deliver the recovered helicopter to south cape station and analyze intel with bandit 3 situation sentinel has launched a coordinated strike on liberty city , targeting diplomatic personnel and skell tech employees. seven are confirmed dead and thirteen more are missing. intelligence indicates the enemy seized liberty port and liberty airport as staging areas to move captives to an unknown destination. the city fight is fluid and fast-moving. the team has to destroy immediate threats, gather intelligence on the abducted personnel, and stay ready to exploit any targets of opportunity that appear while crossing the ao. execution phase 1 helocast into dolphin bay, secure liberty port, and establish the first intel picture from the enemy toc. phase 2 use the canal west of the port to move into the city unseen and maintain tempo instead of slow building-by-building clearance. phase 3 push from winter lake to auroa parliament and liberty airport, recapture the final site, then return the helicopter for exploitation with bandit 3. tempo speed matters more than deep room-by-room clearing. the mission is built around fast exterior dominance and rapid threat collapse to stop more killings and abductions. access route dolphin bay canal approach follow-on this story continues in op-wandering-wraith , where one of the men behind the attack is captured. alpha liberty port secure the port and exploit the enemy tactical operations center for intelligence on the abducted personnel network. bravo winter lake shopping street use the canal west of the port to enter the city undetected and secure the winter lake commercial sector. seize any viable targets of opportunity during the push. charlie auroa parliament establish control over the outer ring and the central interior of the parliament complex. delta liberty airport recapture the airport, collapse the final staging node, and secure whatever transport or detention intel remains on site. when the chain is complete, fly the helicopter back to south cape station for analysis with bandit 3. operation path full-display route reference for the dolphin bay insertion, canal entry, liberty city assault progression, and the airport finish before rtb.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-killswitch%20%5B1191460355466080296%5D.html', label: 'op-killswitch', searchLabel: 'op killswitch', text: 'operation killswitch operation killswitch team killswitch will halo into lake country to steal the dta reset module, convert the local behemoth network to friendly control through brn-6 at harper lake, and flip sentinel’s own autonomous heavy drones into a regional force multiplier for liberation operations. brief erewhon hq, after-sundown launch insertion halo drop from above 1000 meters into lake country airspace payload recover dta reset instructions and upload them to brn-6 at harper lake effect convert all behemoths in the area to friendly target-acquisition behavior situation echelon and jace skell identified a route to seize control of the behemoth drone layer in central eastern auroa. the critical path runs through the drones target acquisition program hosted at the skell security assembly hall in lake country, where a hidden module contains the instructions needed to reset behemoth target-acquisition behavior. only top-tier skell credentials can access that system. if the team can steal the correct credentials, download the reset package, and upload it at the brn-6 relay in harper lake , the behemoths across the region will switch from hostile control to friendly alignment and materially shift the local balance against sentinel. execution phase 1 halo into lake country after dark and infiltrate skell estate to acquire c1 access credentials. phase 2 clear drone station w121 to block qrf interference, then enter assembly hall and pull the dta package with the recovered rfid access. phase 3 move to harper lake, defeat the behemoth controlling the relay network, upload the reset module to brn-6, confirm remote execution, and call extraction. access constraint the whole mission hinges on credential theft. without the c1 rfid path, the dta module cannot be reached and the behemoth conversion never happens. office code wdt2gs relay target brn-6, harper lake alpha skell estate infiltrate the office, bypass local computer security, and use the code path to reach the credential store. transfer c1 credentials onto an rfid card for the downstream access chain. bravo drone station w121 neutralize the hostile presence to remove qrf interference from the assembly hall and harper lake phases. charlie assembly hall access the encrypted computer, authenticate with the rfid credentials, and download the dta program. delta harper lake kill the behemoth controlling the network and install the dta package on brn-6. confirm remote execution so the regional behemoths flip to friendly status. echo extraction initiate the extraction request once the network conversion is verified.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-kobold%20%5B1237392300489838692%5D.html', label: 'op-kobold', searchLabel: 'op kobold', text: 'operation kobold operation kobold qrf hazard will halo into wild coast to stop an imminent contamination and bombing plot against liberty city, eliminate the forward qrf screen, destroy the explosives vehicle at the toxic storage depot, and seize the engine r&d center to break enemy opsec and stand up a new fob. brief erewhon hq, 2008 hours insertion 2045 halo deployment to the lz with foot movement across all objectives threat heavy-metal contamination attempt on the parliament water supply plus a planned liberty port bombing finish establish a fob and observation post at engine r&d center after server breach and reinforcements linkup situation jsoc analysts and an undercover cia maintenance source produced an actionable package on an enemy cell operating out of the toxic storage depot in mount hodgson. reaper 2 confirmed hostile forces are loading barrels of heavy-metal concentrate for an imminent strike designed to contaminate the auroa parliament water supply and poison senior diplomats. the same plot includes a follow-on bombing at liberty port intended to disguise both attacks as accidents. before the depot can be hit, the nearby enemy qrf at drone station w031 must be silently removed. the final target is the engine r&d center , currently serving as the hostile toc in wild coast. execution phase 1 halo to the lz from erewhon and patrol on foot to alpha for a quiet takedown of the qrf screen. phase 2 secure the toxic storage depot, isolate the explosives vehicle, and execute controlled demolition before the contamination or bombing plan can launch. phase 3 seize engine r&d center, breach the servers, call in reinforcements, and convert the site into the new fob and observation post. strategic risk this is a dual-event attack package. if the depot is not hit in time, the enemy can contaminate a diplomatic water supply and follow with a liberty port blast designed to mask attribution. priority threat toxic storage depot end state break the plot, breach hostile opsec, and hold the engine r&d center as a forward surveillance node. alpha drone station w031 quietly eliminate the enemy qrf before it can reinforce the depot or compromise the patrol route. bravo toxic storage depot secure the depot and stop the contamination package from moving toward liberty city. move the explosives-bearing vehicle off site and conduct controlled demolition. charlie engine r&d center secure the center, breach the servers, and exploit the enemy toc for follow-on intelligence. call in reinforcements and establish the new fob and observation post here. wild coast ao full-display tacmap reference for the halo lz, the qrf takedown at drone station w031, the toxic storage depot strike, and the final seizure of engine r&d center.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-lantern%20%5B1237128602319982714%5D.html', label: 'op-lantern', searchLabel: 'op lantern', text: 'operation lantern operation lantern qrf crazyhorse will halo into new argyll to break sentinel’s hold on the regional food-supply chain, destroy explosive and narcotics shipments, secure endangered civilians, and recover undercover cia driver kestrel from a likely blown-cover situation at the meal packaging center. brief erewhon hq, 1917 hours insertion helicopter deployment at 2000 with halo insertion to the designated lz priority rescue kestrel, secure civilians, and eliminate the truck-borne explosives and narcotics flow specialist demolition expert attached for controlled vehicle and shipment destruction situation sentinel squads have seized key food-supply infrastructure across new argyll , disrupting civilian logistics and coinciding with the disappearance of multiple civilians, mostly female skell technology employees. apex 2 also observed hostile supply trucks moving explosives and narcotics through the same chain. cia asset kestrel , operating undercover as a driver, triggered a sarsat beacon at the meal packaging center, indicating either a blown cover or an active hostage situation. the mission is to clear the network, destroy the hostile shipments, rescue the asset, and recover any intelligence tied to the missing civilians. execution insertion depart hq at 2000 by helicopter, halo to the lz, and move fast into the supply-chain nodes before patrols can reposition. assault conduct a surgical clearance at each site with civilian safety as a standing priority while isolating and exploiting the hostile truck movement. finish conclude at summers homestead with the allied point of contact to exploit intelligence and plan the follow-on move. immediate risk kestrel’s beacon means the meal packaging center can no longer be treated as a routine site sweep. charlie is a rescue problem first and a demolition problem second. primary asset kestrel end state break the supply chain, destroy the hostile trucks, and leave with actionable intel on the missing civilians. alpha new argyll winery secure the winery and clear the grounds around the truck staging area. move the supply trucks off the premises and destroy them with c4. bravo cold storage center secure the storage site and keep every civilian on the property alive. conduct a full site exploitation pass before movement to charlie. charlie meal packaging center secure the center, locate cia asset kestrel, and resolve the likely hostage or blown-cover situation. move the supply trucks away from the buildings and execute controlled demolition. delta summers homestead reach the homestead and link up with the allied point of contact for intelligence review. end the operation at the homestead and prepare the next move from the recovered material. new argyll / fen bog border region full-display tacmap reference for the halo insertion, the three-site assault path, and the final movement to summers homestead for exploitation and operation closeout.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-magician%20%5B1167267837606375474%5D.html', label: 'op-magician', searchLabel: 'op magician', text: 'operation magician operation magician asf tier 1 elements will infil by helocast near wind farm w02, dismantle the enemy control chain across four linked sites, protect civilians, kill christopher becker on sight, and capture michael harris alive despite his concealed suicide vest and no-firearms capture requirement. brief asf hq, 1900-hour launch window insertion helicopter combat-diver helocast at the maritime ip near wind farm w02 threat enemy comms hubs, weapon trafficking, drone control nodes, and two separate hvt problems finish rtb once all four sites are secured and harris is extracted for interrogation situation the ao contains multiple hostile control points spread across wind farm w02 , whalers bay airfield , aconite station , and drone station w061 . intelligence indicates those sites support enemy communications, weapons movement, and drone-control activity that threatens ongoing liberation efforts in the region. two hvts are tied to the chain. christopher becker is an immediate threat to civilians and sits at the top of the kill list. michael harris holds high-value logistics and supply-route intelligence, but he is fanatically unstable and known to wear a concealed s-vest to prevent capture. execution phase 1 depart hq at 1900, helocast near wind farm w02, and push in by cautious amphibious approach for the opening hit. phase 2 collapse the enemy chain in sequence from alpha through delta while preserving civilian safety and securing any exploitable materiel. phase 3 kill becker on sight, then conduct a controlled no-firearms apprehension on harris so eod can clear the vest and extract him alive. capture constraint harris must be taken without any firearms discharge . the team needs a close-control takedown, immediate eod handling, and disciplined spacing to avoid a vest detonation event. kill target christopher becker capture target michael harris alpha wind farm w02 secure the site, protect civilian workers, and strip the qrf before it can reinforce the airfield. disable enemy communications equipment during the clearance. bravo whalers bay airfield capture the airfield, secure weapon caches, and radio in fireteam mongoose to hold the perimeter. christopher becker is believed to be hiding here and is to be eliminated on sight. charlie aconite station infiltrate the station and extract any intelligence tied to possible nerve-agent work in the barricaded labs. equip hazmat ppe, including gas masks, before the breach. delta drone station w061 disable the drone systems to stop hostile air support against friendly forces down south. capture harris alive, clear the s-vest threat, and extract him back to hq for questioning. operational tacmap full-display ao reference for the helocast insertion, the four-target progression from wind farm w02 through drone station w061, and the final return-to-base route after harris is secured.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-morpheus%20%5B1233037653511766027%5D.html', label: 'op-morpheus', searchLabel: 'op morpheus', text: 'operation morpheus operation morpheus fireteam morpheus will isolate darkwood island ahead of the final skell foundation campus assault by blacking out the local comms net, preserving the infrastructure with lr-emps, and capturing hvt crown before he can escape the anchorage arm server station. brief twin islands, 2042 hours insertion little bird infil from twin islands bivouac to a beach lz one klick north of alpha specialty est specialist carrying lr-emps to disable the network without destroying allied-use infrastructure finish extract team and hvt to safehouse charlie november 2 for interrogation and follow-on tasking situation sentinel has seized control of central darkwood island and is using critical skell infrastructure to manage legion drone swarms and ugv control across the area. before the final push to retake the occupied skell foundation campus, the local communications net has to be neutralized so the enemy loses isr, drone coordination, and remote support. the operation also presents a capture opportunity on hvt crown , a former nsa cryptographer now working with sentinel near anchorage arm. his specialization in encryption and communications protocols makes him a high-value intelligence target for broader enemy-network exploitation across auroa. execution phase 1 launch at 2100 by little bird, land at the coastal lz north of alpha, and move in with black kits to keep the approach low-signature. phase 2 shut down the comms chain with lr-emps, preserving infrastructure for allied reuse while stripping sentinel of network control. phase 3 capture crown alive if possible, extract by air to charlie november 2, and report to toc for the next step in the campus campaign. mission focus the point is not simple destruction. the team is expected to render the ao comms architecture inoperative while leaving skell systems recoverable for allied control after the island is retaken. hvt crown civilian risk possible civilians under duress at every site. pid discipline stays tight throughout the chain. alpha ai experimental center secure the complex and clear the grounds around the relay layout. deactivate all four main antenna relays with emps. bravo campus relay station secure the relay station and shut down all comms equipment on site. bag any portable electronic equipment before moving on. charlie server station breach the server room and make sure the network goes dark across the area. apprehend hvt crown before he can leave the location. delta charlie november 2 following jackpot, bring the pilot in and extract the team plus hvt to the safehouse. operation concludes at the safehouse with interrogation and a report to toc for further directives. cape north / darkwood island tacmap full-display ao reference for twin islands bivouac, the coastal lz, alpha through delta, and the final extraction route into charlie november 2.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-neptune-spear%20%5B1231244746471637074%5D.html', label: 'op-neptune-spear', searchLabel: 'op neptune spear', text: 'operation neptune spear operation neptune spear team neptune will infil fen bog by helocast, seize a rhib at the ancient village, and clear a four-site chain across sinking country to recover skell technology classified report 681, protect cia asset pilgrim, and expose the main azrael uav base before more rebel positions are hit. brief erewhon hq, 2031 hours insertion helocast to grid 68372, swim to alpha, then transition to captured rhib movement priority recover report 681 and keep pilgrim plus all civilians alive finish sweep delta, exploit all intel, and extract by lightning 1-5 situation enemy uav strikes have already inflicted heavy casualties on allied rebel positions. socom analysts working with undercover cia operative pilgrim identified three fen bog and sinking country locations tied to the main azrael uav drone base. the decisive lead is skell technology classified report 681 , a report now moving between those sites and likely containing the base location. pilgrim confirmed the document exists and secured a photo of it, but could not lift it without blowing his cover. he is expected at drone station w051 wearing a high-visibility vest to aid pid during the bravo clearance. the mission now is to clear the entire chain, recover the report wherever it surfaces, and prevent further uav strikes by exposing the launch site. execution insertion depart erewhon at 2100, helocast six hundred meters southeast of alpha, and swim into the ancient village for the initial foothold. mobility shift seize the rhib at the dock and use it as the primary movement platform between bravo, charlie, and delta. rules move silently and fast under nighttime cover, keep pilgrim and civilians safe, and maintain tight pid discipline before every shot. mission focus the report is the center of gravity. any target location may be holding it temporarily, so each site requires a full search and exploitation pass before movement continues. pid challenge panther pid response apex follow-on the storyline continues in op-crusader . neptune spear functions as part one of that linked deployment sequence. alpha ancient village complete the swim in from the helocast point and secure the village dock area. obtain the rhib and prepare the waterborne push to bravo. bravo drone station w051 secure the station, link up with pilgrim, and preserve all civilians on site. search aggressively for report 681 while maintaining strict positive id. charlie control station tiger 02 investigate the observed shipment activity and clear the control site. exploit any documentation, manifests, or transit evidence tied to the report. delta bunker edgehod south secure the island, sweep for intelligence, and expect elevated resistance. possible hvt, gunship presence, and targets of opportunity are greenlit before extraction. fen bog / sinking country tacmap full-display ao reference for the helocast swim lane, rhib pickup, target sequence, and final island sweep before calling lightning 1-5 for extraction.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-neptune-wrath%20%5B1230504126220206233%5D.html', label: 'op-neptune-wrath', searchLabel: 'op neptune wrath', text: 'operation neptune wrath operation neptune wrath qrf neptune will launch from south cape station by rhib to stop the final fielding cycle of two unmanned sedna submarines before they are armed with slbms. the operation runs in three phases: seize control of the submarines at the naval base, kill the submarine commander at the airfield, and demolish the torpedo and missile stockpile at shark base. brief south cape station, 2057 hours insertion rhib combat-diver deployment with demolition and communications specialists threat two unmanned sedna submarines en route to slbm arming at shark base finish rtb south cape station once subs are diverted and ordnance is destroyed situation operative jasper has confirmed that the wolves are entering the final exercise cycle for the sedna submarines , previously spotted in the bering sea near alaska. the two remote-controlled craft are heavily modified akula-platform derivatives capable of carrying ballistic missiles with reach into the continental united states. imint shows the submarines are still unarmed and currently 43 klicks south of auroa, moving slowly toward shark base for slbm loading. the narrow window is now: seize the control chain before the boats are armed, kill the commander who just arrived in theater, and destroy the stored submarine ordnance before the system goes live. execution phase 1 launch from south cape station by rhib, hit the sentinel corp. naval base, secure the control terminal in the communications building, and redirect the submarines to grid 58039 for the poseidon recovery team. phase 2 shift by rhib to nbaa, eliminate the submarine commander and his security detail, and reopen the airfield for local allied rebel control. phase 3 assault shark base, conduct exploitation, and destroy every torpedo and ballistic missile staged for the sedna boats with c4 before they can be loaded. primary window the boats are still unarmed. once shark base completes the slbm integration, the threat profile changes from recoverable to strategic launch risk. alpha must happen fast enough to keep poseidon in play. mobility plan the rhib remains the primary transportation method for the full operation. the team should think in terms of a continuous maritime strike chain, not disconnected inland raids. shark base note shark base is the decisive denial point. if the team gets lost or slow inside the facility, the last phase drags and the whole strategic window narrows. internal familiarity matters more here than raw speed. objectives alpha sentinel corp. naval base secure the base, gather intelligence, access the submarine control terminal, redirect the sedna boats to grid 58039, and notify poseidon for recovery. bravo naval base auroa airfield kill the submarine commander and his security detail after their helicopter arrival, then hand the airfield back to the local allied rebel element. charlie shark base secure the base, exploit the site, and destroy every torpedo and ballistic missile intended for the submarines using c4. support references tacmap south cape station launch reference with the rhib route and all three objective areas: the sentinel corp. naval base, naval base auroa airfield, and shark base.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-noxious-snare%20%5B1235971720599310457%5D.html', label: 'op-noxious-snare', searchLabel: 'op noxious snare', text: 'operation noxious snare operation noxious snare qrf venom is tasked with breaking a sentinel abduction and experimentation chain tied to auroa hospital. the team must secure vip skull before he breaks under torture, then pivot into a follow-on search for dr. bloom and the remaining abductees by exploiting the intel trail through south cape station and camp viper. brief erewhon hq, 2019 hours launch 2105 little bird departure, black kits, pilot retained for all lifts immediate priority secure auroa hospital and recover skull from the l3 lab alive finish camp viper exploited, then rtb erewhon hq for debrief with schulz situation joint jsoc and cia reporting has clarified the trafficking pattern on auroa: sentinel is conducting forced medical experiments on many of the civilians it kidnaps. kyle and emmet benton, scouts working for schulz, were taken several days ago. kyle escaped, but emmet, codenamed skull , remains held in the auroa hospital l3 laboratory. command assesses that skull may reveal critical resistance intelligence under torture if left in place. in parallel, sigint indicates other abductees, including hospital director dr. bloom, are being moved deeper into sentinel custody, likely toward a black-site network elsewhere on auroa. execution phase 1 after the schulz brief, fly straight to auroa hospital and clear the entire site with strict pid before making contact with skull in the l3 laboratory. phase 2 do not return to erewhon after the rescue. shift immediately to south cape station, meet ito, and pivot onto the second objective chain tied to dr. bloom and the other abductees. phase 3 reactivate the ito replay flow, resupply at the bivouac, deploy at dusk, investigate camp viper, exploit any live intelligence, and return to erewhon hq for final debrief. pid requirement the hospital assault sits inside a dense civilian environment. target identification discipline is non-negotiable; the site has to be fully secured before the team interacts with skull. technical note objective markers and mission reminders should stay enabled for the team to preserve the interactive chain and maintain timing and contact clarity during the replay-driven segments. mission end state skull recovered, south cape intelligence chain activated, camp viper investigated, and the trafficking network pushed toward a usable location fix for dr. bloom and the remaining captives. objectives alpha auroa hospital secure the hospital, prevent further abductions or civilian casualties, and only after the site is clear make contact with vip skull in the l3 laboratory. bravo south cape station meet ito, shift onto the second intelligence chain, and refresh the operational picture on dr. bloom and the missing abductees without breaking mission tempo. charlie camp viper investigate the camp immediately on the back of the ito handoff, exploit every actionable clue, and close the operation only after the new intel has been pulled and reported. support references' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-overcrank%20%5B1235602457854476412%5D.html', label: 'op-overcrank', searchLabel: 'op overcrank', text: 'operation overcrank operation overcrank mitchell has confirmed that stone has aligned with raven\'s rock and is preparing operation kingmaker, a chemical-weapons and drone strike campaign aimed at the united states. with no meaningful backup coming, the task force must dismantle raven\'s rock leadership node by node, strip their weapons caches, and close in on stone through a distributed hvt-hunt across auroa. brief erewhon hq, 1400 hours structure episode 3 mission-board campaign with sequential target packages mission logic neutralize raven\'s rock leadership, destroy caches, isolate stone end state operation kingmaker broken at the command level before execution situation fsb reporting and mitchell\'s relay make the threat explicit: stone has tied sentinel\'s remaining power to russian ultra-nationalist actors inside raven\'s rock . imint suggests multiple chemical-weapon stockpiles are already in place and that the network intends to coordinate a large-scale drone strike against the u.s. congressional scrutiny has effectively cut off meaningful support, so the burden shifts to direct action. the only workable path is decapitation: remove the specialists and command staff driving the operation, tear out their logistical and weapons backbone, and leave stone exposed. execution phase 1 open the objective chain through the episode 3 board and launch the selected mission replay to receive the in-world tasking for that target package. phase 2 hunt each raven\'s rock specialist in their assigned ao, disrupt their domain expertise at the source, and remove supporting caches or operational nodes tied to that target. phase 3 collapse the leadership ring from manticore through sphinx, then close on atlas, identified as stone, to terminate operation kingmaker at command level. campaign priority this is a distributed kill chain, not a single strike. each target represents a capability pillar inside raven\'s rock, so the value is in dismantling the network in sequence rather than treating the packages as isolated raids. known constraint manticore is assessed to wear an s-vest and must be handled with extreme caution. other packages are conventional hvt removals, but all of them feed the same stone end-state. terminal target atlas is stone. humint ties him directly to executions, martial-law enforcement on auroa, and the command decision to partner with raven\'s rock after walker\'s death. he is the final command node and must be stopped. mission board alpha manticore / smugglers cove stepan belevitch. drone and logistics expert. former spetsnaz engineer with deep drone-employment expertise and a paranoia-driven s-vest capture defense. bravo basilisk / new stirling pyotr bukharov. organizational leader and planner. special-operations background, revenge motive, and command-level stewardship of operation kingmaker. charlie oracle / windy islands ivan ivanov. intelligence officer and protocol specialist focused on defeating u.s. defensive logic and coordinating drone operations at policy level. delta harpy / driftwood islets claro gentile. demolitions and drone-attack planner. former marine combat engineer turned wolf founding member with a preference for devastating strike design. echo cyclops / silent mountain boris govoretski. stealth technology specialist focused on camouflage, counter-detection, and defeating u.s. radar and surveillance architecture. foxtrot medusa / restricted area 01 artiom zubkov. chemical-weapons specialist with a history tied to neurotoxin use and a clear preference for unconventional mass-casualty methods. golf kraken / fen bog miroslav semenevitch. submarine-unit commander linked to a yasen-class ssgn and suspected maritime support for gas-drone deployment plans. hotel griffin / wild coast alexei lissitzine. smuggler and ratline architect. former fsb field officer assessed as the network\'s logistics and clandestine-pathway manager. india sphinx / seal islands anthony barkley jr. hitman. former navy seal and walker loyalist willing to die preserving the kingmaker chain of command. juliet atlas / lake country stone. final commander. former u.s. covert operator turned sentinel war-crimes architect and raven\'s rock partner after walker\'s death. support references' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-payday%20%5B1250470093142364221%5D.html', label: 'op-payday', searchLabel: 'op payday', text: 'operation payday operation payday qrf mint will jump into southeast restricted area 01 to break a live weapons deal. the team first wipes the nearby mine-based qrf and interrogates its leader, then destroys the missile stockpile and heavy equipment at burnet ridge, and finally moves on liberty airport if command confirms the buyer\'s location. start south cape station, 2052 brief, 2110 launch insertion overseer haho insertion, black kits, foot movement from the lz priority destroy weapons stockpiles and identify or kill the buyer finish aircraft handoff at whiskey india 7 or rtb south cape station situation eagle 1-3 has fixed a weapons deal at burnet ridge in southeast ra1. isr confirms large quantities of arms and roughly ten surface-to-air missiles staged on-site while the seller waits for an unidentified buyer to arrive. before hitting the deal site, the team must cut down the nearby qrf at russel gold mine and interrogate its leader for details on the transaction. intercepted communications suggest the buyer may have flown in from auckland international airport, so command has airport surveillance active and can cue a fast third phase if confirmed. execution phase 1 jump from overseer, land at the haho lz, and move on foot to russel gold mine to wipe the qrf and interrogate its leader for deal intelligence. phase 2 push to burnet ridge, secure the site, collect all available intelligence, and conduct a controlled demolition of the missile inventory, weapons, and supporting equipment. phase 3 if command confirms the buyer at liberty airport, move immediately to the airfield, neutralize greenback and his detail, secure the airport, and deliver the aircraft package to bandit 1-4 at whiskey india 7. strike focus burnet ridge is the central denial target. the missile stack and all associated weapons equipment must be demolished in a controlled way after site intelligence has been collected. interrogation note the qrf leader at russel gold mine can be roleplayed by a commander or any enemy on-site if a specific leader archetype does not spawn. the point is extracting usable deal intelligence before bravo. end state weapons deal disrupted, greenback neutralized if present, airport secured, and both the plane and helicopter handed off to bandit 1-4 at whiskey india 7 or returned through south cape station. objectives alpha russel gold mine eliminate the qrf, isolate their leader, and interrogate him for actionable details on the burnet ridge weapons deal. bravo burnet ridge secure the deal site, gather all intelligence, and destroy the weapons, equipment, and missile stockpile with controlled demolitions. charlie liberty airport if the buyer is confirmed, neutralize hvt greenback and his detail, secure the airport, and deliver the plane and helicopter to whiskey india 7. support references russel gold mine reference for the opening qrf strike and interrogation site before the team moves on the weapons deal itself. burnet ridge reference for the main weapons-deal target area where the missile cache and heavy equipment are staged for demolition. liberty airport reference for the buyer hit at charlie where greenback and the payment detail can be intercepted if command confirms the airport location. whiskey india 7 landing and handoff reference for the aircraft package transfer to bandit 1-4 at the end of the airport phase. phase one tacmap restricted area 01 reference for the haho insertion, russel gold mine strike, and the follow-on movement into burnet ridge. phase two tacmap liberty reference for the airport hit, buyer neutralization, and aircraft delivery route to whiskey india 7.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-red-blanket%20%5B1193325640200491208%5D.html', label: 'op-red-blanket', searchLabel: 'op red blanket', text: 'operation red blanket operation red blanket fireteam clearwater will haho into lake country to break a sentinel interrogation dragnet, rescue cia operative lantern at two lakes residences, and then secure two contested skell cyber sites before enemy forces can seize or exfiltrate the encrypted data stored there. launch erewhon hq after sundown insertion haho jump to site hotel one, then foot movement priority protect lantern, preserve cybint, and deny sentinel access finish extraction from skell security operations after allied handoff situation an undercover cia operative, codenamed lantern , has been trapped at two lakes residences after a sentinel detachment sealed the area and began interrogations to identify whoever has been leaking troop movements to the rebels. the immediate opening task is to break that cordon, protect the operative, and get him equipped for independent extraction to lima romeo 2. after the rescue, the mission pivots into a cybint denial operation. both the maintenance area and skell security operations hold highly sensitive aes-encrypted data that fell into opfor hands earlier in the day. the team carries the st decryption key and must secure both access points long enough to back up the data and hand the sites to allied rebels. execution phase 1 haho into site hotel one, move on foot to two lakes residences, and clear the interrogation zone before sentinel can compromise or lift lantern. phase 2 issue lantern a kit and let him extract independently, then push to the maintenance area and back up all uav flight data from the hangar access point before calling in hydro to hold the site. phase 3 seize skell security operations, obtain rfid access to the server room on the south building\'s top floor, complete the data backup, hand security to liquid, and extract from the compound. primary sensitivity the cybint at bravo and charlie cannot be allowed to fall fully into enemy hands. site control matters, but the mission-critical action is reaching the access points, backing up the data, and preserving custody until command can assess it. access constraint charlie is partially locked down. the server room sits on the top floor of the south building and requires rfid access sourced from personnel on-site before the backup can be completed. optional extension if command wants the operation extended, intel recovered at charlie can point to sentinel lieutenant alexander peterson meeting at the skell security r&d center east of the haho lz. that branch becomes a live-capture follow-on, not part of the base completion state. objectives alpha two lakes residences secure the area, identify lantern among the civilians, rescue him from the sentinel sweep, and provide the kit he needs for extraction to lima romeo 2. bravo maintenance area reach the hangar access point, back up all uav flight data, and radio in rebel element hydro to assume compound security after the data pull. charlie skell security operations gain rfid access, reach the locked server room on the south building\'s top floor, back up the sensitive data, and hand the compound over to liquid before extraction. support references two lakes residences reference for the opening rescue zone where lantern is hidden among civilians under sentinel interrogation pressure. maintenance area reference for the bravo compound and the main access route toward the hangar data-recovery point. hangar access point close reference for the bravo access point used to back up the uav flight data before calling in hydro. skell security operations reference for the charlie site, including the south-building approach needed to reach the locked server room and complete the final backup. tacmap rundown full-area route reference for the haho insertion, the two lakes rescue, the maintenance area data pull, and the skell security operations finish and extraction point.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-red-dawn%20%5B1175836735452741632%5D.html', label: 'op-red-dawn', searchLabel: 'op red dawn', text: 'operation red dawn operation red dawn a sentinel cell led by the butcher has seized the oceanic power plant on petrel island and is preparing an attack against outcast leadership. the team will infiltrate by sea, capture the hvt at the plant, then use his retinal id to access the whalers bay workshop and find or neutralize the bomb before it can be launched. launch rally point leviathan with watercraft insertion approach sea infil to alpha, then pipeline advance into the compound primary action capture the butcher and stop the bombing plot at whalers bay finish bomb neutralized and full rtb to hq after site security situation at 0600 utc, a sentinel terrorist cell led by the butcher seized the oceanic power plant on petrel island. current intelligence ties the takeover to a broader plot targeting outcast leader haruhi ito and a bombing against outcast headquarters. the ground truth still has to be confirmed on-site. the butcher is the key to the next layer of the operation: his detention provides both intelligence on the attack plan and the retinal access required to open the workshop at whalers bay airfield. execution phase 1 secure a watercraft near leviathan island bivouac, move by sea toward alpha, and infiltrate the power-plant compound by following the pipeline into the target area. phase 2 secure the hvt and the site, then use the on-site helicopter to move the butcher to whalers bay airfield for the second half of the operation. phase 3 open the workshop with retinal id, locate the explosive device, and either conduct on-site eod if it is still unarmed or move the aircraft out to sea if the bomb is already mounted and live. bomb logic if the device is inside the workshop and not yet armed, eod can handle it on-site. if the workshop is clear and the bomb is mounted on an aircraft, it is treated as already armed and must be flown out and neutralized at sea. hvt note the game does not always spawn a commander near the construction site. if needed, any enemy around that area can be roleplayed as the butcher for the capture and retinal-id sequence. mission end state the butcher is secured, the whalers bay access chain is exploited, the bomb is identified and safely neutralized, and the team returns to hq with the threat fully shut down. objectives alpha oceanic power plant reach the site from the sea, infiltrate along the pipeline, secure the compound, and capture the butcher near the construction area before lifting out by helicopter. bravo whalers bay airfield use the hvt\'s retinal id to open the workshop, search for the bomb, then clear the airstrip and aircraft if the device has already been moved. support references alpha ip and overview reference for the sea approach and the pipeline-fed infiltration route into the oceanic power plant compound. alpha main compound reference for the butcher\'s patrol area near the construction site and the helicopter used for onward transport to bravo. bravo airfield search reference for the likely bomb locations at whalers bay: either inside the workshop or mounted on an aircraft at the strip. workshop access reference for the retinal-id workshop entry point that gates the first bomb-search branch at bravo. tacmap rundown full channels and whalers bay reference showing the sea approach, the petrel island power-plant target, the whalers bay follow-on site, and the overall movement path between alpha and bravo.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-rubedo%20%5B1231577660183023736%5D.html', label: 'op-rubedo', searchLabel: 'op rubedo', text: 'operation rubedo operation rubedo sentinel cells in smugglers cove are moving prisoners for a possible exchange tied to a suspected radiological device codenamed pyramid. qrf rubedo will cut off the trafficking chain, secure civilians at two coastal sites, and capture badger at the spanish fortress before he disappears back into the tunnel network. start erewhon hq, 2007 brief, 2030 launch insertion little bird infil to the dockside lz with lightweight black kits priority civilian protection first, no radio alert before badger is secured finish handoff at safehouse echo 6 and on-site intel exploitation situation sigint indicates sentinel is preparing a major move in northwest smugglers cove: prisoners are being staged for transport off-island in exchange for a device codenamed pyramid , believed to be some form of radiological dispersal weapon. command is pursuing both the trafficking network and the weapons angle, but immediate action is needed to stop more civilians from disappearing. isr has finally fixed hvt badger , sentinel\'s chief weapons specialist, at the spanish fortress. his pattern suggests he has been using an unconfirmed tunnel network to stay off-grid, so this is a narrow capture window. execution phase 1 depart erewhon by little bird, land near the dockside lz, and patrol the coast on foot toward alpha with a light, low-signature footprint. phase 2 secure wind farm w01 and drone station w011 in sequence, protect civilians, and exploit every comms or data node before pushing inland to charlie. phase 3 capture badger at the fortress without alerting the wider network, extract his devices, then relocate to safehouse echo 6 for hvt handoff and immediate on-site analysis. critical control no radio alert can be allowed before badger is in custody. if he is spooked, he will likely vanish into the suspected tunnel system and the strike window will close. hvt handling thermal imagery suggests badger is wearing an explosive s-vest to avoid capture. a hands-on apprehension is required, and an eod specialist must immediately take over once he is restrained. mission end state alpha and bravo stabilized, badger handed off alive at echo 6, all captured electronics exploited on-site, and the final intelligence package reported directly back to hq. objectives alpha wind farm w01 secure the compound, ensure civilian safety, sweep the comms building for intelligence, and patrol onward to bravo. bravo drone station w011 secure the station, assist civilians, gather actionable intelligence, and continue the foot movement toward charlie. charlie spanish fortress capture badger, recover every electronic device on-site, and keep the detention sequence controlled enough for immediate eod management of the vest threat. support references wind farm w01 reference image for the first civilian-protection sweep and the comms-building exploitation point at alpha. drone station w011 reference image for the second compound sweep where civilian protection continues and the team collects follow-on actionable intel. spanish fortress badger capture reference for the close-guard position and the final approach to the hvt before handoff relocation. safehouse echo 6 end-state reference for the badger handoff to bravo team and the on-site intel exploitation station used to close the mission. tacmap rundown full northwest smugglers cove route reference showing the dockside lz, alpha at wind farm w01, bravo at drone station w011, charlie at the spanish fortress, and the final handoff point at safehouse echo 6.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-saber%20%5B1169712957500952728%5D.html', label: 'op-saber', searchLabel: 'op saber', text: 'operation saber operation saber a hostile insurgent cell in mount hodgson is moving to convert regional infrastructure into future chemical-weapons production sites. the team inserts under darkness by overseer, secures four key facilities, removes or captures designated leadership targets, protects civilians, and returns with the recovered enemy helicopter. launch night departure from hq via overseer insertion rapid low-fast drop at the lz near alpha with black kits primary effect break the insurgent industrial foothold before chem production starts finish rtb with the acquired enemy helicopter after site actions situation intelligence indicates an insurgent cell in mount hodgson is actively seizing industrial infrastructure with the long-term intent of pivoting those facilities toward illicit chemical-weapons production. the immediate task is to break that network before the sites can be consolidated and repurposed. civilian workers remain present across several facilities, which makes speed and control equally important. the mission combines direct action, hvt handling, intelligence exploitation, and site denial in a single push across the ao. execution phase 1 approach the ao under darkness from hq aboard overseer, insert near alpha, and lock down the perimeter fast before the cell can scatter or destroy evidence. phase 2 clear the mines, chemical site, and control center while handling hvts according to roe: eliminate rogue, apprehend specter, and capture bagman for air-movement intelligence. phase 3 finish at silent valley mine, protect civilians, exploit intel, move prisoners to the designated abandoned sites, and recover the enemy helicopter for return flight to hq. handling notes hvt identities are roleplay-driven. the nearest marked abandoned sites are the drop-off locations for apprehended prisoners. rogue is kill-on-sight. specter and bagman are capture priorities. civilian priority bald peak mine and silent valley mine both require civilian safety to stay central to the assault. the site seizure only counts if workers survive the contact and remain secured. mission end state infrastructure secured, insurgent chem plans disrupted, intelligence collected, priority detainees delivered, and the recovered helicopter flown back for allied use. objectives alpha bald peak mine secure the facility, keep civilian workers safe, and eliminate rogue, the insurgent recruiter and trainer identified by the dagger tattoo on his neck. bravo chem-extraction complex investigate the complex, apprehend specter, the suspected cell chemist with the scarred left cheek, and deliver him to bravo 2 for interrogation. charlie mining control center secure the control center, capture bagman for air-movement intelligence, move him to bravo 3, and recover the helicopter for friendly reuse after mission completion. delta silent valley mine reclaim the site while prioritizing civilian safety. no fixed hvt is assigned here, but any target of opportunity is greenlit during the final clearance. tacmap rundown full ao reference for the mount hodgson objective chain, including the insertion zone, the four target sites, and the abandonment points used for detainee handoff.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-sifted-lover%20%5B1232290083701260339%5D.html', label: 'op-sifted-lover', searchLabel: 'op sifted lover', text: 'operation sifted lover operation sifted lover fireteam lover deploys from erewhon hq for a halo insertion into restricted area 01 to kill outlaw at the training center without tripping a radio alert. once the hvt is down and the center is secured, the team will roll through fox echo, outpost red fox, and freeman residences to strip intel, destroy drone cargo, free pows, and stop an active civilian roundup. start erewhon hq, 1730 brief, 1905 launch insertion helicopter to halo ip, green kits, foot patrol to target area primary effect kill outlaw and retake the training center as a future rebel fob finish use the on-site helicopter at freeman for extraction after final capture situation thomas blackwell, codename outlaw , serves as the lead instructor shaping enemy fighters at the training center in restricted area 01. he is tied to executions at black sites and labor camps, and is suspected of directing the earlier assault on auroa parliament that killed fifteen civilians. his reputation is part of sentinel\'s recruiting image. removing him damages both leadership credibility and morale, while taking the training center intact gives allied rebels a valuable base for future force development. execution phase 1 deploy from erewhon by helicopter, conduct the halo jump onto the marked ip near the waterfall and swarm launcher, then move on foot to the training center. phase 2 eliminate outlaw quietly, suppress any radio alert, and secure the training center with minimal infrastructure damage to preserve it for later rebel use. phase 3 sweep fox echo, red fox, and freeman in sequence for intel, demolition, pow recovery, and leader capture before extracting via the helicopter on-site at the final objective. priority control the hvt kill at alpha must happen without triggering any radio alert. if the training center goes loud too early, the follow-on objectives in the area risk compromise and loss of initiative. operational gain the training center is not just a kill box. the intent is to hold it with limited structural damage so it can be reused as a primary forward training site for allied rebel forces. end state outlaw eliminated, fox echo exploited, drone crates destroyed, pows freed, freeman civilians protected, local enemy leader captured, and the team extracted by helicopter with actionable ao intelligence. objectives alpha training center take out outlaw, represented on-site by any special enemy, and secure the complex while minimizing damage to infrastructure needed for future rebel use. bravo checkpoint fox echo secure the checkpoint and gather all available intel on heavy weapon movement through the region for command exploitation. charlie outpost red fox clear the site, destroy the two skell tech drone crates with c4, and free the pows confirmed to be held inside the position. delta freeman residences break the ongoing civilian roundup, prevent casualties or abductions, capture the enemy leader directing the attack, and use the on-site helicopter for mission extraction. support references halo lz / ip drop reference for the red tree near the waterfall and swarm launcher, used to start the foot infiltration into restricted area 01. training center target site primary assault reference for the alpha kill and site seizure, with emphasis on a silent hvt removal and controlled structural damage. tacmap rundown area overview for the halo insertion point and all four objectives across restricted area 01: alpha at the training center, bravo at checkpoint fox echo, charlie at outpost red fox, and delta at freeman residences.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-sirroco%20%5B1183414051318013982%5D.html', label: 'op-sirroco', searchLabel: 'op sirroco', text: 'operation sirroco operation sirroco sigint and humint have fixed the location of sandman, sentinel\'s bomb-maker tied to recent attacks in liberty. the team will move from fob bandit by rhib, break a civilian roundup chain across three residential targets, exploit fox 02 for fresh comms intelligence, and finish with a controlled capture at liberty transport hub. launch fob bandit, south cape station, at sundown insertion rhib movement to island ip south of alpha mission bias fast rescue sweeps, low-signature approach on hvt end state rtb with sandman alive for eod strip and interrogation situation building on the success of op-canopy , signal exploitation identified ethan reynolds, callsign sandman , as sentinel\'s explosives specialist. he is assessed as erratic, operationally valuable, and directly linked to bomb attacks on auroan diplomats in liberty. sentinel is also moving civilians tied to skell tech into northern work camps. three residential sites require immediate intervention before the roundup completes, making the opening phase both a rescue action and a pressure sweep designed to break enemy tempo before the hvt hit. execution phase 1 launch from fob bandit with rhib insertion to the island ip south of alpha. black qrf or combat diver kits are acceptable as long as the approach stays controlled and quiet. phase 2 sweep the residential targets and fox 02 in sequence, prevent abductions, eliminate hostile elements, and pull supplemental comms intelligence on liberty transport hub. phase 3 isolate sandman without gunfire near the hvt, disable the s-vest through eod handling, secure the hub, conduct sse, and exfiltrate with the prisoner. priority intel humint confirms sandman wears a concealed s-vest when outside the base. firearms discharge near or on the hvt is prohibited. capture must be deliberate, close, and controlled to avoid a detonation trigger. civilian focus alpha, charlie, and delta are rescue-led sweeps. kill speed matters less than stopping sentinel from lifting civilians off-site. clear armed resistance fast and stabilize the scene for follow-on recovery. mission end state fox 02 exploited, liberty transport hub searched, hvt secured alive, explosive belt rendered safe, and all collected intel routed back to fob bandit for immediate follow-on analysis. objectives alpha jane addams residences secure the block, eliminate hostile elements, and prevent civilians from being abducted before sentinel can move them north. bravo control station fox 02 clear the station and connect to the enemy comms net to pull supplementary intelligence on the hvt and liberty transport hub activity. charlie benjamin franklin residences conduct a second residential sweep, neutralize armed resistance, and assist any civilians still under immediate threat. delta richard cobden residences finish the residential clearance, secure civilians, and interrogate the local enemy leader on-site before leaving him for the recovery team. echo liberty transport hub locate sandman first, isolate him without gunfire, perform eod handling on the vest after capture, then secure the hub and run sse for planned-attack intelligence before exfiltration. support references fob bandit rhib launch reference for the south cape station departure point and the maritime staging setup used to start the mission at sundown. island infiltration point visual reference for the island ip south of alpha, used to stage the initial dismount and start the residential sweep sequence. tacmap rundown route overview for alpha through echo, showing the southern island insertion, inner-area sweep path, fox 02 exploitation, and the final liberty transport hub approach.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-staghorn%20%5B1167101545284894803%5D.html', label: 'op-staghorn', searchLabel: 'op staghorn', text: 'operation staghorn operation staghorn sentinel’s eclipse unit has surged into liberty city and is actively abducting civilians into a trafficking pipeline. qrf will infil from seal passage in low-profile civilian clothing, move fast through a chain of urban hot zones, clear hostile pockets, assist civilians on contact, and recover intelligence at liberty port on where the captives are being moved. insertion seal passage, western approach at sundown profile civilian concealment, low-visibility entry pace rapid sweeps, no deep room-by-room clears finish rtb south cape station after liberty port intel situation this is the urban twin of `op-coral`, built around a denser liberty city environment and the same underlying human-trafficking crisis. eclipse personnel are abducting civilians, exploiting city blocks as transient holding areas, and moving victims toward an unknown final destination. the mission is not about holding terrain. it is about speed, civilian protection, and striking every identified hotspot before the trafficking chain can relocate its captives. every cleared zone should immediately reduce local danger and push the team closer to the logistics answer at liberty port. execution infil enter from seal passage at sundown in civilian clothes and move with minimal signature through the city edge. urban sweep clear the first six hot zones fast, assist civilians, and kill all hostiles or any target of opportunity threatening the rescue tempo. port exploit finish at liberty port, locate the enemy toc, and recover intelligence revealing where civilians are being transported. priority intel the team is explicitly not expected to clear every room in depth. quick security sweeps are enough as long as the route keeps moving and civilians are stabilized. delay helps the traffickers more than a perfect sweep does. the final answer sits at liberty port. every earlier location is a suppression and protection stop, but the port objective is the one that should expose the outbound route for the kidnapped civilians and let follow-on operations hit the pipeline deeper. mission end state eclipse hot zones across liberty city are broken up, civilians are rescued or stabilized wherever possible, the trafficking network loses local momentum, and the team leaves liberty port with actionable intelligence on the next transfer destination before returning to south cape station. alpha parliament shopping street initial urban contact zone. clear the street fast and protect civilians caught in the first active trafficking pocket. bravo thomas jefferson residences break the residential strongpoint and keep the trafficking route from using apartment cover to stage or sort captives. charlie auroa parliament retake the government-sector hotspot and prevent eclipse from turning a symbolic civic site into a transit choke point. delta adam smith district suppress the district node quickly and keep the route open for civilian movement away from the core fighting. echo construction site clear the construction block and deny eclipse another temporary holding area inside unfinished urban structures. foxtrot winter lake shopping street remove the final city-center trafficking pocket before the team pushes onto the logistics hub at the waterfront. golf liberty port exploit the enemy toc and recover the intelligence package showing where eclipse is taking the abducted civilians. hot zone route primary route reference covering the infiltration point, all urban hot zones, and the final path into liberty port. undercover kit reference for the intended low-profile civilian look: concealed plate carrier, minimum visible military gear, and suppressed smg or pistol loadout. tacmap liberty city hot-zone map covering the west-side infil at seal passage, the full seven-point objective chain, and the final move to liberty port.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-stranded-knight%20%5B1193888398314848387%5D.html', label: 'op-stranded-knight', searchLabel: 'op stranded knight', text: 'operation stranded knight operation stranded knight qrf cherokee will move through the lake country border region to recover cia operative jayhawk after his sentinel cover was burned during an investigation into a human trafficking network. the route follows the likely detention chain from a construction-site intel cache to drone support facilities, a suspected prison camp, and finally camp viper where the operative or his trail is expected to resolve. launch site erewhon hq insertion little bird to lz near ra01 construction site world params drones, azrael, and helicopters on classic method covert foot patrol across all objectives situation jayhawk, an undercover cia operative embedded with sentinel to expose a trafficking ring in lake country, triggered his distress beacon after his cover was compromised. isr lost the signal near crown mountain, which suggests immediate capture, transfer, or execution pressure. the enemy trail links several sites that can reveal his fate: an rfid-secured construction cache, a drone maintenance hub supporting regional patrols, a prison-camp-style ancient fort, and camp viper farther north. the mission therefore runs as a deliberate exploitation chain rather than a single rescue breach. execution alpha clear the construction site, exploit the rfid-secured storage, and search the northeast three-story building for intelligence on jayhawk or the trafficking network. bravo secure control station viper 01, demolish the workshop, and destroy the murmur drone patrol on crown mountain to reduce isr pressure. charlie raid ancient fort, interrogate the camp leader, and determine whether jayhawk is present, recently moved, or tied to additional captives. delta push north to camp viper, liberate the camp with minimal asset damage, and return the commanding officer alive to hq for interrogation. priority intel alpha’s rfid-secured storage and nearby multistory building are the first real clue nodes and should be exploited thoroughly before the team outruns the evidence chain. bravo is technically a target of opportunity, but the drone workshop and murmur patrol meaningfully reduce enemy overwatch over the rest of the route. charlie contains the key branch logic. if a prisoner spawns in the ancient fort cells, that prisoner is treated as jayhawk and indicates his asset is also at camp viper. if no prisoner appears, the interrogated camp leader confirms jayhawk was recently moved there instead. either way, camp viper becomes the final decisive site. mission end state the trafficking-ring infrastructure is exposed, drone support around crown mountain is degraded, ancient fort is exploited for detainee intelligence, camp viper is liberated, and jayhawk’s status is resolved with the enemy commander taken alive for follow-on questioning back at hq. alpha construction site clear the site, exploit the rfid-secured storage unit, and search the northeast three-story building for anything tied to jayhawk or the trafficking ring. bravo control station viper 01 take the maintenance hub, demolish the workshop, and eliminate the murmur drone patrol operating over crown mountain to weaken hostile isr. charlie ancient fort search the prison camp, exploit the detention cells, and interrogate the camp leader to determine jayhawk’s current location and the state of the captive network. delta camp viper liberate the camp with minimal damage to usable assets, secure any remaining captives, and bring the commanding officer back alive for interrogation. murmur patrol supplementary reference for the drone-maintenance area and nearby aerial patrol coverage tied to the bravo target. route reference north restricted area 01 and lake country border route linking the construction site, viper 01, ancient fort, and camp viper along the full rescue trail. tacmap north restricted area 01 and lake country border-region map covering all four objectives and the full overland rescue progression.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-subzero%20%5B1241003925063340102%5D.html', label: 'op-subzero', searchLabel: 'op subzero', text: 'operation subzero operation subzero fireteam polar will hunt the sokol unit across the dt. servo mountain belt after the terrorists executed civilians at natural hazards control and prepared a propaganda broadcast. the mission combines war-crimes evidence recovery, isr degradation, hvt interrogation, and final seizure of a chemical weapons laboratory before the cell can widen its attacks. launch site army pass bivouac, dt. servo step-off 1930 hours mode conquest enabled movement walk, drive, then helo lifts for charlie and delta situation the sokol unit, a bodark-linked terrorist cell embedded with sentinel, has launched a violent offensive through the mountain facilities of auroa. isr confirms they executed civilians at natural hazards control and appear to be staging a future broadcast built around the killings and their demands. their occupation spreads across a support network of sites that enables atrocity footage handling, isr coverage, network control, and chemical-weapons risk. the operation is therefore built as a rolling suppression and exploitation chain rather than a single direct-action hit. execution alpha patrol on foot to natural hazards control, kill sokol personnel, secure the execution footage devices, and search for surviving civilians. bravo use a land vehicle to reach drone station w071, search for survivors, exploit the site, and sabotage both relay antennas. charlie fly to the charlie lz, eliminate the remaining sokol takeover element at auroa intranet control, and interrogate razor plus his personal guard on site. delta fly to the delta lz, secure hemlock station, and hold for oxide to take over the chemical weapons laboratory before debriefing on site. priority intel alpha is both an assault and an evidence-recovery task. the devices containing execution footage must survive the fight so the war-crimes package can be exploited later. survivor search is not optional if civilians remain alive inside the objective area. charlie carries the key interrogation target set. razor, identified on the right, and his left-side personal guard both need to be apprehended, questioned about additional planned attacks, and then left on site per the original brief. mission end state sokol’s occupied facilities are cleared, their propaganda footage and network access chain are seized, their isr posture is reduced, razor’s cell is broken, and hemlock station is transferred to the incoming cbrn team with the area stable enough to end the operation in place. alpha natural hazards control eliminate sokol elements, recover the devices containing execution footage, and search the site for any surviving civilians in need of aid. bravo drone station w071 search for survivors, exploit the station, and sabotage both drone relay antennas to reduce enemy isr coverage across the region. charlie auroa intranet control kill the remaining takeover force, capture razor and his personal guard for on-site interrogation, and stop the broadcast preparation cycle. delta hemlock station secure the chemical weapons laboratory identified by raven 2, hold the site, and hand over control to oxide for specialist cbrn follow-on support. hvt reference identification reference for razor on the right and his personal guard on the left during the charlie-site interrogation phase. movement logic route reference preserving the original movement chain: walk to alpha, drive to bravo, fly to charlie lz, then fly to delta lz. tacmap dt. servo movement reference covering natural hazards control, drone station w071, auroa intranet control, hemlock station, and the full multi-leg insertion route.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-titan-shield%20%5B1237861316774068305%5D.html', label: 'op-titan-shield', searchLabel: 'op titan shield', text: 'operation titan shield operation titan shield qrf titan will counter a sen-wol attempt to seize golem island and project titan by stopping a pipeline sabotage, killing hvt condor at the scandium mine, and then capturing hvt cipher at camp salamander before hostile forces can burn the island’s drone and project data infrastructure for profit. launch site sector 1 bivouac step-off 2040 hours mobility watercraft insertion with eod support finish debrief on site after charlie situation a hostile sen-wol detachment has launched a takeover attempt across golem island, threatening project titan assets, advanced uav stocks, and any recoverable project data. local security has already been overwhelmed, and humint indicates the enemy is prepared to destroy what it cannot hold before selling the rest offshore. the immediate enemy scheme is spread across three critical nodes: a bomb-rigged chemical pipeline, condor’s activity at the scandium mine, and a tactical operations center at camp salamander where cipher is believed to hold the broader plan for the island. execution alpha secure the chemical pipeline, defuse the explosive package, tow it offshore in a sacrificial rhib, and destroy it at sea while preserving the production line. bravo ride the remaining rhib to the scandium mine, kill condor near the office building, upload the kill photo to zulu 3, and recover any operational intelligence. charlie move on camp salamander, capture cipher alive from the center of the site, clear the camp, interrogate the target, and gain access to enemy servers. priority intel alpha depends on deliberate eod handling, not brute-force clearance. the bomb must be defused and disposed of offshore using the two-rhib method rather than detonated on the pipeline itself, since preserving infrastructure is part of the mission. condor is a kill target at bravo, but cipher is the intelligence prize. charlie only closes correctly once the area is secure enough to interrogate him and exploit the camp’s server access for the larger golem island picture. mission end state the chemical pipeline stays intact, condor is eliminated and documented, camp salamander is retaken, cipher is captured and exploited on site, and the hostile detachment loses both its operational tempo and its chance to profit from project titan assets. alpha chemical pipeline secure the pipeline, defuse the bomb package, and destroy it safely at sea using the two-rhib disposal method while keeping the production line viable. bravo scandium mine neutralize condor near the office building, upload the proof-of-kill image to zulu 3, and collect whatever intelligence the mine can provide on offshore financing. charlie camp salamander capture cipher alive from the center of the camp, secure the full site, interrogate him, and break into the hostile server stack before the final debrief. tacmap golem island route reference covering the pipeline, scandium mine, camp salamander, and the overall qrf titan progression across the island.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-trihedron%20%5B1270213805447712788%5D.html', label: 'op-trihedron', searchLabel: 'op trihedron', text: 'operation trihedron operation trihedron combat divers team hydra will conduct a maritime-led assault across sinking country to break hostile control of offshore bunkers, seize the northern radar station for allied air management, and recapture a strategic ammunition depot without destroying the stock that local rebels need for resupply. launch site erewhon hq step-off 1850 hours insertion blackhawk helocast to maritime ip extraction hlz kratos near man eater slough situation enemy forces have entrenched themselves across a contested sinking country corridor, using offshore bunker positions to coordinate attacks, radar coverage to interfere with air movements, and an ammunition depot to sustain pressure against allied rebels on the southern border. the operation is designed to reverse that control in phases: strip bunker leadership first, turn the radar site into an allied forward air-control point, then recapture the depot intact enough for immediate resupply support. execution insert depart erewhon by blackhawk, helocast at the maritime ip, and swim 500 meters to the bunker island for the opening breach. alpha secure bunker edgehod north and conduct site exploitation of the underground bunker complex. bravo use a watercraft to reach radar station north, seize the site, and notify local assets to establish a fob for air-traffic control. charlie foot patrol to the ammunition depot, recapture it while preserving stock integrity, and extract any hvt found on site before moving to hlz kratos. priority intel alpha is a leadership-disruption task as much as a clearance task. offshore bunker control is what allows the enemy to direct attacks across the sector, so the underground exploitation phase matters as much as simply owning the island surface. charlie requires restraint. the depot is meant to be reused by friendly forces, which means demolition is not the objective there. if an hvt appears on site, the team is cleared to pull him out with the package and fold him into the final extraction. mission end state offshore command positions are broken, radar station north is converted into a friendly air-management node, the ammunition depot is restored for allied resupply, and hydra exits via kratos with any captured hvt and the region materially shifted back toward local rebel control. alpha bunker edgehod north helocast offshore, swim to the island, clear the bunker complex, and exploit the underground site for command and targeting intelligence. bravo radar station north move by watercraft, seize the radar installation, and transition the site to local assets as a forward operating base for managing regional air traffic. charlie ammunition depot advance on foot, recapture the depot without destroying stock, notify allies for resupply, and extract any hvt encountered on site with the team. tacmap mission route reference covering the maritime insertion, bunker island, radar station north, ammunition depot, and extraction to hlz kratos near man eater slough.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-vandal%20%5B1232342930631426149%5D.html', label: 'op-vandal', searchLabel: 'op vandal', text: 'operation vandal operation vandal qrf vandal will strike a hostile drone-production corridor in restricted area 01. the mission starts with locating the missing raven 3 recon team, then shutting down the nearby uav relay before finishing on assembly hall omega 01, where lethal aamon land drones are being mass assembled for wider deployment against allied territory. launch site fob bandit, south cape station step-off 2115 hours insertion halo to the ip loadout black kits with demolition specialist situation enemy forces are accelerating land-drone production on auroa, massing lethal aamon platforms to dominate disputed areas while allied rebels and skell tech field personnel take mounting losses. at 2035, raven 3 disappeared near the production corridor, and their last location now sits under drone guard. the immediate operational logic is clear: recover the recon team if possible, degrade enemy isr by taking down the uav relay, and then sabotage the assembly hall driving the wider aamon surge before the site can disperse output or hide surviving civilians inside the complex. execution insert halo onto the ip from fob bandit and patrol on foot through hostile hotspot terrain toward the first contact point. alpha neutralize the aamon perimeter around raven 3’s last known grid and re-establish contact with the recon team. bravo take drone station w161 and deactivate the uav communications relay to collapse enemy isr and strike coordination. charlie secure assembly hall omega 01, account for any civilians on site, and sabotage the land-drone production facility before returning or using the on-site helicopter. priority intel alpha is not just a rescue run. raven 3’s position is ringed by aamon drones, so the recovery only works if the perimeter is decisively stripped first. the drone threat is the main obstacle, not the terrain. bravo directly shapes charlie. cutting the w161 relay significantly reduces hostile isr and strike capability before the team commits to the assembly hall. if time remains after the main chain, nearby targets of opportunity are already cleared and the on-site helicopter can support a faster rtb. mission end state raven 3 is recovered or accounted for, the uav relay is offline, assembly hall omega 01 is sabotaged, surviving civilians are protected, and enemy aamon land-drone production in the sector is broken hard enough to relieve immediate pressure on allied fighters and skell personnel. alpha raven 3 contact point clear the drone-guarded perimeter at grid yankee echo 35642 and make contact with raven 3 at their last known position. bravo drone station w161 seize the station and shut down the uav comms relay to cut enemy isr coverage and reduce their ability to coordinate strikes. charlie assembly hall omega 01 secure the production site, protect any civilians still inside, and sabotage the hall responsible for assembling lethal aamon land drones. tacmap restricted area 01 route reference covering the halo ip, raven 3 last known position, drone station w161, and assembly hall omega 01.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-wandering-wraith%20%5B1240241026182942790%5D.html', label: 'op-wandering-wraith', searchLabel: 'op wandering wraith', text: 'operation wandering wraith operation wandering wraith fireteam hammer will hit a four-part emergency chain inside restricted area 01: investigate project titan ugv activity at the gold trail testing zone, capture hvt raider at nugget cliff, retake jace skell dam before more executions occur, and finish by destroying the enemy quick-reaction force at the auroa solar power plant while protecting trapped civilians. launch site south cape station step-off 2013 hours settings drone presence: classic flow foot movement for alpha/bravo, helo lift to charlie situation onyx reconnaissance triggered contact near the gold trail testing zone while investigating suspected project titan ugv trials. their drone confirmed lethal unmanned patrols before it was shot down, raising the possibility that skell employees or civilians are trapped inside the warehouse complex. at the same time, raider has surfaced at nugget cliff mine, where he is wanted for questioning over the recent auroa parliament attack, and a rogue sentinel cell has seized jace skell dam after executing four engineers on camera. they have threatened more killings by 0900, which turns the dam into a no-delay crisis objective. execution insert launch from south cape station by overseer and stage at the skell technology location lz near the testing zone. alpha / bravo move on foot to neutralize the gold trail ugv threat, rescue survivors, then capture raider at nugget cliff and hand him to bravo team back at the lz. charlie board the helicopter from the lz and move fast to jace skell dam to halt further executions and secure the site. delta push into the auroa solar power plant, eliminate the enemy qrf, assist civilians, and end the operation inside the plant for debrief. priority intel the testing zone is expected to contain lethal ugvs, not just infantry. if the warehouse doors trap the team inside, the field note is to hack the laptop to reopen them rather than treating it as a dead end. raider can be represented by any enemy at the mine, but custody transfer still matters to the mission narrative. after the handoff at the lz, hammer must use the helicopter jump to compress the response time on the dam before the terrorist deadline overtakes the operation. mission end state the gold trail ugv test sector is cleared, survivors are recovered, raider is transferred alive for questioning, the dam hostage crisis is broken before additional executions occur, and the solar plant qrf is destroyed with civilians stabilized and the debrief conducted on site. alpha gold trail testing zone destroy every lethal drone in the test sector, investigate the warehouse, and recover any trapped skell staff or civilians before the site is abandoned. bravo nugget cliff mine capture raider alive, bring him back to the skell technology location lz, roleplay the handoff to bravo team, and prepare for immediate lift-out. charlie jace skell dam retake the dam, stop the terrorist cell from carrying out additional engineer executions, and restore control of the site before the ultimatum expires. delta auroa solar power plant neutralize the qrf element holding the plant, help trapped civilians, and finish the mission inside the complex for the final debrief. tacmap restricted area 01 movement reference covering the gold trail testing zone, nugget cliff, jace skell dam, auroa solar power plant, and the final movement logic across the whole objective chain. lz reference skell technology location used as the initial landing point, raider transfer site, and helicopter pickup before the push to charlie. ugv recon feed last close-range drone footage from onyx before the feed was cut, confirming lethal ugv presence in the testing sector.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-warlord%20%5B1179008062988767252%5D.html', label: 'op-warlord', searchLabel: 'op warlord', text: 'operation warlord operation warlord ground branch will strike a hostile support belt built around a fuel storage site, a west radar station, and an ammunition depot inside the seal islands - restricted area 01 corridor. the mission is designed to cripple enemy sustainment and information control while simultaneously recovering allied points of contact tied to charlie team. launch site black site wolverine mode story or conquest insertion overseer halo by day, haho by night recovery return captured hvt to black site wolverine situation the enemy is holding three infrastructure nodes that directly support its ability to fight in the region: fuel, radar coverage, and ammunition. reclaiming those sites weakens hostile warfighting capacity while strengthening allied freedom of movement in the surrounding area. the raid is coupled with a rescue track for local allied contacts associated with charlie team. each objective therefore carries both a strike task and a personnel recovery requirement, which makes controlled tempo more important than a simple smash-and-grab approach. execution insert lift from black site wolverine aboard an overseer helicopter, conduct a high-altitude jump into the ao, regroup, and move on foot. alpha secure the fuel storage site with minimal damage to infrastructure and recover charlie team’s first point of contact. bravo take the west radar station, kill phoenix on sight, document the id, rescue the outcast scout, and seize the comms net after collecting movement intel. charlie raid the ammunition depot, hold the stockpile for local allies, capture specter alive, secure the final allied poc, and return to black site wolverine. priority intel phoenix at bravo is the enemy cyber warfare specialist responsible for opsec disruption and is a hard kill target. specter at charlie is the more valuable capture, with knowledge of upcoming operations that justifies immediate live extraction. as originally briefed, hvt identity can be roleplayed if needed. additional targets of opportunity threatening allied forces are already greenlit, but alpha still requires discipline to avoid wrecking infrastructure meant to be handed back to friendly control. mission end state fuel, radar, and ammunition assets are denied to the enemy, all allied contacts are recovered, the hostile communications network is turned, phoenix is confirmed dead, specter is extracted alive, and ground branch returns to black site wolverine with the ao reset in favor of allied forces. alpha fuel storage facility secure the site intact enough for allied reuse while recovering charlie team’s first point of contact from inside the objective area. bravo west radar station kill phoenix, photograph the id confirmation, rescue the allied scout, and flip control of the communications net after collecting local movement intelligence. charlie ammunition storage depot secure the munitions stockpile for allied use, capture specter alive, and protect the final friendly point of contact before exfiltration. tacmap seal islands - restricted area 01 reference showing black site wolverine as the start and finish point with all three mission objectives along the route. black site access ground-level doors are sealed. re-entry is through the roof access on the smaller building where the staircase door remains usable. roof landing reference a competent pilot can land a team and captured hvt directly onto the roof entry point for clean mission recovery. extraction setup secondary reference for the black site wolverine rooftop approach during final hvt recovery and debrief handoff.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-x-ray%20%5B1172994829140099115%5D.html', label: 'op-x-ray', searchLabel: 'op x ray', text: 'operation x-ray operation x-ray ground branch is tasked with dismantling an insurgent pocket spread across camp kodiak, the ancient cemetery, and the driftwood islets testing zone. the cell is stockpiling weapons, masking movement through the cemetery, and experimenting with drone-linked equipment on the islets. the operation will hit all three sectors in sequence before the network can disperse. launch asf hq / tier 1 insertion blackhawk haho into camp kodiak settings drone presence set to classic loadout note heavy gunner recommended situation an insurgent threat is consolidating across a compact but varied operational belt. camp kodiak is supporting weapons flow and command activity, the ancient cemetery is being used as concealment for illicit movement, and driftwood islets hosts testing tied to experimental equipment and hostile drone capability. the mission favors a silent opening and disciplined progression northward through the ao. surprise matters, but once contact is made, all hostile elements and viable targets of opportunity are cleared for engagement. execution insert launch from hq by blackhawk, conduct a night haho drop directly into camp kodiak, and secure the landing sector fast. alpha disable camp kodiak’s communications hub, seize shipment intelligence, and prevent hvt lynx from escaping. bravo push north through the ancient cemetery, clear enemy presence, and recover field intelligence from bodies and site clutter. charlie recon the driftwood islets testing zone, identify experimental equipment before contact, recover drone circuit boards, and capture griffin alive for return to base. priority intel lynx at alpha and griffin at charlie are roleplay hvts, so any suitable enemy can be assigned to those identities if the team wants to preserve the original immersion brief. griffin remains the live-capture priority because of his connection to insurgent experimental weaponry. charlie is not a blind assault. the team is expected to conduct a deliberate read of the testing zone first, recover drone circuit boards where possible, and then exploit the site for capability intelligence before exfiltrating with the hvt. mission end state camp kodiak’s command and comms function is broken, the cemetery cover route is stripped clean, experimental drone hardware is collected from driftwood islets, and griffin is brought back alive with enough captured intelligence to map the insurgent weapons pipeline. alpha camp kodiak break the communications hub, recover shipment intel, and kill lynx before he can collapse the site or flee the camp. bravo ancient cemetery clear the cemetery of hostile presence and strip bodies or abandoned positions for phones, ids, radios, and any linkable field intelligence. charlie driftwood islets testing zone survey the experimental site, bag recoverable drone circuit boards, sweep the area for capability intel, and capture griffin alive for interrogation. tacmap operational reference covering camp kodiak, the ancient cemetery, and the driftwood islets testing zone across the full x-ray objective chain.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-zero-nova%20%5B1246997863838388244%5D.html', label: 'op-zero-nova', searchLabel: 'op zero nova', text: 'operation zero nova operation zero nova ground branch will infiltrate golem island to break an enemy communications program before it reaches operational use. the raid centers on disabling satcom control infrastructure, clearing a qrf anchor point at forgotten sanctuary, and demolishing the heliport shipment tied to the same advanced communications network. launch site wild island bivouac, cape north step-off 2100 hours insertion overseer helicopter, halo northwest of alpha recovery lizard to bandit 1-2 at infil point situation enemy forces on golem island are close to fielding a new communications capability with strategic implications beyond the island. the operational backbone is split between the satellite control infrastructure, a quick-reaction element staged at forgotten sanctuary, and a heliport shipment supporting continued technology expansion. the terrain favors covert movement through dense forest and maintenance access routes. the mission depends on hitting each site fast enough to prevent the communications network from hardening or repositioning once the first target goes dark. execution insert depart wild island bivouac by overseer helo, hold above 1500 meters, and halo northwest of the alpha target. alpha cut power in the underground server area and communications building to disable the satellite dish control center and seize any comtec intelligence. bravo eliminate the qrf detachment at forgotten sanctuary and sabotage worthwhile targets of opportunity before advancing. charlie secure the heliport, demolish the shipment in and around the west warehouse, and capture lizard for turnover at the infil point. priority intel alpha is the mission’s decisive systems target. power cuts at both the underground server area and the communications building are required to fully compromise the satellite control chain rather than just damaging surface equipment. lizard is assessed as the enemy logistics specialist at the heliport. if no formal pid is possible, the hvt handoff still follows the roleplay brief: designate a captured hostile, move him to bandit 1-2 at the infil point, then break for debrief at erewhon. mission end state the satcom control node is shut down, the sanctuary qrf is neutralized, the heliport shipment is destroyed before redistribution, and lizard is handed over alive, leaving the island’s communications program and logistics chain in immediate disarray. alpha satellite control center disable the dish control infrastructure by cutting power in both the underground servers area and the communications building, then seize enemy comtec intelligence. bravo forgotten sanctuary destroy the quick-reaction element anchoring the route to the heliport and sabotage any viable supporting assets encountered on the way through. charlie heliport demolish the weapons and supply shipment around the west warehouse, capture lizard if present, and deliver the hvt back to the original infil point. tacmap golem island movement reference from wild island insertion through alpha, forgotten sanctuary, the heliport, and the marked maintenance tunnel route.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20BRAVO%20-%20op-zodiac%20%5B1174380288827207710%5D.html', label: 'op-zodiac', searchLabel: 'op zodiac', text: 'operation zodiac operation zodiac bodark special forces are actively hitting restricted area 01 while sentinel brokers skell technology into a growing black-market pipeline. ground branch will insert from ancient fort by helicopter, conduct a high-altitude approach west of the island, rescue trapped scientists at omega operations, and then roll the connected command, tunnel, and logistics nodes feeding the network. launch site ancient fort, east liberty step-off 2100 hours insertion helicopter haho west of the island mode conquest active, bodark storyline situation a scientist distress call from restricted area 01 indicates omega operations is under direct bodark assault. camp ferret is functioning as a tactical operations center for the enemy push, and an underground tunnel linked to the camp is hosting a weapons exchange tied to the larger sentinel-bodark trade in skell technology. camp weasel anchors the network’s follow-on logistics and stronghold posture. the mission is not just a rescue. it is a deliberate dismantling of the arms chain, with hvt handling and intelligence capture required at each stage to expose the broader trade route. execution insert launch from ancient fort, stay high to avoid radar, and haho west of the island before forming up on the ground. alpha hit omega operations, rescue civilians, neutralize the bodark island element, and destroy every sam blocking follow-on air support. bravo / charlie clear camp ferret, eliminate dmitri ivanov, use the tunnel link to break the weapons deal, and seize the supply truck while interrogating any senior enemy present. delta assault camp weasel, capture nolan turner alive, secure the full stronghold, and hold on site for enhanced interrogation and final debrief. priority intel this ao contains substantial blufor activity that may create temporary opportunities but cannot be treated as a stable shield. if the team wants to reduce outcast interference and avoid accidental alerts, conquest progress should be reset before launch as briefed in the original op note. dmitri ivanov at camp ferret is the local chief tactician and a valid kill objective. nolan turner at camp weasel is the more valuable capture target because of his logistics role inside the wolves’ arms network. mission end state scientists are extracted from omega operations, enemy air-denial assets are demolished, the ferret tunnel deal is broken, the supply truck is seized, and camp weasel is held with turner in custody so the enhanced interrogation team can exploit the network in place. alpha omega operations rescue the trapped scientists, wipe the bodark island detachment, and destroy the sam belt preventing friendly air support from entering the fight. bravo camp ferret collapse the tactical operations center, gather actionable intelligence, and eliminate dmitri ivanov to disrupt enemy command continuity. charlie underground tunnel use the ferret tunnel access to hit the weapons deal, seize the supply truck, and pressure any senior hostile for intelligence tied to camp weasel and the trade network. delta camp weasel assault the stronghold, capture nolan turner alive, secure both interior and exterior sectors, and hold for the interrogation team and on-site debrief. tacmap central restricted area 01 movement reference covering omega operations, camp ferret, the tunnel route, camp weasel, and the dt.servo operational corridor.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20CHARLIE%20-%20op-charger%20%5B1280680710839210015%5D.html', label: 'op-charger', searchLabel: 'op charger', text: 'operation charger operation charger raven 5 isr has fixed a hostile network operating across the south new argyll border belt. skell estate is functioning as the regional command post, long valley residences is being used as a communications and intelligence hide, and the brewery has been converted into a weapons and ied supply site. ground branch will move under darkness, break the cell in sequence, and stop any follow-on strikes against nearby civilian infrastructure. hq erewhon hq step-off 2030 hours mobility starfield x4 technical delivery blackbeard to bandit 2 at brown homestead situation the target cluster forms a compact command, intel, and logistics chain inside south new argyll. skell estate is directing the network, long valley residences is shielding key operators among civilians, and the brewery is storing weapons while supporting improvised explosive device production. the mission requires a controlled sweep across all three sites to collapse the cell before it can launch further attacks. tactical surprise matters because the objectives sit close enough together that a noisy breach at one can destabilize the rest of the operation. execution insert depart erewhon by technical and stage north of skell estate under darkness. alpha secure skell estate and eliminate the enemy command center before the network can react. bravo push into long valley residences, neutralize operators, and seize portable communications devices. charlie raid the brewery, capture blackbeard, mark all ied and supply caches for eod, then deliver the hvt to brown homestead. priority intel long valley is a civilian-covered site, so visual discrimination and disciplined target identification matter. portable electronic devices at bravo are collection priority and should be bagged intact for exploitation after the raid. blackbeard is the designated demolition specialist at the brewery. any enemy on site may be selected to stand in as the hvt, but the handoff must still support the interrogation narrative and preserve the mission finish. mission end state enemy command, communications, and supply activity across south new argyll are dismantled; the hvt is transferred alive to bandit 2; explosive stockpiles are flagged for follow-on eod action; and ground branch returns to base with the cell broken before it can strike civilian infrastructure. alpha skell estate take down the regional command node and clear the estate before enemy control can shift to backup sites. bravo long valley residences neutralize the communications and intelligence element while collecting any portable electronic comms devices left on site. charlie brewery capture blackbeard, mark supply and ied points with chemlight for eod, then move the hvt to brown homestead for turnover. tacmap south new argyll movement reference covering the estate, residences, brewery, and final transfer route to brown homestead.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20CHARLIE%20-%20op-iron-nest%20%5B1283120832813600809%5D.html', label: 'op-iron-nest', searchLabel: 'op iron nest', text: 'operation iron nest operation iron nest enemy forces have overrun the skell foundation head office and are actively hunting a c1 ugv engineer while sweeping civilians at gunpoint. team iron nest must recover any surviving engineer, secure the underground research lab before sensitive prototypes are seized, then move on the infinity transport hub to capture the enemy pilot known as horizon and extract both the hvt and target helicopter to summers homestead. hq erewhon hq step-off 1947 hours insertion overseer helo, touch-and-go quick insert delivery summers homestead via captured helicopter situation bandit 2-4 reports that the skell foundation head office has been overrun and enemy squads are actively searching for a c1 ugv engineer while interrogating civilians across the area. the underground research lab contains sensitive prototypes and classified material that cannot be allowed to fall into hostile hands. a second time-sensitive opportunity exists at the infinity transport hub, where the hvt code-named horizon , an enemy pilot with detailed knowledge of radar coverage and aerial operations, is present on site. capturing horizon intact offers immediate exploitation value for the wider ao. execution insert lift from erewhon near sundown in black kits and use a touch-and-go helo insertion onto the lz. alpha patrol southwest to the head office and conduct the raid with full stealth to avoid any radio alert. bravo once alpha is secure, move directly on infinity transport hub before the hvt can be spooked or displaced. charlie deliver horizon and the captured helicopter to bandit-3 at summers homestead for handoff. priority intel hvt: horizon, enemy pilot at infinity transport hub. alpha must remain quiet. any radio alarm from the head office risks losing horizon and the aircraft before the team can transition to bravo. mission end state the head office and underground lab are secured, any surviving engineer is recovered, horizon is captured, the enemy helicopter is seized, and both packages are delivered intact to summers homestead. objectives alpha skell foundation head office secure the site, recover the ugv engineer if present, and investigate the underground research lab for prototypes and intelligence. bravo infinity transport hub infiltrate the hub, liberate civilians, apprehend horizon, and capture the helicopter for follow-on transport. charlie summers homestead deliver horizon and the captured helicopter to bandit-3 for turnover and immediate exploitation. tacmap rundown northeast infinity ao reference showing the stealth push from head office to transport hub and the final handoff route into summers homestead.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20CHARLIE%20-%20op-moonshine%20%5B1281031266896187422%5D.html', label: 'op-moonshine', searchLabel: 'op moonshine', text: 'operation moonshine operation moonshine two hardened laboratories in smuggler coves are processing chemical precursors, either for narcotics production or for weapons development. team moonshine will hit the labs first, seize the lead scientist, destroy the facilities, then roll directly into outpost red tiger to free the captive local asset, steal the gunship, and collapse the linked air-strike node. hq erewhon hq step-off 2149 hours insertion night haho with gas masks at lz extraction gunship plus ground escort back to hq situation isr from reaper-6 has identified two secure laboratories in smuggler coves receiving chemical precursors in volume. the enemy\'s end state is unclear, but the indicators point either to narcotics production or to an active chemical weapons program. the labs are linked to outpost red tiger, a heavily fortified fob that has been launching air strikes on allied rebel positions. the mission is therefore built to remove both the chemical node and the support outpost in one continuous raid. execution insert depart hq by night and conduct a haho insertion into the ao before masking up at the landing zone. tempo use speed, surprise, and violence of action to stop the scientist from fleeing or warning red tiger. mobility acquire transportation inside the ao only after the raid begins and the hvt is secured. return split the exfil with two operators flying the gunship overhead while two escort the scientist back to erewhon by ground. priority intel hvt: scientist in charge of the labs. any hostile inside one of the labs may be roleplayed as the scientist, but command requires the hvt alive for interrogation. the package cannot be lost during the shift from alpha to bravo. mission end state both labs are destroyed, the scientist is extracted alive, red tiger is stripped of its weapon caches and aviation platform, and the team returns to hq with the hvt under escort. objectives alpha oleander station secure both labs, capture the scientist, destroy the facilities with c4, and move immediately toward bravo with the hvt. bravo outpost red tiger secure the outpost, liberate the local asset, steal the gunship, and destroy the weapon caches with controlled charges. air-ground return concept showing the split escort posture for the scientist package and captured gunship. tacmap rundown south central smuggler coves reference showing the relation between oleander station, outpost red tiger, and the return route back toward erewhon with the hvt.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20CHARLIE%20-%20op-vespa%20%5B1277622595713241103%5D.html', label: 'op-vespa', searchLabel: 'op vespa', text: 'operation vespa operation vespa sentinel has consolidated control over large sections of windy islands and is using the region to support a black-market arms network tied to mercenary activity in the middle east. team vespa will investigate the rebel camp attack, break the port supply line, disable the drone control node, seize chemical evidence and the hvt at the incineration plant, then disrupt the logistics hub at the auroa recycling factory. fob south cape station launch 1732 brief / 1800 insertion insertion uh-60 black hawk in green kits final contact jupiter 6 after mission completion situation sentinel now controls a large share of windy islands, exploiting the remoteness of the terrain to sustain a covert arms operation. reaper 3 isr also indicates two allied rebels kia at site whiskey india one, where a makeshift humint and patrol camp was recently hit by sentinel paratroopers. the mission is designed to dismantle the network in sequence: confirm what happened at the rebel site, choke the port supply line, shut down the uav attack node, seize remaining chemical evidence before it is burned, and break the recycling factory hub that keeps local enemy logistics moving. execution insert deploy from south cape station by uh-60 in green kits and land on the first objective at 1800. alpha secure the initial lz and perimeter, then conduct site exploitation at whiskey india one. shift reuse the helicopter to move toward the secondary landing zone near bravo before transitioning to movement on foot. end complete the echo logistics denial, establish communication with jupiter 6, and rtb with the hvt package. priority intel hvt: nox, chemical weapons expert supervising disposal operations. the critical evidence chain sits at the incineration plant. if the team arrives too late, the chemical weapons test trail is destroyed and the logistics hub at echo can continue operating with reduced pressure. mission end state sentinel\'s windy islands supply line is disrupted, drone attacks are curtailed, chemical evidence is recovered with nox in custody, and the recycling factory no longer functions as a viable logistics node. objectives alpha whiskey india one secure the perimeter and conduct site exploitation at the attacked rebel humint camp. bravo windy islands port retake the port and tag weapons containers for demo team disposal before they can be shipped overseas. charlie drone station s01 neutralize the station, recover uav flight data, and use an emp device to render the electronics inoperable. delta incineration plant don gas masks, secure the plant, apprehend nox, and recover remaining chemical samples before they are destroyed. echo auroa recycling factory secure key infrastructure to break the enemy logistics hub and create room for local allies to establish a foothold. tacmap rundown ao reference showing the objective flow from whiskey india one through the port, drone station, incineration plant, and final logistics denial at the recycling factory.' },
  { href: 'Ground%20Branch%20Task%20Force%20-%20OPORDS%20BREAKPOINT%20CHARLIE%20-%20op-wolverine%20%5B1276163608425922590%5D.html', label: 'op-wolverine', searchLabel: 'op wolverine', text: 'operation wolverine operation wolverine enemy forces have launched from a forward operating base tied to the auroa weather station and are holding hostages while attempting to coordinate with the marauders cell. team wolverine must cut the quick reaction force relay, wipe the supporting fob, and reach the weather station fast enough to free the captives before negotiations turn into a handoff or execution. fob south cape station fob step-off 1900 hours insertion halo in white kits force mix demo and overwatch elements attached situation the situation in the mountainous south-central auroa region is unstable and escalating. reaper-1-3 isr confirms the enemy is holding multiple hostages at the auroa weather station while coordinating with the marauders terrorist cell for a possible transfer. the team must first blind and break the enemy\'s quick reaction capability, then destroy the supporting fob before pushing the final hostage rescue. targets of opportunity across the ao are authorized, and no negotiation is to be entertained with the hostile cell. execution insert halo from south cape station in white kits and move on foot toward alpha and bravo. mobility acquire vehicles inside the ao only as needed after the initial infiltration phase. tempo move with speed and precision to keep the weather station blind to the assault chain. end after delta, remain on site to protect civilians until guardian arrives for relocation and conduct debrief on site. priority intel threat link: weather station captors are negotiating with marauders. the relay at the mine and the qrf at nugget cliff are the key interruption points. if they stay live, the weather station can harden before team wolverine reaches the hostage package. mission end state the enemy relay and qrf are destroyed, red ferret is rendered unusable, hostages are recovered alive, and civilians remain under team wolverine protection until guardian completes the relocation handoff. objectives alpha mine relay site rig the communications relay antenna with c4 so the enemy loses the ability to warn the weather station in time. bravo nugget cliff detonate the relay charges and assault the enemy quick reaction force simultaneously before they can react or reinforce. charlie outpost red ferret secure the outpost, liberate the pow, and demolish the enemy\'s equipment, weapons, and vehicles with controlled charges. delta auroa weather station neutralize all hostiles fast enough to prevent hostage casualties, then establish contact with guardian for civilian relocation. tacmap rundown west restricted area 01 reference showing the progression from mine relay sabotage through red ferret and the final hostage rescue at the weather station in the good hope mountain sector.' },
  { href: 'JSOC%20Ghost%20Division%20-%20%F0%9F%97%82%20OPERATIONS%20III%20-%20op-eos%20%5B1051851626253660171%5D.html', label: 'op-eos', searchLabel: 'op eos', text: 'operation eos operation eos an aircraft loaded with weapons and critical supplies is sitting at liberty airport and scheduled to depart at 0500. outcast forces urgently need the package, so the task force must split between ground and overwatch elements, seize the aircraft before takeoff, land it at plz coral, and tag it for recovery by the outcast team on standby. briefing south cape station, windy islands target liberty airport aircraft team split alpha ground / bravo overwatch delivery plz coral with cospas-sarsat tag situation outcast command has confirmed an aircraft loaded with weapons and valuable supplies is staged at liberty airport on auroa\'s south coast. the aircraft is expected to depart at 0500, which leaves a narrow window to seize it before sentinel can move the cargo out of reach. the resource package is significant enough to affect regional resistance operations, so speed matters. the team must hit the airport hard enough to secure the plane intact, then move it to a safe landing area where the outcast recovery element can take over. execution alpha ground team infil by rhib from the south and push toward the airport objective by sea approach. bravo overwatch team departs by helicopter, conducts a long-range haho, lands east of the airport, and establishes an op atop the atc tower. assault coordinate both elements to break airport security, recover the aircraft, and keep the target flyable. recovery land at plz coral, tag the aircraft with the modified beacon, then radio in the outcast recovery team. debrief return to south cape station after handoff is complete. objective chain 1 alpha reaches the south ip by sea while bravo hahos to the east ip and sets the tower op. 2 coordinate the assault to recover the target aircraft. 3 land the aircraft safely at plz coral. 4 tag the aircraft with the modified beacon. 5 radio the recovery team. 6 return to south cape station for debrief. priority intel departure deadline: 0500 local at liberty airport. the mission fails strategically if the aircraft leaves the ground before capture. bravo\'s atc tower op and alpha\'s sea infiltration are designed to keep early warning low while preserving a synchronized strike. mission end state the aircraft is seized intact, landed safely at plz coral, tagged for friendly recovery, and transferred to the outcast package before the team returns to south cape station. satellite reference of liberty airport and the wider airport objective area. additional close-up of the airport interior lanes and access geometry around the objective. further target detail to support the synchronized alpha and bravo assault sequence. plz coral landing reference for the aircraft handoff and recovery signal procedure. modified cospas-sarsat beacon to tag the aircraft for the outcast recovery team at plz coral. tacmap overall mission reference showing the split-element insertion concept, liberty airport objective, and the follow-on landing route into plz coral.' },
  { href: 'JSOC%20Ghost%20Division%20-%20%F0%9F%97%82%20OPERATIONS%20III%20-%20op-man-cave%20%5B1182487457460129904%5D.html', label: 'op-man-cave', searchLabel: 'op man cave', text: 'operation man cave operation man cave sentinel has broken jace skell\'s satellite encryption and is using the underwater cable station near twin islands, cape north to monitor friendly movement. the task force must secure the uplink chain, exploit the short blackout window created by skell\'s ai thumb drive, and cripple the underground cable site before the enemy can reassert control. launch point erewhon, near dusk special item ai thumb drive from jace skell initial target radar station north (rsn) final target underground cable station (ucs) situation near twin islands in cape north, sentinel occupies the underwater cable station and has reportedly broken the encryption jace skell placed on his company\'s satellite network roughly 33 hours before the brief. that breach has likely exposed friendly movement and operating patterns. skell assesses that a new encryption scheme can be stood up if the station is crippled in time. the mission therefore focuses on knocking out the monitoring chain at speed and denying sentinel its access point before they can adapt. execution deploy lift from erewhon in black kits near dusk and move by helicopter to secure radar station north. upload use skell\'s ai thumb drive at the remote uplink station to temporarily disable the satlink. window exploit the short blackout window to move toward twin islands before sentinel can restore visibility. assault likely transition to watercraft and approach the underground cable station through the cave site. objective chain 1 deploy via erewhon hq. 2 secure radar station north (rsn). 3 upload the ai drive at remote uplink station (rus). 4 move to underground cable station (ucs). 5 cripple the underground cable station. priority intel critical dependency: skell\'s ai thumb drive creates the assault window. if the remote uplink upload fails or is delayed, the force loses the advantage needed to push from rsn through the twin islands route and into the cave-side approach on favorable terms. mission end state the sentinel monitoring chain is interrupted, the underwater cable infrastructure is crippled, and skell is free to roll a new encryption layer without sentinel continuing to watch friendly movement. area of operations i reference covering the broader cape north approach corridor. area of operations ii showing the relationship between twin islands and the inland staging route. radar station north isr reference for the initial helo-delivered strike objective. remote uplink station reference where the ai thumb drive must be uploaded. underground cable station target area tied to the final cave-side assault and station disablement.' },
  { href: 'JSOC%20Ghost%20Division%20-%20%F0%9F%97%82%20OPERATIONS%20III%20-%20op-subsistence%20%5B1117526514452410399%5D.html', label: 'op-subsistence', searchLabel: 'op subsistence', text: 'operation subsistence operation subsistence sentinel is conducting large-scale amber ruin testing across auroa, killing wildlife and non-combatants to study the agent\'s effects. after a legion drone swarm downed the inbound helicopter off smuggler\'s beach, the fireteam is stranded with minimal gear and no outside communications, but still tasked with pushing inland and securing intelligence on project amber ruin. start galleon cove bivouac, northeast of ip loadout gas mask, unsuppressed pistol, flashbangs only exfil safe site extract to erewhon for decon and aar situation auroa is under active assault while sentinel runs devastating amber ruin trials in multiple regions. the team was inbound to the infiltration point at smuggler\'s beach when a legion drone swarm destroyed the helicopter over the shoreline, killing the pilot and scattering equipment into the sea. survivors made landfall, but the crash left them cut off, under-equipped, and operating in contaminated conditions. the mission remains intact: investigate the objective chain and recover actionable intelligence on project amber ruin before the testing expands further. execution start from galleon cove bivouac and move toward the ip wearing a gas mask of your choice. initial combat is pistol-only and unsuppressed with minimal accessories; gear upgrades are expected to come from on-site procurement and roleplayed field pickup as the team progresses. a wind farm w01 b foxglove station c aamon assault area d hybrid engine factory exfil designated safe site for extraction back to erewhon mission condition world parameter: amber ruin turned on. the crash strips the team down to survival conditions from the outset. subsistence works best when the run feels improvised, contaminated, and resource-starved rather than fully kitted from step-off. tacmap isr compact ao reference showing the full objective chain from the northeast start point through final exfil under amber ruin conditions.' },
  { href: 'JSOC%20Ghost%20Division%20-%20%F0%9F%97%82%20OPERATIONS%20V%20-%20op-boomstick%20%5B1318787425559908404%5D.html', label: 'op-boomstick', searchLabel: 'op boomstick', text: 'operation boomstick operation boomstick enemy forces have occupied kelso fields in central new stirling and turned the farmland into an ied production and trafficking corridor while severing supply access for allied units. delta team is tasked with breaking the network by retaking supply-chain nodes, destroying the weapons cache, and capturing the leader known as badger . fob echo fob (erewhon) launch 1745 brief / black hawk departure insertion halo jump to designated entry point extraction hlz romeo 3 via jackal 2-1 situation actionable intelligence confirms an enemy detachment has seized kelso fields and repurposed the farmland to support ied production, weapons trafficking, and interdiction of allied supply lines across central new stirling. harrier imint indicates the road network is active with technicals and convoy movement. the mission is to fracture the network in sequence, rescue civilians where present, destroy the explosive stockpile, and capture badger before the enemy can break contact. execution insert depart echo fob by black hawk and conduct a halo jump onto the designated insertion point. recon establish uav coverage on touchdown, assess enemy positions, and begin the ground movement under delta callsign. mobility stay off the road network where possible; harrier reports multiple technicals and convoy traffic along hot routes. strike hit alpha through delta with speed and stealth to preserve surprise and keep badger fixed at the final site. extract move the hvt conscious to hlz romeo 3 and call jackal 2-1, standing by on five mikes, for rtb extraction. priority intel hvt: badger at delta objective. badger can be roleplayed by any senior-value hostile on site, including an rto, commander, bagman, or comparable enemy leadership figure tied to the agronomy center node. mission end state enemy comms are penetrated, civilians are recovered, the ied truck is destroyed at safe distance, badger is captured alive, and delta extracts clean from hlz romeo 3. objectives alpha drone station w132 secure the station and tap into enemy communications to track the imminent arrival of badger at the delta objective. bravo mossburn hopfield rescue all civilians under duress, secure the site, and sweep the warehouses for any additional intelligence. charlie kelso farm seize the supply truck carrying the ied and weapons cache, move it clear of the farm, and destroy it with a controlled c4 detonation. delta agronomy center confirm badger\'s presence, capture the target alive, and secure the site against enemy counteraction. hlz romeo 3 reference for the final extraction with badger package intact and conscious. area of operations ao reference showing the alpha through delta progression across kelso fields and the relationship between the farm nodes, badger site, and extraction corridor.' },
  { href: 'JSOC%20Ghost%20Division%20-%20%F0%9F%97%82%20OPERATIONS%20V%20-%20op-midnight-tango%20%5B1320144771242524795%5D.html', label: 'op-midnight-tango', searchLabel: 'op midnight tango', text: 'operation midnight tango operation midnight tango enemy elements tied to local special operations forces are building lethal ugvs across a fortified cluster of sites in north lake county under the program name iron phantom . delta team is tasked with dismantling the production chain, recovering coerced skell tech personnel, placing communications intercept hardware, and capturing the officer running the project before the network can disperse. fob echo fob (erewhon) launch 2217 brief / 2245 departure insertion mh-6 little bird with halo jump extraction on-site helo to site india 7 situation sigint intercepts identify an enemy detachment managing a hardened ugv production effort designated iron phantom . three primary locations support the program, and coerced skell tech engineers are believed to be working inside the network under duress. the task force must move quickly and quietly through the cluster, disrupt the build chain, secure civilian technical personnel, and capture the program lead at the main outpost before the enemy can destroy matériel, evacuate staff, or reposition the hvt. execution 2245 depart echo fob in black kits aboard mh-6 little bird with two combat divers and two security operators. insertion conduct a halo jump to the designated skell tech safehouse and recover the pre-staged commint device. bravo advance on the ancient village, eliminate the qrf, secure caches, and call bandit 1-3 for discreet recovery. charlie split into overwatch and diver elements to emplace the commint package on the floating antenna array in blackwater lake. final clear the prototype workshop, seize the hvt at the outpost, then deliver the package by captured helicopter to site india 7 for handoff and debrief. priority intel program: iron phantom, an enemy ugv build network in north lake county. portable electronics recovered from enemy personnel are to be bagged for exploitation. the main objective is the officer directing the project from the outpost tied to the workshop cluster. mission end state commint is emplaced, the qrf node and workshop are neutralized, caches and electronics are secured, skell personnel are recovered, and the iron phantom lead is transferred intact to bravo team at india 7. objectives alpha skell tech safehouse halo onto the skell tech location and retrieve the commint device staged there for the lake intercept phase. bravo ancient village eliminate the quick reaction force, secure weapons and ammunition caches, and prepare the site for quiet recovery by bandit 1-3. charlie blackwater lake array hold two-man overwatch while the diver element plants the commint device on the central hub of the floating antenna array for follow-on intercept. delta ugv prototype workshop secure the workshop quietly and prevent any alarm from reaching the nearby outpost before the hvt can be moved or warned. echo main outpost locate and apprehend the officer running iron phantom, then use the on-site helicopter to transfer the hvt to bravo team at site india 7 in hanged man wood. site india 7 reference for the final hvt handoff and on-site debrief linkup. ao and objective map area overview showing the alpha through echo chain, blackwater lake intercept site, and the final handoff route toward site india 7.' },
  { href: 'JSOC%20Ghost%20Division%20-%20%F0%9F%97%82%20OPERATIONS%20V%20-%20op-zephyr%20%5B1314986669182550026%5D.html', label: 'op-zephyr', searchLabel: 'op zephyr', text: 'operation zephyr operation zephyr multiple high-security research facilities in north central liberty are tied to the genesis pathogen program, human experimentation, and trafficking of live test subjects. the task force must infiltrate the network, secure viral samples and research, rescue civilians where possible, and prevent any catastrophic release before the enemy can disperse or burn the evidence. fob south cape station fob step-off 1730 brief / 1800 launch insertion mh-6 little bird to safehouse foxtrot extraction on-site helo from delta back to scc fob situation intelligence confirms an active bio-weapon development chain spread across several hardened compounds in north central liberty. the network is conducting viral manipulation, live human testing, and trafficking of detainees used as experimental subjects. intercepted communications identify the flagship pathogen as genesis , a weaponized agent with strategic-level threat potential. zephyr is tasked with breaking the facility chain, collecting viable samples and research, and recovering trapped civilians without triggering a large-scale contamination event. execution 1800 launch from south cape station fob with full cbrn loadout aboard mh-6 little bird platforms. insertion approach low to minimize radar exposure and land one klick west of alpha at safehouse foxtrot. isolation use emp and electronic warfare support to collapse local comms and prevent warning traffic between compounds. advance move on foot between objectives, stay off the road network, and use charlie team\'s cctv intercepts to confirm target activity. final at delta, seize the on-site helicopter, package the hvt, and return directly to south cape station fob for follow-on exploitation. priority intel hvt: blackwood, architect of the bio-weapon program. blackwood was last seen at the cryohope complex roofline with hostages and a dedicated security element. any on-site breacher is to be treated as part of the hvt package. mission end state viral material and research are secured, detainees are liberated where feasible, blackwood is apprehended, and the team extracts intact by captured aircraft without allowing the genesis program to scatter or leak. objectives alpha auroa hospital infiltrate the hospital, secure the top-floor laboratory, and collect all viral experiments and samples currently held on site. bravo eternity facility secure the compound and force access to the underground panic room, which is believed to contain critical research archives tied to the genesis program. charlie cryogenization site rescue civilians, breach the cryogenization room, and conduct full site exploitation for evidence, materials, and follow-on target data. delta cryohope complex free civilians under duress, apprehend blackwood and his detail, then transition immediately to rooftop extraction using the aircraft staged on site. initial surveillance of the north central liberty lab chain tied to viral development. terrain and compound spacing reinforce the need for low-signature movement between objectives. secondary site overview showing the scale and hardening of the facility network. additional visual confirmation of the operational environment and likely approach constraints. insertion reference for the little bird approach and landing zone near safehouse foxtrot. extraction concept showing the captured helicopter route from delta back to south cape station fob. tacmap rundown consolidated reference for insertion, alpha through delta sequencing, and the final aircraft extraction lane tied to blackwood\'s capture package.' },
  { href: 'op-terminal.html', label: 'op-terminal', searchLabel: 'op terminal', text: 'operation terminal operation terminal cobblestone industries has forced control of the rx6 project and rushed fatal human trials on auroa. delta team is tasked with cutting through the company leadership chain, securing key witnesses, and extracting both evidence and high-value detainees back to echo fob. fob echo fob step-off 1800 brief / 1930 launch insertion blackhawk via pelican 1-3 extraction ground convoy to erewhon situation a local cia ground branch asset has been working closely with journalist marika fairburn during her investigation into cobblestone industries. the company fronts as legitimate, but its record points to corruption, trafficking, narcotics movement, and direct involvement in the seizure of skell technology\'s umbrella nootropics research. rx6 was designed as a ptsd treatment meant to prevent traumatic memory encoding. cobblestone hijacked the program and rushed live trials, resulting in multiple civilian deaths. bravo team is assigned to secure the testing facility in liberty, while delta team targets cobblestone leadership and logistics on the ground. execution 1930 lift with pelican 1-3 by blackhawk and insert onto ardmore ridge. phase i recon site alpha from elevation, then continue the approach on foot. phase ii capture the supply chain officer at dunback farm and transfer him to bandit 2 at the abandoned site north of the farm. phase iii secure polaris residences, locate marika fairburn, and collect any additional intelligence on the cobblestone head office. final apprehend the cobblestone ceo at head office, gather evidence, then exfil to echo fob using on-site vehicles. all targets of opportunity are greenlit. priority intel witness to protect: marika fairburn last reported wearing rain boots, gray cargo pants, red plaid shirt, blue jacket, and a scarf . she has been conducting surveillance on the cobblestone head office and may hold follow-on evidence. mission end state cobblestone\'s logistics chief is captured, fairburn is recovered, the ceo is detained, and physical proof of the rx6 conspiracy is extracted to echo fob alongside the hvt package. objectives alpha dunback farm capture cobblestone\'s supply chain officer, identified as the "bagman." intelligence suggests he may be supervising narcotics shipments disguised as food deliveries. transfer abandoned site north of farm hand the bagman to bandit 2 at the designated relay point to keep the package moving while the team continues deeper into the target chain. bravo polaris residences clear the residences, establish contact with fairburn, and secure whatever intelligence she has compiled on cobblestone\'s head office activity. charlie head office secure the building, detain the ceo and his detail, recover evidence tied to the nootropics program, then exfil the hvt by ground vehicle to erewhon. insertion route and early terrain overview from the ardmore ridge approach. tacmap rundown infinity ao reference showing the relationship between insertion, objectives, handoff point, and final ground extraction route.' }
];
